title: pea pickin' cake
directions: Bake cake by directions on box for two 9-inch layers.
Cool completely.

title: ranch style chicken casserole
directions: Saute onion in a little butter or oleo.
Add soups, tomatoes and seasonings.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Cover the bottom of a 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking pan with broken tortilla chips.
Add chicken to soup mixture and pour mixture over chips.
Cover with grated cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: lasagna
directions: Shred last 3 cheeses and mix together; set aside.
Fry hamburger meat and rinse with hot water.
Blot dry.
Mix together with tomato paste and cottage cheese.
Layer bottom of dish with meat sauce.
Top with part of cheese mixture.
Layer with cooked noodles.
Repeat until sauce is gone.
Last layer:
noodles with cheese sprinkled on top.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Uncover to brown.

title: baked apples
directions: Core center of apples out.
Add dot of butter to opening on each apple.
Mix cinnamon and sugar.
Spoon into openings.
Wrap apples in heavy-duty foil and put into coals.
Cook 20 minutes. Check to see of soft and cooked.
May need up to 20 more minutes depending on heat of fire.

title: bread pudding
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Butter 1 loaf bread, cut into fourths. Layer pan and sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.
Do another layer the same.
Beat eggs; add milk.
Add sugar, vanilla and salt.
Mix well.
Pour over bread.
Set pan in another pan with water to bake. Bake for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix until well blended.

title: strawberry-pineapple bavarian
directions: In 1-quart glass measure, dissolve gelatin in 1 cup boiling water.
Stir in 1/2 cup cold water and the pineapple with its juice.
Refrigerate 30 minutes or until slightly thickened.

title: whole wheat molasses batter bread
directions: Heat the buttermilk, molasses and margarine in saucepan until margarine is melted and mixture is warm, not hot.
Mix the dry ingredients, including yeast in mixing bowl.
Add buttermilk mixture to dry ingredients and beat for 3 minutes.
Cover dough and set somewhere warm (not hot) and let rise 1 to 2 hours.
Beat the risen dough down with spoon.
Pour into 2 greased bread pans. Let rise 45 minutes.
Before bread is ready to bake, turn oven on. When hot, bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until done; drain.
Add to broccoli while hot the cheese and 1/2 stick butter.
Melt together 1/2 stick butter and Ritz crackers.
Sprinkle on top of broccoli.
Bake for 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: upside down cobbler
directions: Melt butter in baking dish (cake pan size).
In large bowl, mix all ingredients except butter and filling.
Pour batter over melted butter.
Do not stir.
Spoon in fruit pie filling.
Do not stir!
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: ambrosia pie(makes 2 pies)
directions: Mix pineapple, flour and sugar.
Cook until thick and clear. Cool.
Slice bananas in baked crusts.
Sprinkle nuts over bananas. Pour cooled pineapple mixture in.
Sprinkle coconut and top with Cool Whip.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: finger lickin' cake
directions: Mix and beat 3 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes (longer in oblong pan until done).

title: cucumber relish
directions: Boil 30 minutes.
Seal in hot jars.

title: german chocolate icing
directions: Beat egg yolks.
Add milk.
Cook over medium heat until it starts to thicken.
Add all other ingredients to it.
Beat until it is ready to spread on cake.

title: stilton cheese spread
directions: Bring ingredients to room temperature
process in food processor.	Serve with crackers.

title: egg rolls
directions: Combine pork, soy sauce and garlic powder.
Mix well.
Let stand for 10 minutes.
Heat 2 tablespoons oil in large skillet over medium heat.
Brown pork mixture in hot oil.
Add onion and cook for 2 minutes.
Add carrots, celery and cabbage.
Stir-fry until vegetables are tender crisp, drain and cool.
Dissolve flour in 1/4 cup of water.
Place about 2-3 tablespoons pork mixture on lower half of egg roll wrapper.
Fold bottom edge up to just cover filling.
Fold left and right edges 1/2 inch over; roll up jelly roll fashion.
Moisten top edge with flour mixture and seal. Complete all rolls.
Heat oil for frying in wok or large saucepan over high heat.
Deep fry rolls, a few at a time about 5-7 minutes or till golden brown.
Drain on paper towels.
Serve with mustard, catsup or sweet and sour sauce, as desired.

title: plain cake
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Beat 2 or 3 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.
Will make one 9 x 13-inch cake, 2 layers or 1 tube or Bundt cake.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Combine soup, mayonnaise, curry, lemon juice and grated cheese.
Slice cooked chicken and layer with cooked broccoli in casserole. Pour soup mixture over top layers.
Top with bread crumbs. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: ever ready muffin mix(yields 96 muffins)
directions: Sift flour, sugar, soda and salt together (using large mixing bowl).
Mix with cereal, raisins and nuts; make a well in center of mixture.
Pour in milk, eggs and oil.
Stir with a spoon, starting in center and work slowly to outside; stir only until moist.
Bake in greased muffin pan, 18 to 20 minutes at 400°. Batter maybe kept in refrigerator up to 6 weeks.
Do not freeze batter!

title: carrot cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Combine oil and sugar; mix well.
Sift together remaining dry ingredients.
Add 1/2 of dry ingredients to sugar mixture.
Blend.
Add other dry ingredients alternately with eggs, 1 at a time, mixing well after each.
Add carrots.
Mix well.
Add nuts; mix.

title: fox creek crab casserole
directions: Mix crab, salt, red peppers and vinegar.
Toss in cheese and mayonnaise.
Put into greased casserole dish.
Top with croutons and dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: marinated country fried steak or venison
directions: Place steak (or venison) in a shallow dish and sprinkle with garlic salt.
Pour soy sauce over meat.
Cover and marinate in refrigerator for 3 to 6 hours.
Drain.
Dredge steak or venison in flour.
Brown on both sides in hot oil over low heat.

title: field peas with snaps
directions: Pick a good mess of peas.
Be sure to get some snaps.
(I prefer a mixture of about 1/2 snaps to 1/2 shelled.)
Shell and snap peas.
Wash thoroughly several times, changing water each time.
Remove any "buggy" peas.

title: red beans
directions: In an 8-quart pot prepare the red beans and add enough stock to cover beans by 2 inches.
Add the rest of the ingredients and simmer covered for 2 hours, stirring occasionally so the beans won't stick.
Serve over cooked rice with chopped onion and hot peppers.
Serves 6 to 10.

title: cheese crisps
directions: Cream butter and cheese.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Add flour, a little at a time.
Add salt and cayenne and combine well. Add Rice Krispies and combine well.

title: frozen cherry salad
directions: Stir together topping and cream cheese.
Fold in pie filling. Put oranges into cherry mixture.
Line a pan (9 x 5 x 3-inch) loaf pan with waxed paper.
Freeze until firm.
To serve, let stand 10 minutes. Garnish with leftover orange slices.
Its fast and good and you can make this ahead.

title: connie's yeast rolls
directions: Bring water to a boil. Pour over sugar, shortening and salt. Stir to dissolve. Cool to lukewarm (115°).
Add yeast. Stir. Add beaten eggs. Stir in flour, 2 cups at a time.
Dough will be sticky. Cover and refrigerate 8 hours or overnight.
(Dough will keep at least a week in refrigerator.)

title: cheesy vegetable chowder
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in a large, heavy pot.
Bring to a boil and cook, covered, at low heat until potatoes are tender, about 20 minutes.
Add corn and remove from heat.

title: fettucini alfredo
directions: Cook and drain pasta in water, salt and oil.
Do not rinse pasta.
Toss pasta in butter and add cream, cheese and parsley. Toss again, then add egg.
Toss and serve immediately.
(You can leave out the egg if you worry whether it will cook completely when tossed in the hot pasta.)

title: s'mores
directions: Take graham selects square; add 6 milk chocolate squares.
Top it with a marshmallow; microwave on High for 10 to 15 seconds. Top it with a second graham cracker and enjoy.

title: cheesy sausage quiche
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Bake shell for 7 minutes.
Remove from oven and reduce temperature to 350°.
Brown sausage and drain. Reserve 2 tablespoons fat and cook and stir onion and green pepper in reserved fat.
Stir in sausage.
Spoon into pastry shell. Sprinkle with cheese.

title: cheesy baked potato
directions: Cut each potato into shoestrings and place in center of foil. Top with butter, cheese and salt and pepper to taste.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until tender using 1 piece tinfoil per potato.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add milk slowly while stirring.
Cook in double boiler until well thickened.
Pour over egg yolks, stirring rapidly.
Add margarine and pour back into top of double boiler. Cook a little longer.
Remove from heat, cool and add vanilla and coconut.
Pour into baked pastry shell.
Cover with meringue and sprinkle well with remaining coconut.
Place in 350° oven and brown.

title: chocolate cherry bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine in a large bowl, stir by hand until well mixed.
Pour into a 9x13-inch pan and bake 25 to 30 minutes.
Allow cake to cool 10 minutes, then start to make the icing.

title: italian pie
directions: Mix tuna, milk, eggs (beaten), cheese and spices in bowl. Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake 30 to 45 minutes in a 425° oven (until firm and lightly golden).

title: chile rellenos casserole
directions: Beat half and half with eggs and flour until smooth.
Split open chiles, rinse out seeds and drain on paper towel.
Mix cheeses.
Reserve 1/2 cup for topping.
Make alternate layers of remaining cheese, chiles and egg mixture in deep 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Pour tomato sauce over top.
Sprinkle with reserved cheese.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours or until cooked in center.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream the margarine and sugar.
Add eggs and salt.
Blend well.
Alternately add buttermilk and flour to mixture, blending as you add each.
Add bananas and nuts, if desired.

title: chicken and dressing casserole
directions: Cook chicken breasts in the 4 cups of water with salt to taste until tender.
Cool.
Remove skin and bone from chicken and set aside.
Cook onion and celery in a cup of the chicken broth until tender; add 1 can cream of chicken soup to onion/celery mixture and heat.
Mix cornbread crumbs, seasoned bread crumbs, onion/celery mixture and 3 or 4 cups of broth; add poultry seasoning, salt and pepper to taste.
Add 3 whole eggs and mix thoroughly.
Pout into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish and place boned pieces of chicken breast on top of dressing mixture.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 30 minutes or until lightly browned and bubbling in center of dish.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Cream butter or margarine with sugar.
Add eggs; beat well. Add milk and stir in coconut and pecans.
Add vanilla wafer crumbs.
Mix well.
Bake in a 9 or 10-inch tube pan in a 300° oven about 1 hour and 45 minutes, until done.
Cool; remove from pan.

title: baked chop suey
directions: Brown beef, onions and celery.
Put in casserole.
Add other ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Top with chow mein noodles.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine shortening and sugars.
Stir in eggs and vanilla.
Sift flour, salt and soda.
Stir into mixture.
Stir in oats, nuts and Reese's pieces.
Mix well.
Spoon by teaspoonful onto lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Boil the potatoes with skin on for 15 minutes. Brown hamburger and drain.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray Pam in casserole dish. Combine soup and hamburger (do not add water).
This dish is layered as you would a lasagna.

title: stuffed apple ring salad
directions: Core unpeeled apples and cut into 3/4-inch thick rings.
Dip in pineapple or lemon juice to prevent browning.
Set aside. Place cream cheese in a small mixing bowl; beat at medium speed with an electric mixer until smooth.
Add honey and beat at medium speed until light and fluffy.
Stir in dates and pecans.

title: peanut patties
directions: Microwave sugar, Karo, water and salt for 3 1/2 minutes on High.
Add	peanuts.
Microwave
9	minutes
on
High.
Add margarine, food coloring
and
vanilla.
When
color starts to change, drop by spoonfuls on wax paper.
If it gets too stiff, reheat.
For a different flavor, parch peanuts first.

title: tomato gravy
directions: Pour in about 1 pint to 3/4 quart of tomato juice.
Cook over medium heat, stirring, until it begins to thicken.
May use 2 beef flavored bouillon cubes in place of the meat drippings.

title: spareribs and sauerkraut
directions: Pork chops can be substituted for spareribs.
Simply brown them in a little oil before assembling.
Cut spareribs into serving-size pieces.
Spread 2 cups sauerkraut in the bottom of a 3 to 4-quart casserole.
Top with half the ribs, half the potato pieces, half the diced apple and half the onion.
Add another layer of 2 cups sauerkraut and repeat remaining ribs, potatoes, apple and onion.
Top with remaining sauerkraut.
Combine brown sugar and water.
Pour over casserole, cover and bake at 325° for 2 to 3 hours.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Boil and debone chicken until double.
Cut into bite-size pieces.
Place in the bottom of a medium size casserole dish. Then mix in a separate bowl the following: cream of chicken soup, sour cream, crushed Ritz crackers. Mix well.
Add the poppy seed. Mix together well with the mixture.
Pour evenly on top of diced chicken.
Melt the butter and pour evenly over the top.
Bake uncovered for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: hurricane cake
directions: Spray or grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle 1 cup of coconut on bottom of pan.
Sprinkle 1 cup chopped pecans over coconut.
Mix cake mix like directions on box.
Pour over coconut and nuts.
In a bowl, blend together butter, cream cheese, powdered sugar and vanilla; this will be stiff.
Drop by big teaspoonfuls on top of cake mix.
Do not put this mixture close to edge of pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 12.

title: baked potato crisps
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Oil 2 nonstick baking sheets with olive oil.
Cut potatoes 1/8-inch thick.
Place potatoes in a bowl and toss with olive oil to coat evenly.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Place on baking sheets.
Bake until crisp and brown for 20 to 25 minutes.
Put on serving dish and sprinkle with chives and parsley.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream sugars and shortening; add eggs, beating well. Add vanilla and milk. Mix in remaining ingredients. Roll into balls; placing on cookie sheet, flatten with fork. Bake at 400° for 8 - 10 minutes.

title: risotto-style potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes and shred.
Bring broth, onion and thyme to a boil in saucepan.
Stir in potatoes.
Simmer, covered, stirring frequently, 20 minutes, or until tender.
Remove from heat.
Stir in sour cream, Parmesan cheese and pepper.

title: chocolate cookies with whiskey
directions: In a bowl, knead butter with the grated cookies.
Add the chocolate, the yolks and whiskey.
Mix everything very well. Shape small balls and sprinkle with sugar.
Serve them in baking paper cups (cookies size).

title: broccoli dip
directions: Thaw broccoli.
Add to 1 stick melted butter.
Don't drain juice.
Cube the Velveeta and melt.
Mix together.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Whip with electric mixer the cottage cheese and Cool Whip. Drain crushed pineapple and add to mixture along with dry jello. Drain oranges and whip into mixture (1/2 can).
Fold in remaining half of can with spoon.
Refrigerate at least 4 hours.

title: texas egg custard
directions: Mix all well and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake 45 minutes in 350° oven or until set.
Makes 2 small or one large 10 inch pie.

title: oyster cracker munchies
directions: Heat oil to lukewarm, add all ingredients except crackers. Put crackers in Tupperware container or bread wrapper.
Pour the oil mixture over crackers, shake to mix.
Let stand 1/2 hour before serving.
Store in container.
Will stay fresh for days.

title: bread pudding
directions: Put cubed bread into a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Beat together the eggs, milk and sugar and pour over the bread. Sprinkle top with cinnamon.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.

title: eddie's dills
directions: Bring first 4 ingredients to a boil.
Pack cucumbers in a jar with lots of dill (fresh) and garlic.
Then pour boiling liquid over cukes.
Cover; let cool and then keep refrigerated.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: green chili rice casserole
directions: Mix rice and sour cream.
Remove seeds and veins from chiles and chop (chile peppers in small can).
In casserole put a layer of rice mixture, then a layer of chiles and next a layer of cheese. Alternate layers, ending up with cheese on top.
Bake at 350° approximately 30 minutes.

title: chili sauce
directions: Cook one hour and seal in jars.

title: soft chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream margarine and shortening together.
Add brown and white sugar.
Mix thoroughly.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix well.
Add dry ingredients; blend well.
Add chocolate chips.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto cookie sheet.
Bake 10 minutes in a 375° oven.

title: lo-fat broccoli casserole
directions: In a large bowl, combine broccoli, egg substitute, soup and mayonnaise.
Stir in Cheddar cheese, onions and dash of pepper.

title: french cream dip(great with fruit.)
directions: Whip the cream; add sugar and blend well. Add cream cheese and vanilla; blend until smooth. Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: german potato soup
directions: Dissolve bouillon cubes in water; add carrots, celery and onions and simmer for 20 minutes.
Add potatoes and simmer 20 more minutes or until tender.
Turn heat down and add cheese and cream of chicken soup.
Garnish with bacon bits.

title: chocolate icing
directions: Boil 2 minutes.
Cool to lukewarm.
Add vanilla and beat until right consistency.

title: adele's new orleans style gumbo
directions: Brown flour in oil to a very brown roux.
Lower heat and add onion, garlic and green onions. Simmer until onions are cooked. Add shrimp, crabs and oysters. Simmer until shrimp are pink and (if used) oysters curl.
Add okra, water, bay leaf, salt, pepper and Tabasco sauce and cook until done.
Serve in bowl over boiled rice.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Pare potatoes and cut into 1/4-inch slices.
Place in greased 2-quart casserole or baking dish.
In medium saucepan, melt butter.
Add onion and cook until tender.
Blend in flour, salt and pepper.
Remove from heat and stir in milk.
Return to heat and cook, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens slightly and comes to a boil.
Pour over potatoes, cover and bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Uncover and bake 1 hour longer until potatoes are tender.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: caramel pecan rolls
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover the bottom of pan evenly with pecans.
Place frozen dough nuggets in rows on top.
Sprinkle butterscotch pudding mix on top.
Melt butter and mix in cinnamon and brown sugar to make a syrup.
Pour over top of all.
Place a damp cloth over pan and allow to rise in cold oven overnight. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Turn out onto foil lined cookie sheet.

title: ham or turkey quiche
directions: In blender, mix together egg, onions, light cream, salt, sugar and Tabasco.
Set aside.
Sprinkle meat, broccoli and Mozzarella in bottom of uncooked pie shell.
Pour egg mixture over this and bake in preheated oven at 425° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 300° and bake 30 minutes longer or until knife inserted 1-inch from edge comes out clean.
Let stand 10 minutes before cutting.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: sour cream cake
directions: Mix brown sugar and pecans; reserve.
Mix cake mix and add ingredients.
Pour half of mixture in Bundt pan.
Sprinkle with 1/2 brown sugar mixture.
Add rest of batter and cover with remaining sugar mixture.
Cook 1 hour at 350°.
Use favorite frosting.

title: beaver burgers
directions: Grind beaver, potatoes and onion in a food grinder.
Add garlic powder, salt and pepper to taste and the Worcestershire sauce.
Mix well and form into patties.

title: strawberry rhubarb pie
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into pastry shell. Crisscross pastry strips over top.
Bake at 400° for 50 minutes. Cool completely.

title: fresh vegetable pizza
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients together and set aside.
Spread the crescent rolls on a large cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 5 to 8 minutes.
Let cool. Spread dip on rolls.
Add chopped vegetables. Top off with the cheese.
Pop in oven until cheese melts. Cut into small squares. Great appetizers or quick treats.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix together.
Shape into a ball.
Chill 2 to 3 hours.

title: alma's cherry pie
directions: Combine crumbs and oleo.
Press in bottom of oblong baking dish and bake for 15 minutes at 325°.
Chill.
Cream together milk, sugar and cream cheese.
Spread over crust.
Whip cream stiffly (Cool Whip can be used instead of cream).
Add vanilla. Put layer of chopped nuts between layers of cream cheese and whipping cream.
Chill.
Spread cherry filling over this layer. Chill overnight and serve.
Good to make ahead.

title: heavenly banana cake
directions: Mash bananas, sprinkle with lemon juice. Stir pie filling into cake mix, add eggs and water. Blend to moisten. Stir in bananas, oil, nuts. Mix 2 minutes on medium speed of mixer. Pour into greased
and floured 13 x 9 x 2 pan. Bake in 350 degree oven for 35 minutes or until done. Cool - Frost with 9 oz. carton Cool Whip. Sprinkle with coconut.

title: tater-tot casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Brown ground beef, drain.
Add mushroom soup and 1/2 can water, simmer for 5 min.
Place in 9x12 pan, and put frozen tots on top of beef mixture.
Put in 350 degree oven for 30 min.
Turn on broiler to brown tots.
After browning tots, sprinkle cheese on top, put under broiler and brown.
Cool sightly and serve.

title: rice pudding
directions: In a large, heavy pot, combine milk, sugar and rice.
Stir until mixture begins to boil.
Reduce and simmer for 45 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat.
Beat egg with water. Add vanilla and nutmeg.
Stir into cooked mixture.
Blend thoroughly.
Serves 6.

title: diabetic cake
directions: Cook raisins in water until water is evaporated.
Add applesauce, eggs, sweetener and oil; mix well.
Blend in soda and flour.
Add cinnamon, nutmeg and vanilla.
Pour into 8 x 8-inch pan (greased and floured).
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: peanut butter snack cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Use greased cookie sheet.
Blend oil, peanut butter, honey and egg.
Add rest of ingredients; mix well. Roll into 2-inch balls.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Press flat with a fork.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes about 3 dozen cookies.

title: spinach and artichoke dip
directions: Gather all ingredients, then pour the needed amount of artichoke hearts into a colander and allow to drain thoroughly. Then rough chop into 1/2 inch pieces.
Place all ingredients into large mixing bowl and using rubber spatula mix all ingredients together.
Place 6 ounces of mixture evenly into a bowl; cover and refrigerate.
Microwave until hot.

title: chocolate cream
directions: Melt the chocolate, sugar, Espresso and cinnamon together in a heavy saucepan over low heat, stirring constantly so it doesn't stick.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla; stir again.
Chill for 4 hours or more.
To serve, pour into 6 large dessert glasses.
Whip the heavy cream until soft peaks hold; spoon over top.

title: grandma's sour cream cake
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
Cream sugar and butter with mixer in large bowl until smooth; add eggs one at a time.
Add 1 cup of flour and 1/2 of sour cream; mix together well.
Then add remaining of flour and sour cream.
Mix until smooth and creamy. Stir in vanilla and almond flavoring.
Pour in 9-inch greased tube cake pan.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 375°.
Do not open oven door or cake will fall.
Let cool before cutting.

title: 13 bean soup(serves 8)
directions: Rinse and sort beans before cooking.
Cover beans with water. Add 2 tablespoons salt.
Soak overnight and drain.
Add 2 quarts fresh water and ham or ham hock.
Bring to a boil, simmer 3 hours. Add onion and tomatoes.
Add one of the following three: pod of red pepper, chili powder or green chopped chilies.
Add juice of lemon.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer another 30 minutes or 1 hour.
Flavor improves with age.

title: swiss scalloped corn
directions: Cook bacon until crisp and crumble.
Combine bacon, corn and cheese and place into a 2-quart oblong baking dish.

title: country style steak
directions: Dredge steak in flour, salt and pepper.
Brown thoroughly in oil.
Remove from oil; stir in 1 tablespoon flour.
Blend in water; stir to smooth gravy.
Add steak.
Cover tightly; simmer for 2 hours.

title: sweet potato soup
directions: In a Dutch oven or large (preferably nonstick) saucepot, saute the onion in the oil until the onion is translucent.
Add the tomatoes (including juice) and cook the mixture for about 5 minutes. Add the sweet potatoes, broth and water.
Bring the soup to a boil. Reduce the heat and simmer the soup for 20 or so minutes or until the potatoes are soft.
Puree the soup in a food processor or in batches in a blender or pass through a food mill. Return to the pan.
Add the salt (if desired) and pepper to taste and heat the soup thoroughly.
Serve garnished with parsley. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Cut chicken breasts into cubes.
Cook and brown until done. In bowl mix drained vegetables and celery soup.
Add chicken. Pour into pie shell.
Top with second pie shell.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: mama's goop
directions: Brown onion and ground meat on stove.
Add soup, tomatoes, rice and 2 cups water, stirring thoroughly.
Pour into large baking dish (spray dish with Pam). Top with cheese.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.
Enjoy!
Feeds a family of four for 2 days!!

title: pina colada salad
directions: Mix pudding (dry) with pineapple (undrained); Add coconut and Cool Whip. Mix cream cheese and sugar together and fold into other ingredients. Chill. You can put extra coconut on top.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix oil, sugar and eggs well.
Add dry ingredients; mix all in a large bowl.
Bake in greased and floured oblong cake pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: bread pudding
directions: Soak and squeeze bread (enough for baking pan).
Sift together flour, baking powder and spices.
Combine with raisins.
Bake in slow oven at 300° for about 1 hour.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Mix veggies, ham and cheese in baking pan.
Make white sauce with remaining ingredients and pour over potatoes.
(Can shorten process by not cooking white sauce ingredients, simply mix well and pour over.)
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Uncover and bake 60 more minutes, until potatoes are tender.

title: cheddar muffins
directions: Grease or spray muffin pan.
Stir together flour, cheese, sugar, baking powder, salt and pepper.
Make a well in center.
In a small bowl, combine egg milk and oil.
Add egg mixture to flour mixture.
Stir just until moistened.
Batter should be lumpy. Fold in crumbled bacon.
Fill prepared muffin pan cups.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes, until golden.
Remove from pan.
Serve while warm.

title: texas chili
directions: Brown first 5 ingredients in skillet; drain off grease.
In a large pan, put 1 cup cooked rice; add meat mixture, beans, chili mix, chili powder and salt to taste.
Stir and simmer about 30 minutes.
You may need to add some water while simmering.
Mixture will be real thick.
Serves 8 to 10 people.

title: crescent house hot chicken salad
directions: Combine everything but the cheese and potato chips in a greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch casserole dish.
Combine cheese and potato chips and sprinkle on top.
Bake in preheated oven at 325° for 45 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and top with more grated cheese or bread crumbs mixed with melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes. Serves 10 to 12.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 2 cups boiling water.
Add pineapple and blueberry filling.
Place in dish and refrigerate.

title: strawberry heaven
directions: Cut cake horizontally into 3 layers.
Place 1 cake layer on serving plate.
Spread 1/4 cup of the fruit spread on cake layer. Top with 1/2 cup of the whipped topping.
Repeat layers, ending with cake.
Frost top and sides of cake with remaining whipped topping.
Refrigerate 1 hour or until ready to serve.
Decorate top and sides of cake with strawberry slices and mint leaves. Store leftover cake in refrigerator.
Makes 12 servings.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar until creamy and smooth.
Mash the bananas through a coarse sieve and mix with the sugar and butter mixture.
Add the lightly beaten eggs, lemon juice, nutmeg and raisins.
Sift the salt and baking powder with the flour.
Combine the two mixtures and bake in an oiled bread pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: grandma's chocolate chip-coconut bars
directions: Mix.
Spread into a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Cook ground beef, green pepper and onion until browned and beef is crumbly.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour into a greased 1-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Microwave butter in 4-quart bowl for 1 minute or until melted. Add sugar, Karo and milk.
Mix well.
Microwave on High for 3 minutes.
Stir good and microwave on High for 3 minutes.
Stir good and scrape bowl.
Microwave another 3 minutes more.
Stir well and add chocolate chips and nuts.
Mix well.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch dish. Cool at room temperature.

title: chicken curry casserole
directions: Cook and debone chicken. Cut into bite-size pieces and layer on bottom of casserole dish. Layer pieces of broccoli on top of chicken. Mix soup, mayonnaise and curry powder.
Pour over chicken and broccoli. Cover with shredded cheese and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until cheese is bubbly.
Serve with rice or dinner rolls. Serves 4.

title: apple pie cake
directions: Mix apples, 5 tablespoons sugar and cinnamon and set aside. Combine remaining ingredients; beat until smooth.
Thoroughly grease and flour large tube pan.
(It helps to line the pan with paper.
Grease pan, then grease and flour paper.
Turn out and remove paper while still warm.)

title: hot and spicy fried rice
directions: In skillet, put oil. Stir-fry the onions and red bell pepper. Add the rice. Stir-fry. Add the
egg.
Add the chicken. Add seasoning mixture, sugar, soy sauce and water, then mix all this together.
Pour over the rice and let cook for 1 minute.

title: spinach balls
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix thoroughly.
Refrigerate until well chilled.
Shape into walnut size balls.
Bake in single layer on ungreased pan.
Bake in 350° oven 30 minutes.

title: southern red beans
directions: Sort and wash red beans.
Add cut sausage, onion, bell pepper, garlic, salt and pepper.
Make your roux in a separate pan.
Roux is made by browning flour in cooking oil.
Pour roux over other ingredients (bean and sausage mixture) to thicken the liquid in the pot.	Cook until beans are done.

title: mashed potato casserole
directions: Brown hamburger with onion, salt & pepper.
Drain fat.	Mix in soup and green beans.
Spread potatoes on top & sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: japanese chicken salad
directions: In a frying pan, pour the salad oil, add the almonds and noodles; stir fry until browned.
Drain on a paper towel.
In a large bowl, combine the noodle mixture, chicken, cabbage and onions.
Make a dressing with the salad oil, vinegar and sugar and mix into the salad.

title: strawberry-banana pie
directions: Dissolve jello in water.
Add unthawed frozen strawberries. Break up berries with fork.
As the berries thaw the jello will thicken.
Stir in sliced bananas.

title: easy crescent rolls
directions: Mix all together.
Put in a greased bowl.
Cover with wax paper and a wet towel.
Refrigerate overnight.
Roll 1/2 of dough into a circle and cut into pie-shaped wedges.
Each circle should make 16 rolls.
Roll up and let raise 2 hours.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Yield:
They may be frozen and then allowed to raise 3 to 4 hours.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Mix all ingredients until well blended.
Spread evenly in large pizza pan (14 inch) that has been lined with foil and sprayed with Pam.
Bake 350° for 20-25 minutes or until lightly brown top with following spread.

title: mud fish stew
directions: In a large pot, heat vegetable oil.
Add sauteed onions.
Roll fish that you have cut up into 3-inch pieces in flour.
Place into pot with onion.
Cook on medium heat until slightly brown, turning once.
Mix catsup and water together and pour into pot.
Pour water off of potatoes into a bowl with catsup and stir up and add this to meat pot.
Add potatoes to stew.
Add minced garlic, bell pepper and hot sauce.
Simmer.
Serve over plain rice.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Cook soup bones with lean beef.
When done, remove the bones. Add tomatoes, chopped celery, chopped carrots, onion and potatoes. Cook until all vegetables are done.
Add macaroni that has been cooked separately and drained.
Add corn that has been cooked separately; may stick if added at beginning.
If soup needs more liquid, add water, tomato juice or V-8 juice.

title: easy chocolate cake
directions: Measure and sift the flour, cocoa, soda, baking powder and salt.
Beat shortening and sugar; cream well.
Add alternately with dry ingredients and mix well.
Add buttermilk or sour milk, boiling water and vanilla.
Dough will be thin.
Bake in hot oven at 375° to 400°.

title: sausage quiche
directions: Line shell with cheese and sausage.
Pour other combined ingredients over sausage and cheese.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: fresh fruit ice cream
directions: In ice cream container, combine all ingredients and mix well. Freeze according to manufacturer's instructions.
Freeze leftovers.

title: inez nix's prune cake
directions: Blend sugar, oil and eggs.
Add dry ingredients.
Add baking soda to buttermilk.
Add to mixture.
Mix well but do not beat. Add prunes and nuts.
Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour into pan and bake at 300° until cake pulls away from sides of pan.

title: easy cocoa mix
directions: Mix well.
Store in airtight container to keep powder dry.

title: cream valley dip
directions: Blend cottage cheese and milk in a blender until smooth.
Add salad dressing mix.
Blend until thoroughly mixed.

title: bourbon franks
directions: Mix all ingredients except franks in crock-pot.
Cook on high until bubbly; add franks.
Turn on low and let simmer.
Serve from crock-pot.

title: vegetable marinated salad
directions: Prepare dressing according to package directions.
Combine all vegetables and pour dressing over them.
Stir well.
Place in refrigerator and stir occasionally.
Keeps well chilled.

title: saturday night sandwich
directions: Grind the cheese, onion, green pepper and bacon.
Add the soup, and seasonings.
Split 6 buns and spread half of each with the mixture.
Cover with bun tops and place in moderate hot oven until that wonderful filling has melted.
Serve hot.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Drain beans.
Put them in a 6-quart heavy pot and add 3 quarts water.
Cover and simmer for 1 hour or until beans are tender. Watch that water does not boil down too far.
The beans must have water on them at all times.
Add the rest of the ingredients, except the cooked rice, to the pot and more water to cover, if needed.
Simmer partially covered, for 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until liquid has thickened.
Serve over cooked rice.

title: chicken & noodles
directions: Boil chicken with salt, peppercorns, celery, carrots, and onions.
Take chicken out.
Debone and shred chicken.
Add chicken back to broth and add package of frozen noodles.
Follow directions on noodles to cook.
Serve over mashed potatoes.

title: baked sweet potatoes
directions: Mix apple filling with sweet potatoes.
Dot with margarine and brown sugar.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: blt dip
directions: Cook bacon crisp and dice.
Dice tomatoes.
Mix all ingredients 1 day ahead and serve with toast or crackers.

title: kernville slush
directions: Mix and boil 7 cups water and 1 cup sugar for 1 minute; cool. Boil 2 more cups water and add tea bags or instant tea.
Add frozen orange juice, frozen lemonade and 1 1/2 cups vodka.
Put mixture in freezer.
Next morning, add 1 1/2 cups more Vodka and slush it up.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix ingredients; place in buttered 2-quart casserole dish. Top with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: french dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients in blender and blend until smooth.

title: choc-oat-chip cookies
directions: Beat the shortening and sugar until creamy.
Add eggs, milk and vanilla; beat well.
Add dry ingredients, chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet. Bake for 9 to 10 minutes for a chewy cookie or 12 to 13 minutes for a crisp cookie.

title: apple dapple cake
directions: Mix sugar, eggs and oil. Add dry ingredients, mixing well. Add apples and nuts.
Pour into a greased and floured jelly roll pan. Sprinkle butterscotch chips over the top. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: spicy texas casserole
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and green pepper.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes covered and 15 minutes more uncovered.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix together.
Add mayonnaise to make creamy enough to dip. Tastes better when made the night before.

title: baked pork chops and sauerkraut
directions: Heat the oven to 350°.

Heat the oil in a large skillet and brown the pork chops on both sides over medium heat. Place the browned pork chops in a casserole dish. Pour sauerkraut over the chops and top with caraway seeds, sliced onions and pepper. Bake.

title: chicken with egg dumplings
directions: Stew the chicken until tender. Add the cooked diced potatoes. Mix the flour with the milk. Add to stewed chicken. Top with Egg Dumplings. Cook about 20 minutes.

title: fruit cake
directions: Combine nuts, fruit and raisins in a large bowl.
Toss with 1 cup flour to coat.
Set aside.
Cream butter and sugar; add eggs one at a time, beating each addition. Sift together 2 cups of flour and baking powder.
Add in thirds to the creamed mixture. Mix well.
Add batter to the fruit and nuts.
Add lemon extract; mix well.
Transfer to well-greased tube pan.
Cover tightly with foil.
Place pan of water on bottom grate in oven.
Bake the cake on shelf above the water in a 300° oven for 2 1/2 hours.
Remove foil.
Cook 3 to 5 minutes longer.
Cool.
Remove from pan and brush with syrup.
Pour a little bourbon or brandy over the cake. Wrap in cheesecloth and store in a tin.

title: salmon patties
directions: In a
bowl, combine the first 7 ingredients; mix well. Shape into 6 patties. In a skillet, fry patties in butter over medium heat for 3 to 4 minutes on each side or until heated through.

title: 7-layered salad
directions: Shred lettuce; place in bowl.
Layer the onion, bell pepper, carrot, celery and peas last.
Mix together the mayonnaise and sugar; spread over top of salad, sealing around edges.
Put on cheese.
Crumble bacon on top.
Chill.

title: fruit smoothie
directions: Combine all ingredients except yogurt in container of electric blender.
Process until smooth.
Add yogurt and process until just blended.
Yields 4 cups (142 calories per 1-cup serving). Contains 4 g protein, 1.2 g fat, 31.3 g carbohydrate, 3 mg cholesterol, 41 mg sodium and 118 mg calcium.

title: chicken a'la orange
directions: Sprinkle chicken breasts with paprika and salt.
Melt margarine in skillet; brown chicken slightly on each side.
Add marmalade, tarragon and lemon juice.
Lower heat, simmer about 20 minutes.

title: wiener goulash
directions: In a 2-quart saucepan, fill half with water and half with tomato sauce.
Cut ingredients in 1-inch pieces.
Cook for 1 hour before serving.
Season to taste.
Serves 2 for 3 days.
Next day, flavor is better.
The third day flavor is best.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Use heavy skillet.
Saute onion in butter.
Stir in meat, garlic, flour, salt, onion, pepper, paprika and mushrooms.
Saute for 5 minutes.
Add soup and simmer, uncovered, for 10 minutes. Turn off flame and add sour cream and mix.
Serve on rice or noodles.
Makes 6 servings.

title: tortilla torte
directions: Melt chocolate chips and mix with 4 cups sour cream.
Mix powdered sugar with remaining 2 cups sour cream.
Keep separate.

title: summer squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion for 5 minutes; drain.
Combine chicken soup and sour cream.
Stir in shredded carrots.
Add squash and onions.
Mix stuffing and butter together.
Put half of stuffing on the bottom.
Add the rest to the top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pioneer beans
directions: Brown hamburger, chopped bacon and onions.
Partially drain the beans.
Mix with the above and simmer 20 minutes.
Mix with the remainder of ingredients.
Put in crock-pot.

title: macaroni and cheese casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In a skillet brown meat, onion and Tabasco sauce or red pepper sauce.
When done, drain macaroni.
Add to meat; mix with mushroom soup.
Pour into a casserole dish that has been sprayed with Pam.
Bake 30 minutes.
Add a few slices of cheese on top and bake until cheese has melted.
Cook macaroni according to package directions.

title: marinated shrimp
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients and pour over cooked shrimp, layered with sliced onions.
Let marinate 12 to 48 hours in refrigerator.

title: pineapple fruit dip
directions: Over low heat, cook the pineapple, egg, sugar and flour until thick.
Cool.
Stir well.
Fold in Cool Whip and softened cream cheese.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: scrabble
directions: Mix all salad oil, Worcestershire sauce, garlic salt and seasoning salt and pour over nuts, wheat squares, Cheerios, rice squares and pretzels.
Mix in large roaster.
Bake 2 hours at 250°, stirring several times.

title: seafood casserole
directions: Melt butter (do not brown).
Add onion, parsley and clams. Add bread crumbs, a little at a time, until butter is absorbed. Mix should be dry.
Sprinkle with lemon.
Butter medium size casserole and alternate seafood and crumb mixture starting with fillet of sole; add crumbs, then scallops, crumbs, shrimp, crumbs, lobster and cover with rest of crumb mixture.
Place pads of margarine on top; sprinkle with lemon.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Test to be sure all seafood is cooked.

title: raw vegetable dip
directions: Mix ingredients thoroughly.
Refrigerate.
Serve with your favorite raw vegetables.

title: jimmy coffee cake
directions: Mix all ingredients in bowl, except jimmies.
Beat for 4 minutes.
Add jimmies by hand.

title: crumb cake
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients.
Remove 3/4 cup for Crumb Topping.
To balance of mix, add remaining ingredients.
Mix all ingredients into a smooth, thick batter.
Grease a tube pan and dust with flour.
Pour mix into tube pan.
Sprinkle the 3/4 cup of crumbs for topping.
Bake at 350° for about 50 minutes (ovens vary) or, bake until tester comes out dry.
(I have baked cake at 375° for 35 minutes and it works in my oven.)

title: pineapple cream cheese layer cake
directions: Prepare Jiffy cake mix as directed on package.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan.
Bake until golden brown. (Cake will be thin.)
Remove cooled cake from pan.

title: tomato noodles
directions: Make up biscuit dough, except add two eggs.
Make dough real stiff.
Let stand 1 hour, then roll out as thin as possible on floured board.
Cut into strips as you would dumplings.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: In small microwave bowl, combine butter and onion; cook for two minutes in microwave.
Drain asparagus, place into baking dish.
Pour soup over asparagus and add onion mixture.
Place cheese over top and cover with fried onion rings.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until brown.

title: baked pork chops and rice
directions: Butter bottom of an 11 x 8-inch baking dish.
Cover bottom with rice.
Sprinkle soup mix over rice.
In separate bowl, mix soup, water and milk until smooth; pour over rice and place pork chops on top.
Bake 2 hours at 300°.

title: savory pork casserole
directions: Trim excess fat from chops.
Brown in 2 tablespoons oil, season with salt and pepper.
Set aside.
Saute yellow rice, onions and celery for 5 minutes in remaining 2 tablespoons oil.
Add raisins and stir to mix.
Add boiling water.
Turn into oblong casserole. Top with chops, cover and bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Top pork chops with apple rings brushed with melted butter and sprinkle with nutmeg.
Cover and bake 25 minutes longer.
If desired, run under broiler to brown apple rings.

title: mrs. crawfoot's strawberry pie
directions: Slice strawberries and place in graham cracker crust.
In heavy saucepan place sugar, water and cornstarch.
Cook until clear and thick.
Remove from heat.
Add jello.
Mix well.
Let cool.
Spoon over every berry.
Refrigerate for at least 2 hours before serving.
Top with Cool Whip before serving.

title: potato mints
directions: These are delicious and easy to make and inexpensive.
Add salt and oil of peppermint to hot mashed potatoes.
Work in enough confectioners sugar to make a stiff dough that will hold its shape when made into balls with the fingers.
Place balls on wax paper to set.
These are creamy and good.
They keep well when stored. Other flavoring may be used in place of peppermint if desired.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together.
Add remaining ingredients. Pour into one 9-inch unbaked pie crust at 350° until done.

title: creamy peach dessert
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Combine peaches with sugar, lemon juice and salt.
Add this to gelatin.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Fold in whipped cream.
Pour gelatin mixture into pan.
Chill overnight.
Garnish with fresh peaches.

title: microwave peach crisp
directions: Arrange peaches in square microwave dish (8 x 8 x 2-inch). Mix remaining ingredients until crumbly; sprinkle over peaches. Microwave, uncovered, on High for 6 minutes; rotate dish 1/2 turn. Microwave until peaches are tender, 4 to 6 minutes longer.
Serve with ice cream or whipped cream, if desired.
Makes 6 servings.

title: apple cake
directions: Add sugar gradually to oil, beating until well creamed.
Add eggs and vanilla in a separate bowl.
Sift flour, salt, cloves and cinnamon together, then combine with sugar and oil.
Add nuts and apples.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan or two 8 x 8-inch pans.
Bake at 325° for 70 minutes.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar when done.

title: white fruit cake
directions: Mix flour, nuts, and fruit with 1/2 of the flour.
Add baking powder to the other 1/2 of the flour.
Cream butter and sugar. Add egg whites, beaten until stiff.
Add vanilla flavoring.
In another bowl combine other ingredients and mix well.
Combine with butter/sugar mixture.
Mix well.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan and bake in slow oven on 250° for about 2 hours.
This usually makes 2 good size cakes.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: In saucepan, cook mushrooms and onions covered in the 1/4 cup butter 10 minutes or until tender.
Remove vegetables, leaving butter in skillet.
Set vegetables aside.
Blend flour, chicken bouillon granules, salt, nutmeg and dash of pepper into skillet. Add milk all at once.
Cook and stir until bubbly.
Stir in mushrooms and onion, cooked asparagus and lemon juice.
Turn into a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Combine crumbs and melted butter. Sprinkle atop.
Bake uncovered in at 350° oven 35 to 40 minutes. Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: lemon-lime punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aid according to directions on package.
Add pineapple juice.
Just before serving, add chilled ginger ale. (This can be frozen.
Pour ginger ale over it when it is partially thawed.)

title: broccoli puff
directions: Cook broccoli slightly and place in a greased casserole dish. Mix the next 5 ingredients and spoon over broccoli.
Sprinkle bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until set.

title: chow mein
directions: Cut meat into thin strips; brown lightly in oil.
Add onion, water and seasonings (including bouillon cubes).
Cover tightly and simmer 20 minutes or until meat is almost tender.
Add celery, bean sprouts and mushrooms. Cook 3 minutes, covered tightly.
Make paste of cornstarch and water.
Stir into meat and vegetable mixture.
Continue to stir gently until mixture is thickened, about 2 minutes.
Serve on Chinese noodles.
Yield: 8 servings. Carbohydrate 15 g, protein 15 g, fat 16 g, calories 264.
One serving = 1 bread starch exchange, 2 meat low-fat exchange, 2 fat exchange.
One-half cup Chinese noodles = 1 bread starch exchange, 1 fat exchange.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Heat sugar and milk to a rolling boil.
Boil one minute, stirring constantly.
Add chocolate and salt.
Stir until melted. Beat until smooth with hand rotary beater.
Add butter and extract.
Makes about 2 cups.
Keep refrigerated.

title: lentils with rice
directions: Rinse lentils and add to water.
Bring to boil and cook over medium heat for 15 minutes.
Saute onions in oil until golden brown; add rice and salt.
Cover and simmer 20 to 25 minutes or until rice and lentils are fluffy.
Be careful rice and lentils don't stick.
Place on serving platter and completely cover the lentils and rice with the fried onions.
May be served hot or cold. Serves 6.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Cook fat hen and dice meat.
Saute celery, pimentos and onion in a small amount of butter.
Make chicken gravy very thick from stock, thicken with cornstarch or flour.
Cut up 2 hard-boiled eggs into gravy.
Add sauteed vegetables, 2 cans of mixed peas and carrots and the diced chicken.
Pour into long baking dish and cover with pie crust.
(Bottom crust is optional.)
Bake in moderate oven (350°) until brown, about 45 minutes.

title: homemade butter
directions: Mix together; whip until fluffy.

title: potato soup
directions: Combine all ingredients up to and including pepper in a large pot.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer until veggies are tender (15 to 20 minutes).
Add milk; heat until milk is hot.
Blend flour and 1/2 cup milk; stir into soup.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Add margarine and serve.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Toss together the first 4 ingredients.
Mix in the mayo and mustard.

title: easy and hot peas
directions: Heat the soup.
Add the cheese and stir until melted.
Season to taste; add drained peas.
Serves 8.

title: barbecue ribs
directions: Put onion on ribs and bake at 450° for 45 minutes.
Combine all remaining ingredients; mix well.
Remove meat from oven and drain off grease.
Spoon sauce over meat and bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: chess pie
directions: Sift brown and white sugar, flour and salt.
Add eggs, milk and butter. Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: strawberry punch bowl cake
directions: Cool cake after baking.
Crush strawberries.
Pull apart cake into small chunks; layer cake on bottom of bowl.
Spread strawberries on top of cake.
Spread Cool Whip on top of strawberries.
Repeat layers of cake, strawberries and Cool Whip until it reaches the top.

title: dad's chili
directions: Brown and drain meat. Add onions, tomato sauce and chili powder. Season with salt and pepper to taste. Cook over medium-low heat for 3 to 4 hours for best flavor. Makes enough for 100 hot dogs.

title: lasagna casserole
directions: Saute hamburger and garlic; drain.
Add tomato sauce, tomatoes, salt and oregano; simmer for 20 minutes, then remove bay leaves.
Cook noodles.
Alternate layers of noodles, Mozzarella cheese, cottage cheese, meat sauce and Parmesan cheese, ending with meat sauce and Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: pina colada dip
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients then fold in whipped topping. Refrigerate. Serve with fruit.

title: pumpkin butter
directions: Mix all ingredients in large pot. Cook over low heat for 1 hour or until thick, stirring often. Remove from heat; put in sterilized jars and process to seal.

title: cheesy b~b~q chicken triscuits
directions: Toss chicken strips with barbecue sauce.
Spoon evenly onto crackers.
Top each with one cheese slice.
Place six topped crackers on microwavable plate.
Microwave on High 15 to 20 seconds or until cheese begins to melt.
Repeat with remaining topped crackers.
Sprinkle with green onions.
Best served hot, right out of the microwave.

title: jell-o pie
directions: Make pie shell and cool.
Mix Jello as directed on package. Stir in fruit cocktail. Put in refrigerator and let set.
Line cooled pie shell with sliced bananas.
Spoon Jello mixture over bananas.
Top with Cool Whip.
Refrigerate until ready to eat.

title: christmas wreaths
directions: Melt margarine with marshmallows and add vanilla and food coloring.
Pour over corn flakes and mix.
Drop by teaspoon onto wax paper.
Put red hots or cherry halves in middle to form wreaths.
Chill 40 minutes.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: chicken-apple saute
directions: Sprinkle chicken with salt and pepper.
Brown well in hot oil in skillet.
Add onion and celery; saute until vegetables are tender.
Add wine and marjoram.
Cover; simmer for 25 minutes. Stir in apples.
Cover; simmer for 10 minutes or until apples and chicken are tender.
Makes 4 servings.

title: veg-all chicken pot pie
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Spoon into pie crust.
Crimp edges to seal.
Slit top crust.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: diabetic super chocolate chip cookies(this is a diabetic recipe)
directions: Preheat oven to 425°. Spray 2 cookie sheets with nonstick cooking spray. In large mixing bowl, combine Butter Buds, oil and sugar. Beat in eggs and vanilla. Mix dry ingredients. Add to creamed mixture. Stir in chocolate chips and cereal. Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto prepared cookie sheets. Bake 8 to 10 minutes. Remove cookies immediately to cooling racks.

title: broccoli-cauliflower floret toss
directions: Cook broccoli and cauliflower covered in a small amount of boiling water for 3 minutes.
Drain well.
Place in shallow 1-quart dish.
Add cherry tomatoes and onion; set aside.

title: chili
directions: Fry hamburger, onion, chili powder, salt and pepper until done.
Add all ingredients.
Simmer for a few minutes.
Can be served with cornbread or a salad.

title: sun-dried tomatoes and potatoes
directions: Simmer the dried tomatoes and potatoes in just enough water to cover. During the last 3 minutes of cooking time on the potatoes, add the broccoli florets. Dress tomato-potato combo with parsley, oil, salt and pepper.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Cook broccoli; drain well and set aside.
Prepare Rice-A-Roni according to package directions.
Saute celery and onion in butter.
Add to rice along with soups, ham and broccoli.
Place in buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mints
directions: Work the cream cheese and powdered sugar together with hands until creamy.
Add 1/2 teaspoon peppermint extract.
You may use spearmint, vanilla, almond or coconut, if you desire.
The more you work the dough the creamier the mixture.
Add food coloring and pinch off in 1/2 teaspoon amounts, roll in granulated sugar and press into plastic mold.
Also may use fork to press down into patties.

title: appetizer fondue pizza(snack for a party)
directions: Heat sauce ingredients in fondue pot.
Dip bread chunks into sauce.

title: snack crackers
directions: Mix all ingredients with oil.
Pour over crackers.
Stir well. Put in glass jar with lid.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onions, drain and mash. Add cheese, eggs, butter and crushed crackers. Mix well and put in a greased casserole dish. Sprinkle crushed crackers on top. Bake at 350 degrees for approximately 30 minutes or until firm in center.

title: banana tea bread
directions: Cream butter; add sugar and eggs one at a time.
Add dry ingredients gradually, then bananas and nuts.
Bake 1 hour in greased loaf pan at 350°.

title: butter pecan ice cream
directions: Roast pecans in salt and butter at 250° for 15 minutes, then break into desired sizes. Whip eggs until smooth, then mix with condensed milk and pudding. Add all other ingredients and mix well. Add whole milk to fill ice cream container.

title: hawaiian lemonade
directions: Dilute lemonade with 3/4 cup of water; stir in apricot nectar and unsweetened pineapple juice.
Pour fruit juice mixture over ice cubes in 6 glasses with ginger ale; garnish with lemon slices. This recipe will serve 6 people.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Mix sugar, oil, vinegar, salt, pepper and water in medium size saucepan and boil until sugar is dissolved.
Set aside to cool. Drain all canned vegetables and put in large bowl.
Wash and chop all vegetables.
Mix with other vegetables.
Pour vinegar mixture over all vegetables and mix well.
Refrigerate for 24 hours before serving.
Keeps in refrigerator for 4 to 5 weeks.

title: yummy potatoes
directions: Put wet chunks of potatoes and dressing in a Ziploc bag. Shake well to mix.
To shorten time, put potatoes and butter chunks in microwave for 10 minutes on High.
Put potatoes on a cookie sheet; put in oven under broiler, turning as needed, until golden brown.
Enjoy.
Serves 4.

title: baked beans
directions: Combine all ingredients except bacon.
Place in baking pan. Top with strips of bacon.
Bake 1 to 2 hours.

title: cream cole slaw(my favorite)
directions: Shred cabbage.
Mix sugar with vinegar in cup.
Stir until sugar is dissolved, then add coffee cream and stir.
Mixture will thicken.
Add salt to cabbage, then add cream mixture.
This dressing may be used on other salads.
If not enough, just mix another batch as before.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place apples in greased, shallow baking dish.
Sprinkle with lemon juice.
Combine dry ingredients; add melted butter.
Mix until crumbly.
Sprinkle crumb mixture on top of apples.
Bake in moderate oven at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: punch
directions: Freeze; three hours before serving, thaw.
Put in bowl.
Pour 3 large Mello Yellows over with ice.
Serve.

title: microwave broccoli-cheese casserole
directions: Place broccoli in 1-quart casserole.
Cover and microwave on High power for 6 to 8 minutes, stirring halfway through cooking. Drain. Stir cheese into hot broccoli.
Cover casserole.
Allow to stand until cheese melts. In small bowl, melt butter in microwave on High power for 30 seconds. Stir in salt and crackers.
Sprinkle cracker mixture over broccoli.
Cover casserole.
Microwave on High power for 3 to 5 minutes or until bubbly and heated through.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into 9-inch crust.
Bake at 350° about 50 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Allow to cool.

title: spicy oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine cake mix, eggs, oil and oats in large bowl.
Beat at low speed with an electric mixer until blended.
Stir in raisins. Drop by teaspoon onto baking sheet.
Bake 7 to 9 minutes or until lightly brown.
They will crack.
Cool 1 minute before removing from baking sheet.
Can also use drained pineapple.

title: fresh peach pie
directions: Wash peaches; peel and slice.
Pour a little milk over the slices to prevent fruit from darkening.
Then add sugar, flour, lemon juice, spices and butter.
Bake in shell with lattice top in 400° oven one hour.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Combine sliced cucumbers, water and salt in a large bowl.
Heat vinegar and Sugar Twin to boiling, stir in dill weed.
Set aside to cool.
Drain cucumbers, but do not rinse.
Add liquid and mix well. Pack into freezer containers.
Thawed pickles can be stored for up to 3 weeks.
Makes about 5 cups.
About 10 calories for 1/4-cup serving.

title: giant gingersnaps
directions: In medium bowl combine flour, baking soda, salt and cloves; set aside.
In large bowl, using electric mixer, cream butter, 1 cup sugar and egg until fluffy, scraping the sides of the bowl occasionally.
Beat in corn syrup at low speed.
Add flour mixture and ginger until just combined.
Refrigerate dough until easy to handle.
Heat oven to 350°.
Grease two large cookie sheets and set aside.
Take small pieces of dough, roll into a ball, then in cinnamon-sugar mixture (cinnamon plus 1/4 cup sugar).
Place about 2 to 3 inches apart on cookie sheets.
Bake 15 to 18 minutes, until lightly browned.
Cool on wire racks.

title: root soup from medieval days
directions: Grate vegetables finely (can use food processor).
Melt 2 ounces butter in frying pan.
Saute vegetables in the butter; don't let brown.
Add broth, salt and pepper to taste.
Add sugar; simmer in pot until mixture cooks down, about 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Puree in food processor or food mill.
Continue to simmer until mixture is thick enough to cover a spoon.
During the last 5 minutes, add 1 stick of butter and a handful of chopped parsley.
Serve in medieval style in a hollowed out hard roll. Save hollowed out bread from roll.
Place a tray of bread pieces on the table.
Eat with fingers, dipping pieces of bread in the soup.
Roll can be eaten also.

title: taco soup
directions: Pour soup, water and salsa in a saucepan.
Heat over medium heat.
Heat through, stirring occasionally.
Serve in bowls with tortilla chips.
Sprinkle with onions, cheese and a spoonful of sour cream.
Yields 2 servings.

title: pea salad
directions: Mix sour cream and mayonnaise together to spread on top.

title: best bread pudding
directions: Scald 3 cups of milk.
Add sugar, eggs, margarine and vanilla. Spray 7 x 11-inch Pyrex dish and put raisins on bottom.
Break slices of bread, including crust, and place over raisins.
Pour milk mixture over bread and let stand until bread soaks up milk. Sprinkle sugar and cinnamon on top.
Start in cold oven. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: green apple cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together in a large bowl.
Beat eggs; add sugar, oil and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients.
Stir until well blended.
Fold in apples and nuts.
Batter will be thick.
Place in greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan or 3 1/2-inch tube pan. Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: quick and delicious chicken and stuffing
directions: Mix Stove Top stuffing and place in center of casserole dish. Mix
the
soup with the milk and parsley flakes.
Cover bottom of dish on outer edges of stuffing with a little of the soup mixture.
Place boneless chicken breast pieces over soup mixture. Pour
the
remaining
soup mixture over entire dish. Cover with foil and bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Remove foil and bake another 10 minutes or until chicken is cooked.

title: lasagna
directions: You will need 2 (13 x 9 x 2-inch) ovenproof dishes.

title: cookie press cookies
directions: Mix together first 4 ingredients; add flour.
Fill a cookie press; press on a cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: easy stromboli
directions: Unroll dough. Place on greased cookie sheet. Press dough into a 12 x 8-inch rectangle. Spread sauce on dough to within 2-inches of long side. Top with ham, cheese, green peppers and Italian seasoning. Fold long side of dough over filling. Pinch to seal. Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown. Makes 6 servings.

title: lemonade pies (2)
directions: Mix condensed cream with frozen lemonade.
Add Cool Whip and mix together.
Pour into pie shells and refrigerate for 1 hour.

title: walnut brittle
directions: Cook ingredients together in a heavy saucepan until honey is dark brown and the mixture gives a brittle test in cold water. Pour into greased pan.
Stir occasionally to make sure the nuts don't fall to the bottom of the pan.
When almost cool, cut into squares.

title: one-step pound cake
directions: In large mixing bowl, combine all ingredients, blend at low speed, beat 3 minutes, scraping bowl occasionally.
Pour batter into greased and floured 10-inch Bundt or tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until top springs back when touched lightly.
Cool 15 minutes, remove from pan, cool completely.
Drizzle with glaze.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients in a large bowl.
Add eggs and oil. Stir until moistened. Stir in vanilla, pineapple, 1 cup pecans and bananas.
Put in three 9-inch pans. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Use Cream Cheese Icing and put 1 cup pecans on top and sides.

title: sticky buns
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle nuts on bottom.
Place dough balls on top of nuts.
Melt margarine and brown sugar.
Pour over top of dough.
Sprinkle pudding on top.
Cover with a towel and let rise overnight or about 8 hours.
Bake 25 minutes at 425°.

title: orange julius
directions: Put in a blender for 30 seconds to blend.
Serve immediately. Makes 1 quart.

title: caribbean shrimp and peppers over rice pilaf
directions: Peel shrimp; remove tails if desired.
Blend jerk rub with 2 tsp. oil in a medium bowl; add shrimp, toss to coat and set aside. Meanwhile, prepare rice.
Cut onion into wedges.
Mince garlic. Heat oil in a 2 quart pot over medium-high heat.
Saute onion and garlic 2 to 3 minutes.
Pour in chicken broth; stir in pineapple and jerk seasoning. Bring to a boil, then stir in rice.
Cover pot; reduce heat to low and simmer 15 minutes or until liquid is absorbed.
Set aside.
While rice cooks, seed peppers and remove stems; cut peppers into thin wedges.
Heat a large, non-stick skillet over medium-high heat.
Saute shrimp and peppers 2 to 4 minutes, until shrimp turn opaque, white, and form the letter "C". Serve shrimp and peppers over pilaf.

title: chinese meat balls(appetizer)
directions: Mix all the ingredients together.
Make into 1-inch balls. Bake at 275° for 1 hour.
Makes approximately 50 to 75 meat balls.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients according to directions on package. Add remaining ingredients.
Put in casserole for 30 minutes at 350°.
Top with either cheese, bread crumbs, bacon bits, potato chips or a combination of any.
This is one recipe that will surprise everyone.
It is even good served the next day cold.

title: pepsi-cola cake
directions: Combine flour and sugar in a small bowl.
Heat butter, cocoa and Pepsi to a boil.
Pour over flour mixture; beat well.
Add buttermilk, eggs, baking soda, vanilla and marshmallows.
Beat well and pour in 15 x 10 x 1 1/2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° until done.
Ice while hot.

title: caramel cake
directions: Beat eggs; add oil and sour cream. Dump in cake mix and beat. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: sofkey
directions: Pout 1 pint corn and 1/2 cup water into a hollow or semi-hollow log and start pounding the corn with the pestle hand made from oak. When all the corn has been cracked and the skins are off, take it out; repeat the process with the second pint of corn.
After this is done, take the ground corn and sift it through a large sifter and pound it again; then, sift it through a smaller sifter.
In sifting through the smaller sifter, you get a fine ground meal, about a cup or less, which is ready for cooking.
You must use a big cast-iron pot or washpot.
Pour the water in it and build a fire underneath the pot.
When the water begins to boil, put the corn into the pot.
Remove all the residue which will rise to the top, then pour the ash liquid into this mixture and stir every 20 minutes with a long wooden sofkey ladle for about 3 hours.
Pour the fine ground meal into the pot when it is nearly done in order to thicken the juice.

title: soft molasses cookies
directions: Sift flour once.
Add salt and spices, then sift together. Beat eggs; add sugar.
Blend well, then add molasses and shortening.
Dissolve baking soda in coffee and add to other ingredients.
Combine with flour mixture, mixing thoroughly. Chill at least 1 hour.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Makes 48 medium cookies.

title: churn cucumber pickles
directions: To each gallon of water, put 1 pint of salt.
Wash cucumbers and place in a churn.
Cover with salty water and leave 14 days. Remove, rinse and cut lengthwise.
Cover with water and add alum. Leave overnight.
Drain and rinse; put in vinegar overnight.
Drain vinegar and put in a churn in layers:
1 layer cucumbers, 1 layer sugar, then sprinkle of cucumber spices.
Do this until all cucumbers are layered.
Cover and use as you want.
They are spicy hot, but not too hot.
They will keep for about 1 year.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix well and chill 24 hours.
Good on fresh vegetables and chips.

title: lime salad
directions: Melt the marshmallows in the 2 cups of water over low heat. When melted, pour over the lime gelatin.
Place in refrigerator until partially set, then add the grated cheese, drained pineapple, chopped nuts and whipping cream.

title: broccoli and cheese soup
directions: Saute onion and oil.
Add 6 cups water and bouillon until boils.
Then add noodles slowly, so it doesn't stop boiling.
Cook 4 minutes.
Add broccoli; cook 4 minutes.
Then add milk and cheese.
Cook until melts, stirring occasionally.
Add salt and pepper.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Beat lemonade into milk.
Fold Cool Whip into mixture.
Pour into pie crust and freeze.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients well and heat to boiling or until sugar is thoroughly dissolved.
Highly recommended for use in barbecuing brisket, also excellent for use in barbecuing beef or pork roast, ribs and chicken.
For a more tangy sauce, use only 3 1/2 tablespoons of brown sugar.
Makes enough sauce for cooking for 15 people.

title: parton's shepard's pie(yield: 6 servings)
directions: 1. Preheat oven to 350°.

title: 24 hour refrigerator pickles
directions: Boil last four ingredients and cool.
Pack cucumbers, dill and garlic to taste.
Place in jar or bowl.
Pour brine over cucumbers. Put in refrigerator.

title: french toast
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Dip bread and put on hot griddle.
Serve with honey or syrup.

title: monkey bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/4 cup water and 1 teaspoon sugar; set aside.
Beat egg.
Add 1/2 cup sugar, vegetable oil and salt.
Add yeast and 1 cup warm water.
Add flour until stiff dough (4 to 5 cups).
Pour onto floured board.
Knead until firm, 5 minutes. (This adds about 1 cup flour.) Turn into a greased bowl. Refrigerate overnight, covered with clear plastic wrap.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Mix pretzels, margarine and 2 tablespoons sugar.
Press into approximately 15 x 9-inch glass baking container.
Bake 7 minutes at 400°.
Cool.

title: pork chops baked in tomato soup
directions: Roll pork chops in flour.
Brown in hot fat.
Place the chops in baking dish.
Mix soup, water, onion, celery, pepper and salt. Heat.
Remove from heat and pour over chops.
Cover the dish and bake at 350° for about 1 hour.
Remove the cover for the last 15 minutes.
Cover the top with crushed cornflakes if desired.

title: chicken rice salad
directions: Cook regular or quick brown rice.
I always use the regular white rice.
Cool and add bite size cooked chicken.
Chop celery and nuts and add.
Add mayonnaise and orange segments.
Add salt as you like.

title: spinach lasagna
directions: Combine cottage cheese, 1 cup mozzarella cheese, egg, spinach, salt and oregano in a large mixing bowl; stir well. Spread 1/2 cup spaghetti sauce in a greased 9 X 13 inch baking dish.
Place 1/3 of the lasagne noodles over sauce and spread with half of the cheese mixture.
Repeat layers.
Top with remaining noodles, spaghetti sauce and 1/2 cup mozzarella cheese.
Pour water around edges.
Cover securely with aluminum foil and bake at 350 degrees for 1
1/4 hours.
Let stand 15 minutes before serving.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Peel and quarter apples.
Cook, letting them come to a boil. Then separate biscuits into halves and roll each half flat.
Put 1/5 fruit on a half and top with another half.
Seal overlap by mashing top and bottom edges together.
Repeat for other dumplings.
Mix 1 cup of the water used for cooking the apples with the sugar and 3/4 stick margarine.
Put dumplings in pan and pour mixture over them.
Melt the remaining 1/4 stick butter and pour over all.
Bake at 400° until brown.

title: dolly beans
directions: Put all ingredients in crock-pot and cook on low all day.

title: irresistible peanut butter cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Combine peanut butter, Crisco, brown sugar, milk and vanilla in large bowl.
Beat at medium speed of electric mixer until well blended.
Add egg and beat until blended.
Combine flour, salt and soda.
Add to creamed mixture at low speed.
Drop by heaping spoonfuls 2-inches apart onto ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 7 to 8 minutes or until just beginning to brown.
Cool 2 minutes.
Yields 3 dozen.

title: baked shrimp fettuccine
directions: Saute onions and garlic in butter for 15 minutes.
Add flour; cover and simmer for 15 minutes, stirring frequently.
Add shrimp; stir well.
Cover and cook for 15 minutes, stirring often.
Add cheese, half and half, lemon pepper, salt and pepper.
Cover and cook 15 to 20 minutes.
Cook fettuccine noodles according to package directions.
Drain noodles and blend gently with sauce. Pour into buttered casserole dish.
Cover and bake in preheated 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cover with Parmesan cheese.

title: no bake cheesecake
directions: Beat cheese until smooth; gradually beat in sugar.
Blend in sour cream and vanilla.
Fold in whipped topping, blending well. Spoon into crust.
Chill until set, at least 4 hours.
Garnish with strawberries or cherries, if desired.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Sift together.
Add to mix and stir by hand well, 1 (Number 303) can fruit cocktail and 2 eggs.
Pour into a 13 x 9-inch pan. Sprinkle on top 1/2 cup brown sugar and 1/2 cup pecans.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: pork roast hawaiian style
directions: Rub roast with brown sugar, salt and pepper.
Mix catsup, tomatoes and water with a dash of hot sauce and dash of Worcestershire sauce.
Pour mixture over roast and bake at 350° until tender.
Serve sauce over rice or noodles.

title: swedish sill salad
directions: In
large
bowl
combine potatoes, beef, pickles, diced beets and herring (with sauce).
Cover;
chill several hours. Just before
serving, add mayonnaise.
Toss until ingredients are moistened.
Garnish
with diced egg white, sieved egg yolk and sliced beets.
Makes 25 servings.

title: luscious peach pie
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine cream cheese, powdered sugar and extract. Beat until smooth. Gently fold in La Creme and peaches.
Pour into graham crust.
Chill until firm, about 3 hours.
Serves 6.

title: doughnuts
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add milk, then add flour that has been sifted with salt, baking powder and spices.
Chill dough thoroughly in refrigerator.

title: wacky cake
directions: Add all together and sift.

title: cheesy vegetable soup
directions: In medium saucepan, cook onion in hot oleo until tender but not brown.
Add corn, broccoli, carrot and water and bring to boiling. Reduce heat, cover and simmer 10 minutes or until veggies are tender.
Stir in soup, milk, cheese and pepper.
Cook and stir over medium heat until cheese is melted and mixture is heated through.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle crumbs over butter. Add all other ingredients in layers.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until lightly browned on top.
Cool in pan 15 minutes.
Cut into bars.
Enjoy!

title: peanut butter, oatmeal, bit cookies
directions: Mix melted oleo, sugar, brown sugar, peanut butter, eggs and vanilla.
Sift flour, soda and salt into creamed mixture.
Blend in oats and chocolate bits.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: mayonnaise cake (chocolate)
directions: Measure all dry ingredients into sifter.
Sift into large mixing bowl.
Add water, vanilla and mayonnaise and mix well. Pour into greased and floured pans.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes. Top with gloss.

title: easy chicken
directions: Coat skillet with cooking oil.
Place over medium heat until hot.
Add chicken and brown on both sides.
Add water.
Cover and simmer for 15 minutes.
Yields 4 servings. Preparation time is 25 minutes.

title: chili rellenos
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Stuff chilies with cheese slices.
Place in pan.
Add flour to milk; beat until lump free.
Add eggs and salt; beat, then add taco sauce.
Mix well.
Pour over chilies.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: baked beans
directions: Combine all ingredients in saucepan.
Bring to a boil. Transfer to a 10 x 13-inch dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: floating island or boiled custard
directions: Heat milk to warm, but not hot.
Combine eggs, egg yolks, sugar and salt.
Slowly strain into warm milk.
Cook over hot, not boiling, water, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and coats a heavy spoon.
Remove pan immediately from hot water and place in pan of cool water.
When cool, add vanilla.
Chill. (Custard may curdle if water boils.) Float ice cream, whipped cream or broken pieces of angel food cake on top of custard.

title: cherry cake
directions: Bake cake mix according to directions. Cool slightly. Spread pie filling over top. Serve with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: old fashioned sugar cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375 degrees.
Coat baking sheets with nonstick spray.
In a large bowl, beat butter, margarine, confectioners and granulated sugar with mixer on low speed until blended.
Increase to high until fluffy and light.
Beat in egg, vanilla, baking powder and salt.
On low, blend in flour.
Roll dough into 1 inch balls.
Roll balls in coarse sugar.
Place about 2 inches apart on baking sheet.
Flatten balls with the bottom of a glass or bottle into 2 inch rounds.
Bake 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool on baking sheets for 10 seconds or so before removing cookies to wire racks to cool completely.

title: veggie pizza
directions: Unroll the crescent rolls and spread out onto a cookie sheet. Bake 7 to 8 minutes at temperature listed on the package. Allow to cool.

title: apricot slush
directions: Put in freezer until slushy.
To serve, spoon in a nice glass or goblet.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Mix ingredients in a large bowl.
Bake at 350° in 9-inch pans for 20 minutes (3 layers).

title: scalloped corn
directions: Mix together and bake in casserole pan at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: twinkie cake
directions: Slice Twinkies in half.
Place in the bottom of an oblong serving dish with the filling side up.
Prepare pudding according to the package directions.
Pour on top of the Twinkies.
Layer bananas, strawberries, Cool Whip and chopped pecans on top of the pudding.

title: scripture cake(found in old testament)
directions: Mix thoroughly.
Bake in tube pan at 275° for 3 to 4 hours.

title: shrimpalicious hot dip
directions: Saute onions in butter. Take cream and add flour to it and blend well. Pour into onions and butter mixture. Add all other ingredients and stir. Serve hot with bread or crackers.

title: favorite icebox cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs and mix well.
Sift soda and salt with flour.
Add nuts and mix with first part.
