Roll into three round rolls and wrap with wax paper and freeze overnight. Slice thin and bake at 350° until light brown.
(This will keep in freezer if securely wrapped.)

title: cherry pudding
directions: Mix all together and bake at 350°.

title: bourbon marinade for steak or salmon
directions: Mix all ingredients in a glass or plastic container. Add steak or salmon and let soak at least 2 hours or overnight. Guaranteed to be tender and delicious.

title: hamburger noodle casserole
directions: Bring to boil and remove from heat.
Place half the mixture in a 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Add 8 ounces uncooked noodles and top with remaining meat mixture.
Bake at 375° f or 45 minutes. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Serves 6.

title: spiced cocoa
directions: Combine in small container.
Use 2 heaping teaspoonfuls per cup.
Fill cup with 1/2 boiling water and 1/2 whole milk.

title: white cookies
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Cream shortening and sugar together.
Add egg and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients alternately with sour milk.
Drop on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Try adding nuts or raisins (optional).

title: granny's buttermilk pound cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar together.
Add flavoring.
Add eggs one at a time.
Beat at medium speed.
Alternate buttermilk with sifted dry ingredients.
Bake in a tube pan at 350° for one hour.

title: crispy cheese crackers
directions: Mix margarine and cheese.
Add flour; mix well.
Stir in Rice Krispies and pecans.
Roll in long roll and chill.
Cut in slices and bake at 375° for 20 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Add milk and flavoring.
Add dry ingredients. Beat well.
Fold in coconut.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 300° in a large tube pan, greased well.

title: wild rice casserole
directions: Put butter and soups in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Place in 350° oven until butter melts.
Add water chestnuts, rice and seasoning packet.
Stir to mix and return to oven, uncovered, for 1 hour. Serves 6.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Place eggs in a saucepan and cover with water.
Bring to a boil and continue for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and replace with cool water for eggs to cool.
Remove shell from eggs.
Cut eggs in half (lengthwise) and remove the yolk.
Place the yolk in a bowl and mash with a fork.
Add mayonnaise, mustard, salt, pepper and pickles.
Mix well.
Spoon the mixture into a pocket of each egg half and sprinkle paprika on top.
Makes 12.

title: old-fashioned banana pudding
directions: Combine sugar, flour and salt in the double boiler.
Stir in milk.
Cook over boiling water, stirring until thickened.
Beat egg yolks and gradually stir in hot mixture.
Return to double boiler; cook 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; add vanilla.
Line 1-quart casserole with vanilla wafers.
Top with sliced bananas.
Pour portion of custard over bananas. Repeat, ending with custard on top.
Beat egg white stiff but not dry.
Gradually add 1/4 cup sugar and beat until mixture forms stiff peak.
Pile on top of pudding.
Bake in preheated 425° oven 5 minutes.
Serve warm or chilled.
Makes 6 servings.

title: almond-crusted cranberry apple bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour bottom only of 8 x 4-inch or 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
In large bowl, combine all ingredients except sliced almonds and jelly.
Stir 50 to 75 strokes by hand just until dry particles are moistened.
Pour batter into greased and floured pan.
Sprinkle with sliced almonds.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 65 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool loaf in pan on cooling rack 15 minutes; remove from pan.
Cool completely.
Cover; store in refrigerator.
Just before serving, brush with warm apple jelly.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Beat the first three ingredients until smooth.
Add the next 5 ingredients and mix well.
Pour half the batter in a greased tube pan.
Add half the nut mixture (the last 3 ingredients mixed together).
Add remaining batter.
Top with remaining nut mixture. Bake for 45 minutes at 375°.

title: braised red cabbage
directions: Melt butter or margarine in a large skillet.
Add onion. Saute for 1 minute.
Add cabbage and apple and cook for 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Combine salt, pepper, brown sugar, water and vinegar.
Add to cabbage mixture and cook, covered, over low heat for 30 minutes.
Serve hot or cold.
Makes 6 servings.

title: pinto bean pie
directions: Melt butter and add other ingredients. Blend well. Pour into an unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: potato salad
directions: Pour vinegar over flour and sugar; add 2 eggs and prepared mustard.
Cook until thickened and add pepper.
Add mayonnaise if too thick.
Pour over 2 quarts cooked, diced potatoes.

title: orange sherbet salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
While warm add sherbet and Cool Whip.
Blend well; fold in oranges.
Chill.

title: crock-pot brisket
directions: Place brisket in crock-pot.
Combine liquid smoke, catsup, vinegar, soy sauce, Worcestershire, steak sauce, Tabasco, corn syrup, garlic powder, mustard and soft drink.
Cook on high heat for 1 1/2 hours or until sauce is bubbly.
Reduce heat to low and cook for 6 1/2 hours or until done.
Serves 6.

title: almond bark
directions: Place almonds and butter in 9-inch glass pie plate.
Cook 3 to 4 minutes on High in microwave, stirring after every minute.

title: ruby red christmas punch
directions: Chill punch and 7-Up.
Thaw frozen juices, but do not dilute. Mix all ingredients together except 7-Up.
Keep chilled.
Just before serving, carefully pour 7-Up down the side of the punch bowl and stir gently.
Use ice ring made from the punch, if desired.
Makes 25 (5 ounce) servings.

title: best cornbread
directions: Beat all ingredients except bacon grease into a thin batter. Use a heavy iron skillet to heat grease (bacon), then sprinkle a little cornmeal on bottom to make a crust.
Pour batter into hot skillet and bake at 450° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: cheese ball
directions: Place chopped peppers, onions and pineapple on paper towel to absorb moisture.
Blend all ingredients together well.
Refrigerate and chill at least 1/2 hour.
Shape into ball and roll in pecans..

title: roast pork with sauerkraut
directions: Preheat the oven to 450°.
Rub the pork roast with salt and pepper.
Brown on all sides in oven 20 to 30 minutes.
Remove roast from oven.
Scatter sauerkraut around roast.
In a bowl, mix apples, onion, brown sugar, mustard and caraway seed.
Sprinkle this mixture over the sauerkraut; drizzle the beer.
Cover and roast 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until thermometer reaches 160°.
Do not let roast dry out.

title: taco seasoning mix
directions: Add ice cubes before serving.
(12 servings.)

title: buckeyes
directions: Mix margarine, peanut butter and powdered sugar together. Knead like bread.
Form into small balls and chill approximately 1 hour.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook and drain spaghetti.
Set aside.
Chop vegetables.
Add to spaghetti after it is cooled. Pour in the Salad Supreme.
Use the whole bottle.
Then add entire bottle of salad dressing. Toss well.
Let sit for a few hours.
Toss before serving.

title: mom's lettuce and bacon dressing
directions: Beat eggs, water, vinegar and sugar.
Mix well.
Heat at low temperature until thickened.
Fry bacon.
Shred lettuce in bowl. Pour warm dressing over lettuce and crumble bacon into salad. Serve warm.

title: six week bran muffins
directions: Combine all. Fill muffin tins 2/3 full. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: monkey cake
directions: You will also need a tube pan or Bundt pan (solid bottom).

title: shoo-fly pie
directions: Mix the flour, brown sugar and butter into crumbs; set aside. Mix the molasses, baking soda, boiling water and beaten egg, then mix with 1/2 the crumbs, but do not beat.
Put in pie shell. Cover with the remaining crumbs.
Bake at 375° for 11 minutes, then at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: caramel cookies
directions: Combine sugar, butter and evaporated milk.
Bring mixture to a rolling boil, stirring frequently.
Remove from heat and add pudding mix and rolled oats.
Mix together.
Cool 15 minutes. Drop by teaspoon on waxed paper or plastic wrap.

title: spinach quiche
directions: Line a 10-inch deep pan with pie shell.
Bake 15 minutes at 425°.
Remove shell and lower heat to 375°.

title: easy grilled ham
directions: Place steak in a large shallow dish or heavy-duty zip top plastic bag.
Combine ginger ale, orange juice, brown sugar, vegetable oil, white vinegar, dry mustard, ground ginger and ground cloves, stirring until sugar dissolves.
Pour over steak. Cover or seal and refrigerate 8 hours, turning meat occasionally.

title: company hamburger
directions: Brown meat in shortening in large, heavy skillet.
Add remaining ingredients; mix thoroughly.
Cover and cook 1 hour over low heat.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Peel and grate potatoes and onion.
Leave mixture in bowl until water from vegetables rises to top.
Skim off and discard.
Add eggs, flour and seasonings; mix well.
Drop by spoonfuls into hot shortening and flatten mixture until pancake is 4-inches in diameter.
Fry until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels.
Serve with applesauce or sour cream.

title: mountain dew pound cake
directions: Mix and bake in tube pan at 325° until toothpick comes out clean.

title: best cake
directions: Mix by hand the flour, 2 cups sugar, eggs, baking soda and crushed pineapple.
Pour into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: shrimp alfredo
directions: In a large skillet, cook shrimp, shallots and garlic in butter over moderate heat, stirring, 3 to 4 minutes, until shrimp is firm and pink.
Reduce heat to low.
Cook fettucine al dente and add to shrimp.

title: spoon bread
directions: Add boiling water to corn meal, along with margarine.
Stir until meal is well moistened and margarine is melted and mixture is smooth.
Add salt and sugar.
Allow to cool.
Add well beaten eggs.
Pour into hot, well-greased baking dish (1 1/2-quart). Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes or until firm.

title: preacher cookies
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients and boil about 1 minute, then add the last 3 ingredients and mix well.
Drop on wax paper.
Cool and serve.

title: potato casserole
directions: Peel potatoes.
Mix all ingredients, stirring lightly.
Place in a buttered casserole.
Bake at 325° in oven for 1 hour.

title: 3 bean chili beans(in crock-pot)
directions: Cook beef, onion and garlic in fry pan; drain, then put into crock-pot and add remaining ingredients.
Cook on high 1/2 day.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Mix and boil for 1 minute. Set aside to cool.
Mix 2 packages French vanilla instant pudding (small size) and 3 1/2 cups milk. Beat and add one 8 ounce Cool Whip.

title: fried pork chops
directions: Beat together cornmeal, flour, water and eggs to make batter. Moisten chops with water, salt and pepper then dip into batter and fry.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix vinegar, sugar and mayonnaise; pour over other ingredients.

title: fudge caramel cake
directions: Mix cake following box directions.
Preheat oven to 350°. Spray 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam or cooking spray.
Pour 2 cups of cake mix in bottom of pan.
Cook 15 minutes, then remove from oven.
Over low to medium heat, blend butter, condensed milk and caramels in medium saucepan.
Stir until melted and smooth.
Pour caramel mixture over baked layer.
Pour remaining cake mixture over caramel.
Top with nuts.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes or until middle spring back when touched.

title: cinnamon pudding cake
directions: Combine brown sugar, water and 2 Tbsp butter in saucepan and bring to a boil.
Cool.

title: glazed fruit salad
directions: Mix the first four ingredients together.
Add the last three items right before serving.

title: never fail icing
directions: Put all ingredients in double boiler and beat until stiff.

title: pineapple stuffing
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Mix in well beaten eggs. Add crushed pineapple and bread.
Bake in a casserole dish, uncovered, for 1 hour at 350°.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, cornstarch, margarine and vanilla. Gradually add milk and 2 egg yolks.
Bring to slow boil in saucepan, stirring constantly until thickened.
Pour in baked pie shell.

title: tex-mex layered dip
directions: Mix mayonnaise and sour cream.
Using a large pie plate, layer ingredients in order given.
Refrigerate about 2 hours. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: asparagus supreme
directions: In saucepan, blend butter and flour; gradually add milk and seasonings.
Cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and stir in cheese.

title: lady bird's chili con queso party dip
directions: Simmer all ingredients except cheese, slowly for 2 hours, covered, stirring often.
Then uncover and over high heat stir constantly until fluid has evaporated and thick paste remains.

title: french dressing
directions: Using a 1-quart container with a lid, add all ingredients. Secure lid and shake until well mixed.
This will keep in the refrigerator for several weeks.
Shake before using.

title: raw vegetable salad
directions: Cut up all vegetables in small pieces.
Pour 1 bottle Catalina dressing over them.
Serve chilled.

title: diabetic applesauce cookies
directions: Mix in order given.
Drop by spoonfuls on greased cookie sheet.
Bake 20 minutes (or less) at 350°.
Softer cookies will result from larger spoonfuls.

title: artichoke squares
directions: Drain artichokes; save oil from one jar.
Saute onion and garlic in the saved oil. Chop artichokes. Beat eggs. Add crumbs and spices. Add rest of ingredients and mix well.
Pour into greased 8 x 11-inch Pyrex pan. Bake at 325° for 30 minutes or until firm to touch. Cool slightly. Cut into squares and serve warm.

title: shrimp a la perea
directions: Heat oil in large, heavy skillet.
Add the peeled, deveined shrimp and saute quickly, stirring frequently, until pink.
Add green onions and garlic and cook 2 minutes.
Add artichokes, mushrooms, salt, pepper, thyme, parsley and lemon juice.
Cook, stirring, until mushrooms and shrimp are tender, about 3 minutes. Makes 6 servings.
Serve over favorite pasta, coated with butter and olive oil.

title: "who's next" brisket
directions: Marinate in heavy foil (fat side up) overnight or several hours.
Bake or grill slowly 5 or 6 hours.
Slice across the grain.

title: pumpkin squares
directions: Grease 13 x 9 x 3-inch pan on bottom only and flour.
Mix ingredients and put in bottom of pan.

title: zucchini cheese casserole
directions: Slice zucchini 1/8-inch thick; saute in butter until barely tender.
Add seasonings and place in casserole.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Pour in beaten eggs.
Top with shredded cheese; sprinkle with paprika and parsley.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes, until eggs are set.
Serves 6 to 8.
Grease a casserole dish before adding ingredients.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix all together sugar, flour, salt, baking soda, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Add remaining ingredients.
Add nuts if desired.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes about 5 to 6 loaves.

title: zucchini pancakes
directions: Mix all together; drop by teaspoonful into skillet.
Fry in butter and lard until brown and crisp.

title: light gingerbread
directions: Mix well with pastry blender the flour, sugar, shortening, cinnamon and ginger.
Save out 1/2 cup for topping.
Add to flour mixture the egg, molasses, sour milk, soda and salt.
Mix together.
Pour into greased 9 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle with topping.
Bake for 35 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: zucchini (squash) patties
directions: Mix all ingredients with enough milk to moisten and drop in patties in oil.
Fry, brown and drain.

title: freddie's pecan pie(mock)
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugars and butter and mix together.
Add oatmeal and coconut.
Put in shell and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: tops-lite lasagne
directions: Combine water, onion, celery and garlic in large skillet. Cook over medium heat until vegetables are tender and water has evaporated.
Add ground meat and saute slowly until brown.
Stir in tomatoes, tomato paste and seasonings.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, for about 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix.
Sprinkle half of this on top of cake mix.
Put rest of cake mix on top, then rest of cinnamon-sugar.
Bake according to directions on cake mix.
Can serve with Cool Whip.

title: dog biscuits
directions: If using cheese, use 1 stick oleo.
Mix all together. Add enough warm water to make a very stiff dough. Roll out and cut. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Grease a regular size cake pan.
Mix cake mix according to directions.
Sprinkle nuts and coconut on bottom of cake pan. Pour the cake mix on top.
Mix the oleo, powdered sugar and cream cheese together and pour down the middle of the cake and carefully spread it so as not to mix the cake mix.
The cream cheese does not need to cover the cake.
Bake in a 350° oven for 50 minutes. Take out and set until able to set.
The cake should crack down the middle to give the "earthquake" effect.
Does not need icing. This cake doesn't look as good as it tastes, but it doesn't last long and it is definitely a favorite in our family.

title: shrimp spread
directions: Mix all ingredients together; blend until well mixed. Refrigerate about 1 hour before serving.
Good with crackers, celery, carrots, etc.
Yields 1 1/2 cups.

title: blueberry stack cake
directions: Mix cake as directed on box.
Pour into three 9-inch round cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Remove and cool.
Mix cream cheese and sugar until creamy.
Place cake, then cream cheese mixture, then blueberries.
Alternate until you end with blueberries on top.
Let your juice roll down sides of cake on top.

title: pasta vegetable medley
directions: In a large skillet, stir-fry vegetables in margarine until crisp-tender.
Reduce heat to low.
Add cheese spread and milk; stir until cheese is melted.
Add noodles; toss lightly to coat noodles and mix vegetables.

title: guam chicken salad
directions: Sprinkle chicken thighs and breasts with salt.
Place in broiler pan or do over charcoal.
Broil for 15 minutes, until chicken is almost cooked.
Turn over and broil another 15 minutes. Chicken should not be thoroughly cooked.
Debone, chop or grind. Mix all ingredients in a bowl.
Chill at least one hour.
Serve with tortillas, crackers or corn chips.

title: aunt evie's chocolate cake
directions: Baking Temperature: 350°.
Baking Time: 26 minutes for cupcakes; 65 minutes for 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: party chicken
directions: Spray glass casserole dish with Pam.
Line glass with chipped beef slices.
Roll chicken breasts with bacon slices, tucking in edges of bacon.
Place on chipped beef.
Mix soup and sour cream. Pour over chicken breasts.
Cover and refrigerate.
Bake at 275° for 3 hours or longer uncovered.
Baste occasionally.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Mix shortening, sugar and eggs.
Blend.
Add remaining ingredients.
Roll in balls the size of walnuts .
Roll balls in a mixture of 2 tablespoons sugar and 2 teaspoons cinnamon.
Place on ungreased baking sheet about 2 inches apart.
Bake at 200° for about 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes about 5 dozen.

title: apple crumb cake
directions: In casserole dish pour apple pie filling, then take dry cake mix over the apples.
Smooth out cake mix; cut small pat of margarine over the cake mix.
Place in oven at 350° for 25 minutes or until brown.

title: bombs over moscow (shrimp fried rice)
directions: Set wok over high heat; swirl in half of fat or oil.
Add scallions and brown lightly.
Add shrimp; stir-fry 3 minutes. Salt.
Add eggs; scramble until not quite cooked.
Remove to a warm plate.

title: sugar and spice carrot cake
directions: Blend the eggs, carrots, brown sugar and oil.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: reese's peanut butter cups
directions: Mix first four ingredients and press into 13 x 9 x 2-inch greased pan.
Melt chocolate chips and Crisco together.
Pour over top of first mixture.
Refrigerate and cut into squares.

title: sweet chicken
directions: Pull skin off of chicken; put in dish to bake in oven.
Mix onion soup, preserves and dressing together; pour over chicken. Bake at 325° for 1 hour, covered.
Uncover, baste and bake for 30 minutes more.

title: biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in muffin pan.
Bake at 425° until brown.

title: maryland crab cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients, except flour.
Add enough flour to make handling easy.
Shape into patties.
Dust patties with flour.
Fry in just enough oil to brown on both sides.

title: dirty rice
directions: Brown beef, salt, pepper, garlic, onion and celery.
Add mushroom soup and 1/2 can water.
Add cooked rice.

title: red clam chowder
directions: Cook bacon in large pot.
Pour off excess grease.
Add clams. Cook and stir 1/2 hour.
Add all vegetables.
Cook 20 minutes. Add tomato paste and juice.
Cook until all vegetables are tender. Add water to make about 4 quarts.
Season with salt and pepper.

title: pecan pie cake
directions: Mix sugar and eggs until creamy.
Add margarine and vanilla and mix well.
Add flour and pecans.
Bake in 9-inch x 13-inch pan at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: creamy yogurt cups
directions: Completely dissolve jello in boiling water, combined with enough ice cubes to measure 1 cup. Add to jello and stir until slightly thickened. Remove any unmelted ice. Stir in yogurt and vanilla. Pour into 5 or 6 individual dishes. Refrigerate until set. Makes 2 1/2 cups or 5 servings.

title: white russian shakes
directions: In a blender, blend ice cream, vodka
and Kahlua until smooth, but still thick.
Pour into 2 chilled stemmed glasses.
Garnish drinks with chocolate.
Makes 2 drinks.

title: creamy chicken noodle soup
directions: Cook chicken and carrots in water for 40 minutes.
Reserve broth.
Bone and shred chicken.
Saute celery and onion in margarine until soft.
Add flour.
Cook until golden brown.
Add to broth.
Salt and pepper.
Bring to boil.
Add noodles.
Cook until tender.
Stir in chicken and half and half.
When doubling, use only 1/4 cup margarine.

title: gourmet potatoes
directions: Combine cheese and 4 tablespoons butter. Cook over low heat until cheese melts, stirring until smooth. Stir in potatoes, sour cream, onions, salt and pepper.
Place in greased 2-quart casserole. Top with remaining 2 tablespoons butter and paprika. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until heated through.
Makes 8 servings.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream butter and sugar; add spices. Stir cocoa and flour together; add alternately with soda water. Stir in apples.
Pour into a greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan or Bundt pan.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes, until tester comes out clean.

title: la rue's caramel pie
directions: Put all ingredients, except 1 cup sugar into pan to heat. Melt 1 cup sugar in an hot skillet.
Then pour sauce into melted sugar and stirring constantly, cook until thick.
Pour into baked pie shell.

title: granola
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Combine wet ingredients and add to dry. Mix well.
Bake at 225° for 2 hours, stirring a couple of times. Turn temperature to 300° to brown.
Watch carefully.

title: chicken and rice dinner
directions: *For creamier dish, use 1 1/2 cups rice.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix all ingredients except buttermilk.
Add enough buttermilk to desired consistency.
Drop in deep fat until well done.

title: fresh fruit salad dressing
directions: Combine and pour over fresh melon balls, pineapple, peaches, bananas or grapes.

title: shrimp etouffee
directions: Saute onions and celery in oleo over medium heat in a large covered skillet until glazed.
Add tomato paste and blend into the vegetables.
Add shrimp and cook until mixture starts to bubble. Blend in the flour well.
Add salt, pepper, cayenne to taste.
Add shallots and parsley.
Cover and let simmer for 15 minutes.
Serve hot over cooked white rice.

title: sliced beef and gravy
directions: Cook roast, uncovered, at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Cool, cover and refrigerate overnight.
Remove roast from pan; reserve drippings.
Cut roast into thin slices; set aside.
In a medium saucepan, bring water to a boil.
Add bouillon cubes; stir until dissolved.
In a large skillet, heat drippings.
Add flour; blend well.
Cook and stir over low heat until browned and thickened. Gradually add bouillon, stirring constantly, until thickened. Return a layer of sliced beef to roasting pan.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Place a layer of sliced onions on top of meat; season with salt and pepper.
Repeat layers until all beef and onions are used.
Pour gravy over all.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until beef is tender.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: streusel-topped sweet potato casserole(low calorie)
directions: Mash sweet potatoes.
Add 1/2 cup orange juice and next 6 ingredients.
Stir well and set aside.
Beat egg whites at high speed until soft peaks form.
Gradually add 1/4 cup brown sugar, beating until stiff peaks form.
Gently stir 1/4 cup of egg white mixture into potato mixture.
Gently fold remaining egg mixture. Spoon potatoes in an 11 x 7 x 2-inch baking dish coated with spray; set aside.

title: turkey with sausage walnut stuffing
directions: In saucepan over medium-high heat, cook sausage until browned, stirring to separate meat.
Add margarine, celery and onion and cook until tender.
Add broth to boil.
Add stuffing, apple and walnuts and mix.
Stuff turkey and bake according to directions.

title: raisin cheese slaw
directions: Combine cabbage, carrot, cheese and raisins.
Add remaining combined ingredients.
Mix together. Chill several hours. Makes 6 servings.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Crust:
Roll out sugar cookie dough big enough to fit a pizza pan.
Press into pan and sprinkle with sugar.
Bake until brown.

title: chicken pie
directions: Cook chicken until tender.
Pull meat from bones.
Shred with fingers.
Put on large baking dish that has been sprayed with Pam. Melt margarine.
Pour over chicken.
Blend flour and milk together until smooth.
Pour over chicken.
In saucepan, mix soup and broth that chicken was cooked in.
Add pepper and salt.
Heat to boiling point and pour over flour mixture.
Bake at 425° until brown about 1 hour.

title: cranberry sauce
directions: Place sugar and 1/2 cup of water in a large heavy skillet or saucepan on medium heat, and cook until caramelized and golden in color.
Reduce heat to medium, add remaining ingredients and simmer 10 minutes, until cranberries burst and sauce is thickened.
Stir occasionally.
Remove from heat; let sauce cool.
Yields 10 cups.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Prepare tortillas.
Mix chicken or turkey, olives, onion and 1/4 cup cheese; reserve.
Cook and stir garlic in oil over low heat until tender.
Stir in tomato sauce, water and chili powder; heat thoroughly.
Place 2 rounded tablespoonfuls of chicken mixture in center of each tortilla.
Roll up.
Place rolls, seam sides down in ungreased rectangular 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch baking dish.
Spoon remaining chicken mixture over rolled tortillas and pour hot tomato sauce over tortillas.
Sprinkle with 1/4 cup cheese and bake until hot, 15 to 20 minutes.

title: maple candied walnuts
directions: Mix sugar, syrup, water and salt. Cook to soft-ball stage. Add butter and flavoring. Spoon over walnut halves.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: Saute chopped onions in butter until soft.
Add hamburger, mushrooms, flour, garlic, salt, pepper and paprika; saute until hamburger loses its color, then add 1 can condensed cream of chicken soup and simmer for 10 minutes.
Stir in 1 cup sour cream. Serve on toast, topped with chopped parsley.

title: l.b.j.  barbecue sauce
directions: Melt butter and stir in remaining ingredients.

title: baked beans
directions: Saute onion in bacon grease until tender.
Remove from grease. Combine onion and bacon with remaining ingredients in a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: gerry's standard cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Then add milk and flour alternately.
Add flavoring last.
Bake at 350° until done.
Makes 4 layers.
Top with your favorite icing.
I use a cooked chocolate frosting.

title: liz's chocolate chip cookies
directions: Refrigerate dough for at least 2 hours.
Bake at 425° for 6 to 8 minutes.

title: sausage chili
directions: Brown the sausage and ground beef and drain excess fat.
Cook all the ingredients, except kidney beans, in a crock pot.
Toward the end, add the kidney beans.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix flour, white sugar, baking soda, salt, eggs, margarine and fruit cocktail.
Blend well.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: tuna-noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles in boiling salted water and drain.
Combine noodles, tuna, mayonnaise, salt and vegetables.

title: dip for vegetables or crackers
directions: Soften cream cheese in a bowl.
Add liquid smoke and caraway seed to your taste.
Blend well and serve with your choice of vegetables or crackers.

title: cake mix cookies
directions: Mix all together. Drop on cookie sheet and bake at 350° for about 10 minutes. Makes thin cookies.

title: stir crazy cake
directions: Put flour, 1 1/2 cups sugar, cocoa, soda and salt into an ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan and stir with a fork to mix, then form three wells in the mixture.
Pour oil into one well, vinegar into one and vanilla into one.
Pour coffee over all and stir with a fork until well mixed.
Do not beat with mixer.

title: nice and light dessert
directions: Add cup of boiling water to 3 ounce package of gelatin dessert mix.
Stir until dissolved.
Add 1 cup plain yogurt.
Cover and then refrigerate until firm.
Yield: 4 servings, 107 calories per serving.

title: custard pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Add sugar, salt and vanilla.
Slowly add scalded milk.
Pour in unbaked pie shell (9-inch).
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes.
325° until done.

title: kentucky pecan pie
directions: Combine brown sugar, syrup, salt, butter and beaten eggs. Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Sprinkle pecans over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cool.
Serve with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: coconut sour cream cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to directions on package.
Bake in 2 round cake pans.
Cool.
Slice each layer in half.
Combine sugar, sour cream and coconut; mix well and chill.

title: halloween cake
directions: Get cookie dough.
Roll into balls.
Put them in a pan.
Then add Reese's pieces to them.
Then bake them.

title: baked pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops
on
top
of stove in skillet.
Butter the bottom and sides
of Pyrex pan.
Slice potatoes thinly and place in layers on
bottom of pan.
Place grated cheese on top of potatoes.
Place pork
chops on top of potatoes.
Pour soup on top of pork chops.
Cover
with
foil
and
bake
for 1 1/2 hours.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Cream butter or margarine, peanut butter, powdered sugar and vanilla.
Roll in small balls.
Melt paraffin and semi-sweet chocolate together.
Use toothpick to dip each ball in chocolate; place on wax paper.

title: party vegetable sandwiches
directions: Soften cream cheese and mix with mayonnaise, lemon juice and salt.
Add vegetables and mix well.
Spread on bread of your choice.

title: pound cake
directions: Have shortening or butter at room temperature. Line a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan with paper and grease. Sift flour once before measuring. Preheat oven to 350°. Sift together flour, soda and salt. Put shortening, sugar, eggs, vanilla and lemon extract or rind in large bowl. Beat 2 1/2 minutes on high speed and add flour mixture alternately with buttermilk. Scrape bowl while beating. Beat only enough to blend well (about 2 1/2 minutes). Pour batter into prepared pan. Bake about 1 hour and 10 minutes. Turn out of pan and remove paper.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix onion with batter and drop by spoonfuls into a skillet of very hot grease.
It is delicious and a fine way to use leftover fish grease.

title: glazed fruit and nut balls
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.

In medium bowl, using wooden spoon, stir together sugar cookie dough, fruit bits, pecans and flour. Drop dough mixture by heaping tablespoonful onto cookie sheets. Roll into balls, placing 2 inches apart.
Bake 12 to 14 minutes, until edges and tops of cookies are light golden brown.
Let cookies stand 1 minute.
Transfer to wire racks; cool.

title: scrumptious carrots
directions: Saute pepper and onion in oil.
Add other ingredients.
Last add cooked carrots.
Simmer 15 or 20 minutes.
Serve very warm.

title: fry bread
directions: In 2 cup glass measuring cup, combine water, oil, sugar and yeast.
Set aside 5 minutes for yeast to dissolve.
In medium-size bowl, combine 3 cups flour and the salt.
Add yeast mixture to flour mixture and stir until soft dough forms, adding more flour, if necessary, to make dough manageable.
On lightly floured surface, knead dough 6 to 8 times.
Invert bowl over ball of dough and let rest 45 minutes.
In large skillet, heat 1-inch of oil to 375° on deep fat thermometer.
On floured surface with rolling pin, roll out dough to a 14-inch square.
Cut into 16 (3 1/2-inch) squares.
Fry dough squares until golden, about 3 minutes each side.
Drain well on paper towels.
Makes 16 fry breads.

title: italian chicken breast
directions: Mix milk and egg.
Dip chicken breast in the milk and egg. Roll in Italian bread crumbs.
Cook chicken breast in fry pan with butter or margarine until almost fully done.
Mix catsup and oregano together.
Top each chicken breast with 1 tablespoon or desired amount.
Sprinkle top with Parmesan cheese and one slice of Mozzarella cheese for final topping.
Finish cooking till cheese melts.

title: homemade rolls
directions: Let yeast soften in 1 cup water. Put 1/2 cup of water in a measuring cup. Add shortening until cup becomes full of water; this equals 1/2 cup shortening. Pour off water. In a large bowl, combine egg, salt, sugar and shortening that has been melted and cool slightly. Stir well and add dissolved yeast. Add flour until dough has taken all it will hold. Form into a ball and place in greased bowl. Cover and put in refrigerator to let rise at least 8 hours or overnight before using.

title: no-bake banana bars
directions: Grease a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
In a large bowl, combine bananas and granola.
Set aside.
In small saucepan over medium heat, combine marshmallows, peanut butter, juice, margarine and cinnamon.
Cook, stirring constantly, 3 to 5 minutes or until marshmallows are melted.
Pour marshmallow mixture over granola and mix well.
Press into prepared pan.
Refrigerate 2 hours.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a mixing bowl.
Pour into serving bowl and chill in refrigerator.
Can garnish with cherries.

title: no sugar applesauce nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Sift together first 6 ingredients; set aside. Combine eggs, applesauce and melted shortening. Add flour mixture. Stir in nuts. Pour into a greased 9 x 5-inch pan. Bake for 1 hour.

title: cornmeal cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar in mixer bowl until light and fluffy.
Blend in egg.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until light brown.
Cool on wire rack.
Yield:
3 dozen.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Mix venison, sausage, salt, pepper, seasoned salt, onion, eggs and bread crumbs.
Form into balls.
Saute in butter, flour and milk.
Combine remaining ingredients; pour over meatballs.
Simmer in crock-pot for 2 to 3 hours.

title: diabetic fruit bars
directions: Boil together fruits and water; remove from heat.
Add oleo. Mix this mixture with rest of ingredients all at once.
Bake in a greased 8 x 8-inch pan at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cut into bars.

title: french cherry pie
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff. Fold in sugar, crackers, vanilla, vinegar, baking powder and pecans. Spread in 9X13 pan. Bake 15 minutes at 350°. Let cool.

title: jessica's chicken
directions: Wrap 1 slice of bacon around each chicken breast.
Place, side by side, in greased 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with beef.
Mix soup and sour cream; pour over chicken.
Bake at 275° for 3 hours.

title: chicken soup
directions: In a large pot, combine the chicken, onions, garlic and 4 quarts cold water.
Bring to a boil, skimming and discarding foam from surface.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover and simmer for 1 hour. Add carrots, parsnips, celery, salt and pepper to the pot.
Cover and continue to simmer until vegetables are tender, about 30 minutes longer.
Remove pot from heat and take chicken from soup. When the chicken is cool enough to handle, remove meat from bones and shred it.
Return soup to a simmer.
Add shredded chicken and parsley; heat through, about 5 minutes.
Makes about 3 quarts.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Season chicken with pepper and salt as desired.
Place flour and water in plastic baking bag.
Put chicken pieces in bag and shake to cover chicken pieces with flour and water.
Place chicken singly in bag (in pan) and place seasoned vegetables around chicken.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: vegetable pizza #1
directions: Spread out dough.
Bake crescents according to package directions.
Mix softened cream cheese with mayonnaise and Ranch dressing.
Mix well.
Spread on cooled crescents.
Top with vegetables and refrigerate.

title: chocolate-chocolate chip cake
directions: Using a hand mixer, blend together all ingredients, except the chocolate chips, on low speed until moistened.
Mix on medium speed for 2 minutes.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Pour cake batter into a well greased Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes. Check for doneness.
Enjoy cake as is or frost after cooling with favorite chocolate icing.
Yields 1 cake.

title: old fashion candied yams
directions: Peel and cut yams in quarters.
Sprinkle sugar, nutmeg and butter.
Cover and simmer over medium heat until liquid thickens. Top with marshmallows and allow to melt.
Serve hot.

title: fruit custard pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour together.
Add butter and mix, then add eggs and milk.
Place peaches or raspberries in unbaked pie crust. Add custard mixture. Bake like a custard pie.

title: christmas butter cookies
directions: Use large spoon to mix sugar, egg, vanilla and almond extracts. Mix well.
Blend in flour.
Cover bowl and chill for 3 hours. Divide dough in half and roll each half to 3/16-inch thickness. Cut with cookie cutters and place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 7 to 8 minutes.
Decorate if you wish.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs
until
fluffy; add all other ingredients and blend. Turn mixture into pastry shells.
Bake at 300° to 325° for 45 minutes or until slightly brown and firm.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Melt butter in a deep dish.
In another bowl, mix sugar, flour and baking powder.
Pour mixture over melted butter.
Do not stir! Pour fruit and juice over this.
Do not stir.
Sprinkle an additional 1 cup of sugar on mixture.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Bake pie
shell at 450° for five minutes.
Cook butter, coconut, pecans
and brown sugar in pan until butter and sugar melt.
Cool for about 5
minutes.
Place mixture in pie shell. Return to oven for five minutes.
Cook pudding with 2 1/2 cups milk and broken chocolate bar until pudding starts to thicken. Pour immediately into pie shell.
Cool for at least four hours before serving.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all together except 1 cup of the nuts.
Form into a ball and cover with the cup of nuts.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Cook rice as directed.
Cook broccoli as directed on package. Mix rice and broccoli together.
Saute onion and celery in oleo until tender; add to broccoli and rice mixture.
Add cheese, chili powder, pepper and soup, mixing thoroughly.
Bake in a casserole dish for 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: onion potatoes
directions: Slice potatoes thin like au gratin potatoes.
Add milk, butter, garlic powder, salt and pepper.
Microwave for approximately 20 minutes, then add your onions and Parmesan cheese.
Microwave approximately 10 more minutes or until your potatoes are soft.

title: fluffy oven eggs and bacon
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Cut bacon slices into thirds.
Cook bacon in skillet until almost crisp.
Add onion.
Cook until bacon is crisp.
Drain, then spread bacon and onion in bottom of casserole dish.

title: pepper jelly
directions: Chop pepper; add small amount of vinegar to mix.
The pour rest over this and mix with sugar and pinch of salt.
Put on heat and boil 5 minutes; set aside and cool 10 minutes.
Add Certo and pour into jars.
Seal.

title: creamy cauliflower soup
directions: Simmer cauliflower in water to cover until done, about 15 minutes.
Drain reserved liquid.
Dissolve bouillon in reserved liquid.
Melt butter in a 4-quart pan.
Stir in onion and cook until soft.
Add flour gradually.
Stir in bouillon, cream, salt and Worcestershire sauce.
Add cauliflower.
Bring to a boil. Remove from heat.
Stir in cheese until it melts.
Serve hot, sprinkled with chives.
Serves 6.

title: macaroons
directions: Mix, then make small balls on greased cookie sheets.
Let stand 20 minutes, then bake 30 minutes at 325°.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine milk, sugar and salt.
Boil until mixture forms soft ball in cold water.
Remove from heat.
Beat in peanut butter, margarine and vanilla.
When mixture begins to thicken, spread on waxed paper.
Cut into squares.

title: herb bubble bread
directions: In a bowl, combine butter, parsley, garlic powder and garlic salt. Cut dough into 1-inch pieces. Dip into butter mixture. Layer in a greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan. Cover and let rise until doubled, about 1 hour. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: seafood casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Chop onion very fine; spread bread with butter and cut into cubes.
Put seafood in bottom of casserole dish; add drained peas, soup and onion.
Put bread cubes on top. Bake 30 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: turtle cake
directions: Melt caramels with 1/3 cup evaporated milk; set aside.
Beat together dry cake mix, 3/4 cup evaporated milk and 3/4 cup margarine.
Bake half the cake batter in greased 9 x 13-inch pan in 350° oven for 15 minutes.
Spread caramel mixture on top of cake.
Add pecans and chocolate chips.
Spread remaining batter and continue baking for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: coconut cookies
directions: Mix into balls; place on greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: pistachio nut cake
directions: Mix with electric beater for 2 minutes.

title: chocolate bourbon balls
directions: Mix chocolate chips and honey in 1 1/2-quart casserole or bowl. Microwave uncovered on High 1 to 2 minutes or until chips are melted; stir.
Stir in vanilla wafers, walnuts and whiskey.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Roll balls in sugar.
Store in tightly covered container up to 10 days.
Flavor will continue to develop as they stand.
Makes about 1 1/2 dozen candies; 100 calories per candy.

title: cherry squares
directions: Mix in a bowl, flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Using a knife, cut in the butter.
Add beaten egg.
Mixture must be crumbly.
Put 1/2 into 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Put cherries on top. Sprinkle other half on top.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: orange slice cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Shape into balls. Place on greased cookie sheet and press with fork.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: party punch
directions: Mix together orange juice, lemonade and water.
Add sherbet and stir until dissolved.
This may be refrigerated, if not serving immediately.
Prior to serving, add ice cream and stir until dissolved.
Makes 5 quarts.

title: garlic dip in french bread
directions: Saute butter, green onions and garlic until onions wilt.
Set aside.
In a bowl, cut cream cheese into chunks; add onion, garlic, sour cream and cheese.
Mix well; fold in artichoke hearts.

title: water chestnut bites
directions: Roll chestnuts in brown sugar.
Wrap each chestnut with slice of bacon.
Secure with toothpick.
Broil until bacon is tender. Serve warm and enjoy!!!!

title: betty's squash dressing
directions: Saute onion in margarine.
Mix squash, corn bread, soup, salt, pepper and sage.
Pour this mixture into baking dish.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: hawaiian delight
directions: Crush graham crackers to make a crust in large casserole dish. Slice bananas over crust.
Mix lemon juice and milk together and pour over bananas.
Spread pineapple over lemon juice mixture. Top with coconut and nuts. Add cherries, if you like.

title: stir-fried chicken with linguini
directions: Skin and debone chicken. Slice diagonally.
In a bowl, mix chicken, soy sauce and cornstarch. Set aside. Prepare linguini. Drain and set aside.
In skillet, with salad oil over high heat, cook mushrooms, snow peas, onion and red pepper, stirring quickly, until crispy (3 to 5 minutes).
With slotted spoon, remove vegetables to a bowl.
In drippings, cook chicken mixture until tender (3 to 5 minutes). Return vegetables to skillet. Add water and bouillon.
Heat to boiling, stirring to loosen bits from bottom of pan. Add linguini and gently toss.

title: carrot cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In bowl, mix together all dry ingredients well.
Mix together all liquid ingredients in separate bowl.
Fold dry ingredients into the wet ones and mix well.
Do not overmix.
Pour into a 9 x 5 x 3-inch nonstick loaf pan.
Bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: spicy peanut chicken(6 servings)
directions: Combine all ingredients, except chicken, in top of double boiler over simmering water; stir until smooth.
Cook until very thick, stirring frequently, about 20 minutes.
Cool at room temperature.
Discard ginger.
Place chicken in a large baking dish.
Brush sauce generously (both sides).
Cover and let stand 30 minutes.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Spoon remaining sauce over chicken.
Bake approximately 20 minutes.

title: vinegar cookies
directions: Mix butter or margarine and sugar until creamy. Mix in dry ingredients. Add vinegar. Chill one hour. Make into small balls. Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 350°. Cool before removing from cookie sheet.

title: mousseline sauce
directions: Cream half the butter and beat in egg yolks 1 at a time; add cream, salt and cayenne.
Cook in double boiler until thickened, stirring constantly; add lemon juice and remove from heat.
Add remaining butter, cut into bits.
Serve with asparagus, broccoli or cauliflower.
Also good over eggs benedict.

title: yogurt cake(from france)
directions: Mix all ingredients in one container with an electric mixer. Put in greased round 8-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Test with knife to make sure it is done.
Cool.
Remove from the pan while it is still warm.
Cut in half horizontally. Mix one container of sugar and one of fresh cream.
Spread on the cake as icing.

title: shoo-fly cake
directions: Mix molasses, boiling water and baking soda; set aside.
Mix flour, oil and brown sugar until crumbly.
Save 1 1/2 cups crumbs for top.
Add liquid to crumbs a little at a time; mix well. Grease and flour a 13 x 9-inch pan or two 8-inch pans.
Pour batter into pan and top with remaining crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or when cake tester comes out clean.

title: squash casserole
directions: Melt margarine.
Add squash, onion, soup and sour cream, along with stuffing.
Leave some stuffing to put on top.
Bake at 325°. Just before it gets done, put the remaining stuffing on top.

title: lentil stew
directions: Bring water, lentils, salt, thyme and marjoram to a boil. Cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Saute onions and carrots in olive oil slowly, until soft.
Add to stock, along with chopped parsley, tomatoes and sherry.
Cover and simmer until lentils are tender. When ready to serve, put grated Swiss or Jack cheese in the bottom of each bowl and fill with hot stew.

title: 1-2-3 chocolate sauce
directions: In top of double boiler over hot water, melt chips, stirring occasionally (or melt in microwave).
Remove from heat.
Stir in Eagle Brand milk; blend well.
May be served warm or cool.
Good on ice cream or cake.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: sugar-free raisin cake
directions: Cook raisins in the water until water is gone.
Add applesauce, Sweet 'N Low, eggs and oil.
Mix well.
Stir in flour and other ingredients.
Bake in greased and floured pan at 350° for 45 minutes.
I used a 10 x 7-inch pan.

title: pecan kisses
directions: Beat egg white stiff.
Add sugar.
Dip pecans and place on tinfoil lined cookie sheet and bake in oven at 250° for 30 minutes.

title: blueberry cake
directions: Put berries in a 10 1/2 x 7 x 1-inch cake pan. Cover with pineapple.
Pour on dry cake mix.
Scatter nuts on top.
Drizzle melted butter over all.
Place in preheated moderate oven at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool.
Cut into squares.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix together all ingredients, except crackers.
Place in casserole dish.
Crumble cheese crackers and cover top completely with crackers.
Bake for 30 minutes at 325°.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix syrup, sugar, butter, flour, salt, eggs, vanilla and add nuts.
Beat well and pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.

title: summer fruit pies(makes 2 pies)
directions: Cook first 4 ingredients until thick (about 5 minutes).
Add orange jello (dry), bananas, and chopped pecans.
Pour into baked pie crusts.
Top with Cool Whip and chill.

title: praline yams
directions: Place drained yams in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
In small bowl, combine remaining ingredients; blend well.
Sprinkle over yams. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until bubbly.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix all together. Store in tightly sealed container. Place 1/4 cup of hot chocolate mix in a cup; add 1 cup of hot water and stir. Makes about 50 servings.

title: cheese ball
directions: Blend cream cheese, horseradish and Parmesan.
Stir in olives. Shape in balls and roll in dried beef.
Wrap in plastic wrap and chill overnight before serving.

title: spinach bread
directions: Cut top from bread. Remove bread from bottom.
Saute sausage. Cool.
Layer sausage, spinach and top with cheese.
Wrap in foil and bake for 10 minutes at 350°.
Unwrap and slice.
Serve warm.

title: wine sauce round steak
directions: Cut meat into serving size pieces.
Sprinkle both sides with salt, pepper and flour.
Brown on both sides in hot oil.
Drain off fat, add remaining ingredients, cover and let simmer for approximately 1 1/2 hours.
If needed, add more water if liquid boils away too fast.

title: scratch chocolate icing
directions: Melt margarine; add sugar and cocoa.
Then gradually add milk for spreading consistency.

title: oven beef stew
directions: Combine all ingredients except potatoes in a 2 1/2-quart casserole or larger.
Bake in a 325° oven for 3 1/2 hours, stirring often during baking.
If stew gets too thick, stir in more tomato juice or water and cover pot again.
Mix potatoes in the last hour and cook with lid on until done.

title: oatmeal bars
directions: Mix ingredients all together.
Put in 13 x 9 pan.
Bake at 350° for 40-45 minutes.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Melt butter and saute onions until soft.
Add cream of mushroom soup.
Heat through.
Add cheese; stir until melted.
Add Worcestershire and asparagus.
Mix well; fold in bread cubes.
Put in buttered pan; put in oven at 350° until top is browning.

title: sweet and sour cabbage
directions: In a large skillet, combine drippings or oil, brown sugar, vinegar, water, salt and pepper.
Cook for 2 to 3 minutes or until hot, stirring constantly.
Add cabbage.
Cover and cook for 10 minutes over medium heat, stirring occasionally.
Add apples. Cook, uncovered, for about 10 minutes or until tender.
Servings: 6 to 8.

title: coconut sour cream cake
directions: Blend powdered sugar into softened cream cheese, then work in milk and vanilla. Sprinkle coconut over the iced cake.

title: heaven(grilled chicken)
directions: Place chicken in a large shallow dish.
Combine soy and next 4 ingredients, mixing well.
Pour over chicken and let marinate for about 30 minutes.
Remove from marinade.
Grill chicken breasts over hot coals 25 minutes or until done, turning and basting with marinade approximately every 5 minutes.
Place slice of cheese on each chicken breast and grill an additional 5 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: apple cake
directions: Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: seven-up cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter together; beat until light and creamy. Add eggs, one at a time, and beat well.
Add flour; beat well. Add lemon juice and 7-Up.
Pour batter into well-greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 to 1 1/4 hours.

title: peanut butter cups
directions: Crumble together peanut butter, graham cracker crumbs, powdered sugar and oleo.
Pat in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt chocolate chips and spread over top.
Chill.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Mix cocoa and water in saucepan.
Heat and bring to a rapid boil.
Pour over sugar and flour mixture; mix well.
Add remaining ingredients and mix.
Pour into an ungreased jelly roll pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: chili
directions: Saute onion in small amount of oil.
Combine all ingredients. Simmer 20 minutes.
Add 2 cans beans and 1 can corned beef. Simmer another 20 minutes.

title: fried ice cream
directions: Heat brown sugar and butter until melted.
Add corn flakes. Stir well.
Spread 1/2 mixture on bottom of pan.
Spread ice cream.
Top with remaining mixture.
Freeze and enjoy.

title: crab meat mousse
directions: Heat tomato soup and cream cheese until cheese is melted. Dissolve gelatin in cold water; add to mixture and cool.
Add to mixture, celery, onion, mayonnaise, pepper and crab meat or tuna and salmon.
Mix all together and pour into mold.

title: grandmother's tea cake
directions: *If using self-rising, omit soda, baking powder and salt.

title: oven baked chicken parmesan
directions: Coat chicken with coating mix as directed on package. Place in 13 x 9-inch baking pan. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until cooked thoroughly. Top each chicken breast with sauce and cheeses. Sprinkle with oregano. Bake an additional 5 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: peppers stuffed with pork
directions: Combine pork with salt, 1 tablespoon soy sauce, sherry, ginger, scallion, water and cornstarch.
Mix well.
Remove stems from peppers.
Cut hole at the tops.
Remove seeds.
Wash thoroughly; dry.
Fill peppers with pork mixture.
Heat oil in wok to 350°. Stir-fry peppers 1 minute.
Add 2 tablespoons soy sauce, stock and sugar.
Bring to boil.
Turn heat down.
Simmer 20 minutes. Thicken gravy with dissolved cornstarch.
Stir constantly.
Remove peppers to platter and pour sauce over them.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Spread in 8-inch pie plate.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Serve with crackers.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: nola's frosting
directions: Cook the milk and flour until thick; cool and chill.
Beat butter or oleo and sugar.
Mix everything together; beat well. Add vanilla.

title: old fashioned onions-apples
directions: Squeeze the lemon juice over the sliced apples; let set while preparing the onions.
Melt the butter.
Place onions in butter; sprinkle apples on top.
Sprinkle the sugar and salt and pepper to taste.
Use tight lid and steam until apples are soft.
Stir all together and fry until slightly brown.
Good with pork.

title: heavenly strawberry pie
directions: Put sliced strawberries in pie crust.
In medium saucepan, combine dry jello, dry pudding mix and water and cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until it thickens and starts to boil. Remove from heat.
Spoon hot mixture evenly over strawberries. Refrigerate at least 2 hours.
Serve with 2 tablespoons Cool Whip on top of each piece.
Makes 8 servings.

title: turtle waffle cookies
directions: Bake by teaspoonful in waffle iron.
Makes 8 cookies at a time.
Press pecans into hot cookie to resemble turtles.

title: aunt flossie's squash pickles
directions: Wash and slice squash.
Peel and slice onion thin.
Put squash in pan; add onions.
Cover with water and salt.
Let stand 2 hours.
Drain well.
Bring all ingredients to a boil, then add squash, onions and pepper.
Bring back to boil and boil 5 minutes, then pack into hot jars and seal.
Process in hot water bath 15 minutes.
Take out.
Make sure lids are tight.

title: cornbread
directions: Mix together and bake in skillet at 400° until brown.

title: brown bread
directions: Mix ingredients together until well blended.
Pour batter into greased brown bread pan.
Place brown bread pan on rack in large pan of boiling water.
Water should reach 1/4 to 1/2 way up the brown bread pan.
Cover and steam for 1 1/2 hours.
Remove from pan and cool on cake rack.

title: sweet potato pie(century old recipe)
directions: Mix ingredients well and beat until creamy and smooth.
Cook until mixture begins to thicken.
Pour into pie pans lined with pastry and bake in moderate oven (350°) until knife inserted in middle comes out clean, approximately 35 minutes.

title: chocolate-caramel-pecan cheese cake
directions: Combine caramels with milk in heavy saucepan.
Cook over low heat until melted, stirring often.
Pour over graham cracker crust.
Sprinkle pecans evenly over caramel mixture and set aside. Beat cream cheese until fluffy, gradually adding sugar; mix well. Add eggs one at a time; stir in vanilla and melted chocolate chips.
Beat until blended well.
Spoon over pecan layer.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Run knife around edge and cool and refrigerate for 8 hours.
Release from spring-form pan and arrange pecans around edge of cheese cake.

title: crab stuffed eggplant
directions: Cut eggplant in half lengthwise. Scoop out pulp, leaving a shell 1/2-inch thick. Chop eggplant in 1-inch cubes.
Heat oil in a large skillet. Saute eggplant, onion and garlic in oil until onion is soft.
Stir in parsley, cheese and crab.
Mix well. Stuff shells with mixture. Sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Place one slice of tomato on each eggplant.
Sprinkle with about 1/2 teaspoon olive oil, then sprinkle with basil and oregano evenly over the tomato slices.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
This can be a meal in itself if served with a hearty salad and crusty bread or can accompany a simple broiled chicken nicely, too. Serves 8.

title: italian dinner rolls
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine 1 1/2 cups flour, yeast, sugar, salt and seasoning; mix well.
In saucepan heat milk, water and butter until warm (120° to 130°, butter does not need to melt); add to flour mixture.
Add egg.
Blend at low speed until moistened; beat 3 minutes at medium speed.
By hand, gradually stir in 1/2 cup cheese and enough remaining flour to make a firm dough.
Knead on well-floured surface until smooth and elastic, about 3 to 5 minutes.
Place in a greased bowl, turning to grease top.
Cover; let rise in warm oven (turn oven to lowest setting for 1 minute, turn off) for 15 minutes.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Cook potatoes until done.
Mash in a blender.
Add butter, cinnamon, egg and nutmeg.
Pour into pie shell.
Cook at 350° for 30 minutes or until crust is done.
Cool; top with whipped cream and serve.

title: french pudding
directions: Mix butter, coconut, flour and sugar and bake at 300° for 35 minutes or until brown, stirring often.
After the crumbs have cooled, put 1/2 in the bottom of a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix pudding according to directions, using milk.
After partially set, pour over crumbs.
Prepare Dream Whip or Cool Whip.
Spread over the pudding mixture.
Add remaining crumbs on the top and chill.

title: chicken noel(casserole)
directions: Cook broccoli in usual manner.
Place in a buttered flat casserole.
Squeeze lemon over broccoli.
Place chicken breasts skin side up on broccoli.
Combine soup, mushroom caps, sour cream and sherry.
Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with paprika generously. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Delicious with wild rice and tossed salad.

title: mushrooms with long grain and wild rice(this is rich but delicious)
directions: Cook rice according to directions.
Make white sauce with butter, flour, milk, salt and pepper.
Drain mushrooms; save the juice.
Add mushrooms to the sauce, then add to the rice.
(If too thick, add a small amount of the juice from the mushrooms.)
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: donna's potatoes
directions: Combine melted butter, onion and soup together.
Microwave until warm and mixed thoroughly.
Add sour cream and mix.
Place French fries in casserole dish.
Pour soup mixture over fries. Top with grated cheese.
Bake 30 minutes at 400°.

title: swiss-style mocha
directions: Combine ingredients and mix well. Store in airtight container.

title: strawberry magic
directions: Grease bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle marshmallows over bottom of pan.
Combine strawberries and syrup with dry gelatin; set aside.
In large bowl, combine rest of ingredients; beat 3 minutes with mixer at medium speed.
Pour over marshmallows.
Spoon strawberry mixture over batter.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes until golden brown; cool.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients together and cut in shortening.
Add dissolved yeast to buttermilk; add to flour and mix.
Knead on floured board.
Roll and cut.
Dip in melted butter and bake 15 to 20 minutes at 425°.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Pare and thinly slice cucumbers.
Dice onion.
Sprinkle cucumbers and onion with a teaspoon of salt and let stand 10 to 15 minutes.
Pat with paper towel to take out as much moisture as possible.
Place cucumbers and onions in serving dish.
Add sugar and vinegar and mix.
Pour on enough sour cream to half cover and dust with pepper.
Chill.

title: carmen's ole dip
directions: Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Let stand a few minutes.
If you like it spicy, add more salsa.

title: moist chocolate cake
directions: Place the butter, oats and cocoa in a mixing bowl; add boiling water and stir until butter is melted.
Add brown sugar and vanilla; mix well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Combine the flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt; add to oat mixture just until combined.
Pour into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes or until a toothpick inserted near the center comes out clean.
Cool completely on a wire rack.
Frost with chocolate frosting.
Yield: 12 to 16 servings.

title: corn fritters
directions: Mix all dry ingredients.
Mix separately the beaten eggs, corn, onion and melted margarine.
Add dry ingredients slowly to corn mixture; mix well.
Drop by large spoonfuls into hot oil.
(I use an iron skillet that doesn't stick.) Add more oil as needed to skillet.

title: chocolate pixies
directions: *If using self-rising flour, omit baking powder and salt.

title: fresh peach pie
directions: Cook until clear and add 2 tablespoons dry orange jello. Cool.
Pour over 2 to 3 cups of sliced peaches in cooled baked pie shell.
Refrigerate 2 to 3 hours.
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: orange lentil soup(adapted from the vegetarian epicure by anna thomas)
directions: Saute onion and garlic in butter in soup pot until translucent.
Add grated carrots and stir for 1 minute.
Add lentils, water, chicken or vegetable cube (if used) and lemon rind.
Let soup come to a boil, then lower the heat and simmer for 40 minutes.
Add lemon juice and basil; simmer for another 20 minutes.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Start rice (if using non-instant).
Saute all but rice and soup in butter in skillet at 350°.
Heat soup and cook rice (if using instant rice).
When rice is done, mix soup into rice, pour into oblong casserole dish and arrange mixture over top evenly.
Serve immediately.

title: pickled pig's feet
directions: Split pig's feet in half.
Wash well.
Place in pot with enough water to cover. Add salt and pepper.
Cook about 1 hour. Add 1 onion and other spices.
Simmer until tender; drain.
Add 1 sliced onion and 2 cucumbers (sliced thinly) to vinegar.
Marinate pig's feet in the vinegar mixture for 6 to 12 hours.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: boneless pork chops
directions: In electric frypan, brown well on both sides.
Remove from pan and pour in cream of mushroom soup.
Add 1/2 can water-milk.
Mix and stir well with the drippings.
Put chops back in frypan with the soup mixture and simmer slow for 45 minutes, covered.
Serve with noodles or rice.
(I use 4 chops to this amount of gravy, can use more.)

title: chicken hot wings
directions: Marinate the chicken wings in soy sauce overnight or 6 to 8 hours before cooking.
Heat the oil in a deep frying pan before dropping in the wings.
As the wings become done, they seem to float to the top of the oil.
When they are done, drain well and sprinkle both sides generously with white pepper and roll in sesame seed.

title: wanda's dish
directions: Cook rice. Cook meat and put together in skillet.
Add pepper and soup; cook 10 to 15 minutes.
Is also good to use steak strips or chicken in place of hamburger meat.

title: hermits
directions: Cream shortening; add sugar, egg and molasses; mix well.
Sift dry ingredients; add alternately with milk.
Add raisins and nuts and mix well.
"Flop" from spoon on greased baking sheet; bake in moderate oven at 350° about 10 minutes.

title: beverly slimm's herbed pork tenderloin with potatoes
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Stir oil, garlic and seasonings.
Coat meat with 3 tablespoons of seasoning mixture.
Place in large roasting pan.
Toss potatoes with remaining seasoning mixture.
Arrange around meat in pan.
Roast 35 to 40 minutes or until meat thermometer registers 155° and juices run clear, stirring potatoes after 20 minutes.
Broil on top rack of oven 5 minutes to brown. Let stand 5 minutes before slicing.
Serves 8.

title: scalloped asparagus
directions: Make white sauce from first three ingredients.
Cook until thickened, about 5 minutes.
Butter 8 x 12-inch casserole.
Place a layer of cracker crumbs in bottom of casserole.
Drain asparagus and place on crumbs.
Slice eggs and place on asparagus.
Repeat the two layers.
Cover all with the white sauce.
Top with buttered cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: new bride's biscuits
directions: Mix only until flour mix has absorbed the milk.
Turn out onto baking sheet.
Pat flat to about 3/4-inch.
Do not knead!
Cut and bake in preheated oven at 450° until lightly browned, about 12 minutes.

title: nantucket cranberry pie
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients and place in bottom of greased 10-inch pie plate. Mix the remaining ingredients and pour over top of cranberries. Bake at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes until light brown on top. Serve with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Mix together.
Put chocolate chips in last.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 55 minutes.

title: chicken and tomato casserole
directions: Brown chicken in oil.
Place in a 2-quart casserole.
Saute onion and green pepper in frying pan.
Stir in remaining ingredients and pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Serve hot with cooked spaghetti.

title: ham casserole
directions: Cook noodles; drain.
Layer noodles ham, soup and cheese, one half at the time in greased baking dish.
Pour milk over this and dot with butter. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: tartar sauce
directions: Mix together and chill in a covered jar or dish before serving.

title: bread pudding
directions: Mix everything together in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: oklahoma cherry surprise
directions: Melt oleo; mix flour, sugar and pecans and press in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Let cool.
Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and Cool Whip and spread over crust.
Then top with pie filling and chill.

title: fig cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients and add oil; beat well. Add eggs, butter and milk gradually. Add figs, nuts and vanilla. Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: caramel dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and serve.
Great with apple slices.

title: strawberry angel dessert(recipe served at club meetings)
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add frozen strawberries. Allow to thicken slightly.
Tear angel food cake into medium pieces and fold into Jell-O mixture.
Allow to harden.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: elegant chicken
directions: Grease an 8 x 12-inch pan.
Cover pan with chipped beef. Flatten chicken pieces, then roll and wrap with bacon and place in pan.
Blend soup and sour cream; pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake, uncovered, at 275° for 3 hours.
To make a little thinner sauce, add a little milk.
Serve over rice.

title: shrimp provencale
directions: Melt the butter; combine it with the next 5 ingredients.
Add the shrimp, tomatoes, mushrooms, snow peas and green onions.
Cook on high, stirring, until the shrimp are pink.
Serve over rice.

title: butter nut chewies
directions: Beat eggs until foamy.
Beat in sugar, vanilla and margarine. Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to egg mixture.
Beat until blended.
Stir in nuts.
Batter will be stiff.
Spread in pan evenly (13 x 9 x 2-inch pan, greased).
Bake 25 to 30 minutes. Cool.
Cut.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: pimento cheese for sandwiches
directions: Mix cheese and pimentos together. Mash well. Add salad dressing a little at a time until ready to spread. Keep in refrigerator until ready to make sandwiches.

title: mom's layered salad
directions: In large bowl place two layers each of lettuce, pepper, celery and onions.
Top with layer of frozen peas.
Cover completely with mayonnaise or salad dressing.
Sprinkle with sugar, then add layer of cheese and top with bacon bits.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: lemon berry pie
directions: Beat cream cheese, 1 tablespoon milk and sugar in medium bowl, using wire whisk until smooth.
Stir in lemon peel and juice. Stir in 1 1/2 cups of the whipped topping.
Spread evenly in bottom of crust.
Press strawberry halves into cream cheese layer, reserving several for garnish, if desired.
Pour 2 cups milk into large bowl.
Add pudding mixes.
Beat with wire whisk 1 minute. Let stand 1 minute or until thickened.
Gently stir in 1 cup of the whipped topping.
Spoon over strawberries in crust. Refrigerate 4 hours or until set.
Garnish with remaining whipped topping and reserved strawberry halves.
Store leftover pie, covered, in refrigerator.
Makes 8 servings.

title: short-cut eggs benedict
directions: In 2-quart saucepan, combine soup, milk and lemon juice.
Over low heat, heat through, stirring occasionally.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: For broth:
Cook 4 leg quarters in approximately 4 quarts water with 3 chicken bouillon cubes.
Remove chicken when done. Add 2 or 3 drops yellow food coloring.

title: peanut butter and jelly sandwich
directions: Spread the peanut butter on the bread, then spread the jelly on the other part of the bread and you got a peanut butter and jelly sandwich to eat.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Put poppy seed in buttermilk to soak overnight.
Cream together sugar, Crisco, then add eggs and mix.
Add salt and soda to flour and sift.
Add milk and flour and mix.
Bake 1 1/2 hours in 350° oven in greased and floured Bundt pan.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Take a large open field, a half dozen children.
Add 2 or 3 puppies.
Take a generous pinch of brook and pebbles.
Mix all together and put into the field.
Sprinkle with flowers.
Spread a blue sky over all and bake in sunshine.
When brown, set away to cool in a bathtub!

title: linda's roast
directions: Place roast on a large sheet of heavy-duty foil.
Cup it around the roast.
Then season with celery salt and garlic and pour the entire bottle of liquid smoke over the meat.
Put an additional piece of foil on top and seal the 2 pieces together on all sides.

title: yorkshire fruit cake
directions: Beat the butter until soft.
Add the sugar which has been sifted.
Beat until well blended.
Beat in the 6 egg yolks.
Mix 1 3/4 cup of the flour, spices and salt and add alternately with the liquid.

title: walnut bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream butter and sugar. Add rest of ingredients and beat 2 minutes. Spread in shallow pan and bake for 25 minutes. Cool. Cut into bars and roll in powdered sugar.

title: shrimp manale
directions: Melt margarine in heavy saucepan.
Add oil and stir thoroughly.
Add all other ingredients except shrimp.
Heat thoroughly, then set aside, covered, until mealtime.
When ready to cook, bring sauce to a boil, lower heat, add shrimp and simmer 6 to 8 minutes.
Serve in shallow bowls or soup plates with a little juice with each serving.
Serves 6 to 8.
Serve with lots of French bread for "soppin" and red or white wine.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients in bowl. Add milk, oil, eggs, corn, onion and peppers. Mix well. Stir in cheese. Bake in greased pan at 425° for 25 to 30 minutes, until well browned and top of bread is dry.

title: cherry bounce
directions: Mix together.
Punch is done when cherries rise to the top. Makes 1/2 gallon.

title: strawberry sorbet
directions: Blend sugar with strawberries; pour into stainless steel bowl. Add buttermilk.
Stir well.
Put in freezer.

title: linguine salad
directions: Mix all ingredients in a 3-quart casserole.
Chill.

title: fruit punch
directions: Thaw orange juice and lemon juice.
Mix with other items, except last ingredient.
Freeze in smaller containers.
When ready to serve, pour 2 large bottles of beverage of choice over frozen mixture.

title: cranberry gelatin salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 1 cup hot water.
Add 1/2 cup cold water. Chill.
Mash cranberry sauce with fork; add to jello.
Stir in pineapple, marshmallows and pecans.
Chill until firm.

title: potatoes supreme
directions: Cook potatoes until tender; drain and refrigerate, covered, overnight.

title: mushroom turnovers(appetizer)
directions: Cream the first 3 ingredients together.
Mix egg yolk and water together.

title: chocolate chip cheesecake
directions: Break cookies into small pieces.
Mix with melted butter; pat firmly into the bottom of a 9-inch spring-form pan.

title: applesauce pancakes
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Fry in butter at medium heat. Serve warm with lots of syrup.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Light the oven.
Get out bowl, spoons and ingredients.
Grease and flour pans.
Crack nuts.
Remove 18 blocks and 7 toy cars from the kitchen table.
Measure 2 cups of flour.
Remove "Kelly's" hands from flour, wash flour off him/her.
Measure one more cup of flour to replace the flour on the floor.
Put flour, baking powder and salt in sifter.
Get the dust pan and brush up pieces of bowl, which "Kelly" knocked on floor.
Get another bowl.
Answer doorbell.
Return to kitchen and remove "Kelly's" hands from bowl. Wash "Kelly."
Get out egg.
Answer phone.
Return.
Remove cracked egg from greased pan.
Look for "Kelly!"
Get out another pan and grease and flour it.
Answer phone again!
Return to kitchen.
Wash shortening from "Kelly."
Take up greased pan and find 1/4-inch nut shells in it.
Head for "Kelly" who flees, knocking bowl off table. Wash kitchen floor!
Wash the table!
Wash the walls!
Wash the dishes!
Call the bakery!
Lie down!
Serves:

title: eddie's jam cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream butter and sugar.
Beat eggs and yolks together.
Stir into creamed mixture.
Add jam, sift soda, flour and spices.
Add alternately with buttermilk.
Add raisins. Pour in wax paper lined greased and floured cake pans.
Bake 1 hour.

title: mom's golden nuggets
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Stir in nuts, coconut and orange candy.
In another bowl, beat eggs and vanilla until foamy, gradually adding brown sugar.
Beat until thick and add to flour mixture.
Mix well and bake in a greased 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan at 350° for 40 minutes.
Cool and drizzle with glaze.

title: tomato bouillon
directions: Saute onions in butter.
Mix with remaining ingredients and simmer for 30 minutes.
Freezes well.
Makes 12 to 15 servings.

title: brown rice
directions: Brown rice and onions in butter, stirring constantly.
Combine all ingredients and pour into greased casserole dish.
Cover and bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Yield: 4 to 5 servings.

title: mom's best brownies
directions: Mix together the flour, cocoa, salt and vanilla; set aside. Beat the eggs, then add the sugar and butter.
Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Add nuts, if desired.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes in a greased 8 x 8-inch pan.

title: corn and rice casserole
directions: Saute onion and pepper in butter until tender.
Add other ingredients, except rice.
Put rice in bottom of casserole; pour other ingredients over it.
Mix well and top with grated cheese. Cook at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes, until cheese is melted and browned.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Cook in crock-pot about 7 to 8 hours on low.

title: wedding punch
directions: Mix juice and 7-Up.
Pour some into mold and add grapes to make ring.

title: good ole spaghetti
directions: Brown hamburger meat and drain off fat; return meat to pan on low heat.
Chop onion and mushrooms in medium size chunks.
Add to hamburger meat and cook approximately 20 minutes on medium heat with lid on pot.
Add 4 cans of tomato sauce and 1 package of spaghetti mix and cook 1 hour.
Cook spaghetti until done, approximately 30 minutes; drain water.
Add to sauce and serve.

title: cranberry dessert
directions: Mix together butter, sugar, water and evaporated milk.
Sift into a bowl the flour, soda and salt. Add to the first mixture. Stir in cranberries.
Pour into an 8 x 8-inch greased pan and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: skillet garden rice(microwave)
directions: In a microsafe 3 quart casserole, place the butter, onion, garlic, celery and carrot.
Cover tightly.
Microwave at High for 3 minutes, stirring once.
Stir in salt, pepper and rice.
Pour in broth.
Stir and cover.

title: red cabbage
directions: Prepare cabbage and shred.
Heat in about 1-inch salted water and vinegar.
Cover and heat to boiling until cabbage is crisp cooked, about 10 minutes; drain.

title: dilled potato salad
directions: In large bowl, combine oil, vinegar, sour cream, cheese and seasonings.
Stir until well blended.
Add vegetables and toss until well coated.
Refrigerate one hour or until chilled.
Serve as a side dish or salad.
Makes 6 servings.

title: black forest parfaits
directions: Beat cream cheese with mixer, add 1/2 c. milk at low speed till smooth.
Add pudding mix and rest of milk.
Beat till smooth, 1 to 2 minutes.
Spoon 1/2 of the pudding evenly into individual dishes, sprinkle with wafer crumbs.
Cover with pie filling reserving a few cherries for garnish, if desired.
Top with remaining pudding.
Chill till ready to serve.
Garnish with reserved cherries and additional wafer crumbs.
4 - 6 servings.

title: fresh apple pie
directions: Peel and slice apples.
Mix apples, sugar, flour and apple pie spices in large bowl.
Put into 1 pie shell.
Slice margarine and place on top of apples.
Cover with other pie shell and press sides together to keep juices from running out.
Put slits in top of shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Let stand for at least 15 minutes before serving.

title: none such cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
