Add eggs and mix.
Add flour, water with soda, mincemeat and chopped pecans.
Drop onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: amaretto slush
directions: Add boiling water, sugar and tea bags.
Make strong tea.
Add the rest of the ingredients (except 7-Up), making sure the lemonade and orange juice are dissolved.
Pour in the empty gallon container and freeze.
To use, cut gallon container and empty in a punch bowl.
Pour 2 liters of 7-Up over and serve.

title: party mix or nuts and bolts
directions: Melt margarine in saucepan.
Add garlic salt and Worcestershire sauce.
Add cereal and peanuts; mix well.
Pour onto a cookie sheet and bake at 250° for 45 minutes, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: seafood casserole(excellent)
directions: Cook and flake haddock.
Cut scallops into bite-size pieces. Put into cold water and bring to a boil.
Remove from heat immediately.
Put all ingredients into a buttered casserole and cover with bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 300° for 40 minutes.

title: kathy's spanish rice
directions: Brown rice in grease.
Add onion, bell peppers, picante sauce and water.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Uncover; add seasonings and tomato sauce.
Continue simmering until liquid is absorbed. "Ole."

title: cherry-pecan dessert
directions: Drain cherries, reserving liquid.
Add enough water to cherry liquid to equal 1 cup; set aside.
In a bowl, combine flour, cinnamon, soda and 1/4 teaspoon salt.
Combine cherries and 2 tablespoons of the dry ingredients.
Beat egg until thick and lemon colored.
Gradually add 1 cup sugar.
Beat 5 minutes.
Stir in remaining dry ingredients until combined.
Stir in 1 tablespoon melted margarine and almond extract.
Stir in cherry mixture. Transfer to greased 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Top with pecans. Bake in 325° oven for 45 to 50 minutes or until golden.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Chop celery and onion fine and cook in small amount of water until tender.
Drain water.
Cook spaghetti about 12 minutes. Wash until clear (4 or 5 times).
Drain.

title: berry slush
directions: Place about 2 cups crushed ice in a blender with 1/4 cup water.
Add berries.
Blend until slushy.
Add powdered sugar or Sweet 'N Low to desired sweetness.

title: string beans with oil
directions: Rinse fresh beans; drain.
Defrost frozen string beans.
Saute onions in hot oil.
Add string beans, garlic, salt, allspice and water.
Add tomatoes (cut in quarters) to beans the last 5 minutes of cooking time.
Cover and cook over low heat for 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Serve hot or cold.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Melt margarine in 9 x 13 Pyrex or baking pan. Then add all ingredients and mix well. Bake for 45 minutes at 375°.

title: homemade seasoned rice mix
directions: Combine all ingredients in a storage container with a tight fitting lid. Yields 3 1/2 cups.

title: cheese bars
directions: Combine cake mix with one beaten egg and margarine (melted). Place mixture in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Beat the remaining 3 eggs with box of powdered sugar and the cream cheese.
Pour on top of crust mixture.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.
Cool; cut in squares.

title: baked beans
directions: Combine ingredients and cook in crock-pot for 3 to 4 hours.

title: mushroom bread appetizers
directions: Separate rolls.
Spread and press them to cover a 13-inch pizza pan.
Toss sliced mushrooms in melted butter.
Arrange mushrooms on top of rolls and sprinkle with herbs and cheese. Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: hot tamale pie
directions: In saucepan, add and bring to boil the water, oleo and salt. Mix cornmeal, 1 cup water and chili powder.
Add to boiling mixture.
Stir until thickened.

title: taco dip
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Put in taco seasoning and 3/4 cup water. Simmer 20 minutes.
Add Ro-Tel.
Put in Velveeta cheese. Put in small crock-pot to heat and serve.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix Dream Whip as directed.
Add softened cream cheese.
Drain fruit and add.
Add red food coloring.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Mix first four ingredients.
Pour batter into a greased pan and pour peaches on top.
Bake at 450 degrees for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350 degrees and bake until golden.

title: fresh apple date nut cake
directions: Pour sugar over chopped apples and let stand. Beat egg whites until stiff. Add egg yolks to chopped apples and stir. Add cooking oil to egg whites and let stand.

title: sweet french dressing
directions: Blend in blender or with mixer.
Makes about 2 cups.

title: chocolate sauce
directions: Boil on medium heat for 5 minutes, stirring often.
Remove from heat.
Add 1 teaspoon vanilla and a dash of salt.
Beat with mixer.
Serve over ice cream and cake.

title: hansa vasht(literally:  john's sausage)
directions: Combine flour and Crisco.
Beat egg; add ice water, salt and vinegar.
Mix with flour and Crisco.
Roll out on floured surface to thickness of pie crust.
Spread liberally with apple butter. Roll up like a jelly roll.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.
Allow to cool before cutting in 2-inch lengths. Enjoy with coffee or as a child's after school snack.

title: oriental pie
directions: Soften margarine.
Blend in sugar and beaten eggs.
Stir in pecans, coconut, raisins, vinegar and vanilla.
Pour into two 9-inch unbaked pastry shells.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: beef stew 57
directions: Sprinkle meat with salt, pepper and sugar.
Brown well in shortening.
Add water and bouillon cubes.
Cover.
Simmer 1 hour or until meat is almost tender.
Add Heinz 57 sauce and remaining ingredients.
Cover.
Simmer 1 hour or until vegetables are tender.

title: holiday baked chicken or turkey
directions: Mix together all ingredients (except cheese).
Place in oblong baking dish.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 300° until heated through. Do not freeze.

title: tastee skillet dish
directions: Cook crumbled ground beef in skillet until brown.
Pour off fat.
In another pan, melt butter.
Add onion, pepper and celery. Cook until tender.
Add to meat.
Add tomatoes or sauce.
Simmer about 5 to 10 minutes.

title: chocolate mint sauce
directions: Cut chocolate in pieces.
Add water.
Stir over low heat until chocolate is melted.
While stirring, add sugar and salt.
Boil for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat; add butter and peppermint extract.
Serve hot or cold over ice cream, sponge cake, etc. Yields about 1 1/2 cups.

title: mexican pie
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Add green pepper and onion.
Cook until tender.
Add half of process cheese spread and chili powder.
Stir over low heat until process cheese spread is melted.
Stir in tomato; combine remaining process cheese spread, eggs, flour, salt and milk.
Beat until smooth.
Pour into greased 9-inch pie plate. Sprinkle with corn meal.
Spoon meat mixture over batter to within 1-inch of edge.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Bring the oleo, brown sugar, Karo and salt to a boil; boil for 5 minutes.
Put the soda into the mixture and stir hard.
Pour over popcorn; stir.
Put in a 250° oven for 30 to 45 minutes, depending on crispness desired.
Stir once in awhile during baking.

title: hot rolls(very easy)
directions: Combine sugar, oleo, salt and 1 cup water in saucepan over low heat to melt oleo. Cool to lukewarm. Dissolve yeast in 1
cup lukewarm water; add to first mixture.
Beat eggs and add to mixture. Stir in flour. Cover with wax paper and refrigerate several hours or overnight.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt; set aside.
Work shortening in a bowl.
Gradually add sugar and beat until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add flour mixture alternately with mashed bananas, a small amount at a time, beating after each addition until smooth.
Fold in chopped nuts. Turn into a well greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: microwave chicken breast
directions: Lay the chicken breasts flat in a large glass dish.
Pepper the chicken.
Cover the chicken with the soup and spread over the top evenly.
Bake for 17 minutes on High in the microwave, rotating the dish about halfway through.
Let sit for a few minutes before serving.

title: seashell-provolone casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter in a large skillet just until tender. Add ground beef, cook until browned, stirring to crumble meat. Add spaghetti sauce, tomatoes, mushrooms and garlic salt to meat mixture.
Stir well and simmer 20 minutes.
Cook macaroni according to package directions except reduce salt to 1 1/2 teaspoons, drain.

title: 22 minute cake or chocolate sheath cake
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.

title: rye bread
directions: Pour shortening, brown sugar, salt and molasses over milk and add anise seed; let cool.
Mix yeast and water and add to above. Make a well in flour and pour cooled mixture into flour and gradually mix.
Let stand 15 minutes with a wet cloth on top. Make 3 loaves in greased pans.
Let rise in pans 1 hour.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes, then at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: cheese blintzes
directions: Cut crusts from bread.
Mix sugar, cheese and egg yolk and spread mixture on bread.
Roll slices up, then dip in melted butter, then in sugar and cinnamon mixture.
Cut in bite size pieces and freeze.
When ready to use, remove from freezer and bake in 400° oven for 12 minutes.
Ready to serve.

title: hot dill pickle(yields 4 quarts)
directions: Bring first four ingredients to a boil.
In hot clean jars add remaining ingredients.
Cover with liquid and seal.
Process in hot boiling water bath for 5 minutes.
Let set four to five weeks before opening.

title: crock-pot spaghetti sauce
directions: Break up the beef in a large crock-pot, then add the remaining ingredients.
Stir to blend well, then cover and cook on the high setting for 6 to 8 hours or the low heat setting for 10 to 12 hours.
For a thicker sauce, remove the cover for the final 1 to 2 hours or cooking.
Yield: About 10 cups (10 to 12 servings).

title: "let freedom ring" meat loaf
directions: Combine
and
blend all ingredients except mashed potatoes and carrots.
Pack
into
a
greased
9-inch round mold. Bake at 350°
for
25 to 30 minutes.
Gently remove meat from mold.
Place on
platter.
Center
of
meat may be filled now with mashed potatoes surrounded by baby carrots.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: ham loaf
directions: Combine ham, beef, oats, eggs, milk, onion and catsup.
Blend well.
Shape into round loaves.
Bake in slow oven (325°) for 1 hour.
Cover bottom of pans with chicken broth before baking.

title: hot fudge pudding cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix flour, sugar, cocoa, baking powder and salt.
Stir in until mixture is smooth the milk, peanut butter, vegetable oil and vanilla.
Spoon mixture into 9 x 9 x 2-inch square pan.
Spread evenly to edges of pan.
Stir together in small bowl until well blended the brown sugar and cocoa.
Sprinkle brown sugar-cocoa mixture over batter.
Pour hot water over brown sugar mixture but do not stir.
Bake for 45 minutes.
Best when served warm.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: Use a 2-quart bowl.
Cut up lettuce and add onion and green peppers.
Put frozen peas on top of lettuce.
Cover peas with Miracle Whip.
Add Cheddar cheese on top of Miracle Whip.
Then sprinkle bacon bits on top of cheese.
Refrigerate overnight before serving.

title: moist and fruity rainbow cake
directions: Place cake layers, top sides up, in 2 clean layer pans.
Prick each cake with utility fork at 1/2-inch intervals.
Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Pour carefully over cakes.
Chill 3 to 4 hours.
Dip cake pan in warm water for 10 seconds; turn out onto serving plate.
Top with 1 cup of the whipped topping.
Unmold second cake layer and place carefully on first layer.
Frost top and sides with remaining whipped topping.
Chill.
Garnish as desired.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add egg and molasses; beat well. Add sifted dry ingredients and mix well.
Add vanilla and stir in oatmeal.
Drop from teaspoon onto greased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Yields approximately 48 cookies.

title: hawaiian fruit salad(makes 8 servings)
directions: Remove top from pineapple.
Cut pineapple lengthwise in fourths; cut peel and "eyes" from pineapple.
Remove core.
Cut pineapple into 2 x 1-inch pieces.
Cut balls from cantaloupe and honeydew.
Arrange fruit on lettuce leaves.
Serve with Banana Dressing.

title: texas caviar
directions: Combine all ingredients, cover and chill well, at least 2 hours.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: whipped butter
directions: Blanch almonds in hot water and slip off skins.
Chop fine. Cream butter and sugar.
Add remaining ingredients in order listed.
Serve on toast or to make tea sandwiches with banana bread.

title: pumpkin delight
directions: Grease pan with margarine.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: mother's ground beef special
directions: Cook macaroni.
Meanwhile, melt butter; brown meat, onions, pepper and garlic.
Place in a 3-quart casserole dish.
Stir in tomato sauce, then add remaining ingredients.
Stir well. Refrigerate overnight to mellow.
Take out 2 hours before baking. Preheat oven to 250°.
Bake, covered, for 2 hours or until bubbling.

title: corn casserole
directions: Combine corn, cheese, green chilies, onion, milk and eggs. Combine cornmeal, garlic salt, baking soda and add to corn mixture.
Place in greased baking dish and bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: banana-honey bread(makes 1 large loaf)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a 2-quart mixing bowl, sift together the flour, baking powder, soda and salt into a large bowl.
Stir in cereal and nuts.
In a small bowl, beat the egg lightly.
Beat in the honey, oil, milk and bananas.
Add banana mixture all at once to dry ingredients and stir until flour is just damp.
Spoon batter into a greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan. Bake for 1 hour or until a cake tester inserted into the center of the loaf comes out clean.
Cool the loaf in the pan on a wire rack for 10 minutes.
Remove from the pan and cool completely.
Wrap in foil or plastic.
This bread freezes well.

title: pickled peppers or okra
directions: Use pint jars.
Pack washed okra or banana peppers as tightly as possible, without bruising, into sterilized jars.
Add 1/2 teaspoon dill seed, 1 red and 1 green pepper and 2 cloves garlic in each jar.
Boil the vinegar, water and salt; pour while hot over okra or banana peppers.
Seal.
Allow to set 2 weeks.
Makes 4 pints.

title: chocolate steamed pudding
directions: Combine and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: much more than mushrooms
directions: Saute mushrooms in butter 5 minutes.
Add onion, pepper, celery and seasonings; cook 3 minutes more.
Remove from heat.
Stir in mayonnaise and set aside.
Remove crusts from bread and cut into 1-inch squares.
Place 1/2 of bread in a 1 1/2-quart casserole. Spoon mushroom mixture over bread and top with remaining bread. Combine milk and eggs and beat until frothy.
Pour over mixture in casserole.
Refrigerate covered at least 1 hour or as long as overnight.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 50 minutes.
Remove, sprinkle with cheese and return to bake 10 minutes longer.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: pineapple orange punch
directions: Mix gelatin in hot water.
Add sugar, juices and 1 1/2 quarts water.
Pour in ginger ale at serving time.
Yield: 30 to 40 servings.

title: sugared nuts
directions: Mix sugar, cinnamon, water and milk.
Cook 8 minutes, stirring often, until you can form a soft ball in cold water.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and pecans.
Pour on waxed paper and let cool.

title: chicken bake
directions: Place chicken in baking dish.
Layer cheese on top of chicken. Mix in a bowl the soups, gravy, salt and pepper.
Pour over chicken and cheese.
Spread stuffing mix over top.
Pour melted butter over stuffing mix.
To double servings, add only more chicken, Swiss cheese and 1 can chicken broth.

title: overnight rolls
directions: Start the night before.
Grease Bundt pan (spray oil is best). Sprinkle pecans on bottom of pan.
Arrange rolls over pecans. Put dry pudding mix over rolls.
Mix butter, sugar and cinnamon. Pour over rolls.
Cover with wax paper and leave on table overnight.
In the morning, bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: strawberry custard pie
directions: Blend eggs, sugar, flour, salt, vanilla and milk.
Put 1 cup cut-up strawberries in bottom of a 9 or 10-inch unbaked pie shell. Pour blended mixture over top and bake at 400° for 20 minutes. Lower heat to 350°
and bake for 25 minutes.

title: dorothy's pumpkin cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs and beat until light and fluffy.
Stif flour, salt, cinnamon, ginger and nutmeg together. Combine pumpkin and milk.
Add dry ingredients and pumpkin mixture alternately to creamed mixture.
Fold in nuts.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: linguine salad
directions: Mix linguine, Italian dressing and Salad Supreme.
Peel cucumber, slice thinly and quarter slices.
Add cucumber and tomatoes to the linguine.
Mix well together and refrigerate overnight.
Next day, mix well before serving.

title: laura osgood bean's porcupine meatballs
directions: Combine the uncooked meat and uncooked rice with salt, pepper and chopped onion.
Form into balls.
Mix the undiluted soup and water in a pressure saucepan or other covered pan.
Drop meatballs into the tomato soup.
Cook 10 minutes with pressure at cook position or 45 minutes to 1 hour in covered pan in the oven at 350°.

title: pineapple raisin cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar until light.
Add eggs and beat until fluffy. Stir together flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt. Add to creamed mixture alternately with the milk.
Mix until batter is smooth. Stir in the raisins.
Cut pineapple into 1/2-inch pieces and add to the batter.
Turn into a well buttered and floured 6-cup fancy cake or ring mold. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until done.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Heat milk and butter almost to boiling.
Add egg yolks, sugar, cocoa, flour and milk.
Cook until thick.
Remove from heat and add dash of salt and vanilla. Pour into baked pie shell.

title: polynesian meatballs
directions: Combine eggs, milk, bread crumbs, onion, pepper, salt and ground beef in mixing bowl; mix well.
Shape mixture into 48 (1-inch) meatballs.
Arrange half of meatballs in double row on round microproof plate.
Cover with waxed paper.
Cook on High for 5 minutes or until meatballs are firm.
Drain; cover to keep warm. Repeat with second plate.

title: quick cherry squares
directions: In large bowl, cream the butter and sugar.
Add the eggs; beat until light and fluffy.
Add the almond extract.
Stir in flour and baking powder; mix until smooth.
Grease a 13 x 9-inch cake pan.
Place the mixture in the pan.
Spoon pie filling on the cake in 16 spots.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Sprinkle top of cake with powdered sugar.

title: pound cake
directions: Use two bowls to mix this cake.
In one bowl, mix together the flour and butter and work until it is creamy.
In second bowl, mix eggs and sugar, beating until light and fluffy.
Then mix the two together, beating well.
Add baking powder, salt, butter flavoring, and lemon extract and vanilla extract.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour into a very large tube pan (or use 2 pans).
Bake 1 hour in 300° oven. Increase heat to 325° and bake 15 to 20 minutes longer.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Have margarine and eggs at room temperature.
Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Cream the margarine and sugar. Blend in eggs.
Stir in chili peppers, corn and cheese.
Combine remaining ingredients. Add to corn mixture, stirring until well blended.
Pour into baking dish.
Bake for 50 to 60 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cut into squares and serve warm.

title: halloween treats
directions: Mix sugar and corn syrup in 3 qt. pan.
Cook over moderate heat until mixture begins to bubble.
Remove from heat, stir in peanut butter and rice krispies.
Press into buttered 13x9 in. pan and let harden.
Mix chocolate and butterscotch chips in top of double boiler until melted, stirring to blend.
Spread over cereal mixture.
Chill and then cut into square bars.

title: cheese ball
directions: Cream together.
Chill 1 hour.
Roll in ball in chopped nuts. Serve with favorite crackers.

title: e-z apple-cinnamon cake(almost no fat)
directions: Follow directions on side of box, except in lieu of the oil, add equal amount of applesauce.
And instead of whole egg just use egg white.

title: homemade ice cream in a bag
directions: Mix.
Put in a quart zip lock bag, squeeze air out.
Seal bag with duct tape.
Place in a gallon zip lock bag.
Add 1 cup water, 1 cup coarse salt, and fill with ice cubes.
Shake for 10 minutes. May be frozen to enjoy later.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Cook sugar, margarine and 2 tablespoons milk to a taffy.
Add the 2 cups sweet milk, thickened with 3 tablespoons cornstarch, dissolved in a little of the milk and
3 beaten egg yolks and cook until thick.
Add 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Cool and pour into 10-inch cooked pie shell or 9-inch and 6-inch pie shells.
Cover with beaten egg whites and brown.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together lightly.
Pour into 2 greased and floured bread pans.
Bake for 1 hour at 325°, or until cake tester comes out clean.

title: banana split pie
directions: Mix and press in an 11 x 14-inch pan.
Bake 3 minutes at 350°. Or use already prepared graham cracker crust.

title: scandinavian almond cake
directions: This cake is usually baked in a special grooved pan which is about 4 inches across and 11 inches long; it resembles a thick tube which has been cut lengthwise.
Cream egg and sugar well; add flavoring and milk and beat well.
Mix in flour and baking powder; add melted butter.
Mix all ingredients well.
Spray pan with Pam or cooking spray.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Edges must be golden brown.
Cool in pan before removing.
Cake will break if removed too soon.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: church punch
directions: Mix well and add crushed ice.

title: ham loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: sparkling punch
directions: Chill and mix all liquids.
Pour in punch bowl. Scoop orange sherbet on top of juice. Garnish with orange slices, fresh strawberries or mint. Yields 40 servings.

title: pistachio torte
directions: Mix together flour, sugar, chopped nuts and softened oleo. Pat onto 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°. Beat cream cheese, powdered sugar and Cool Whip together and pour on crust.
Mix pudding and milk.
Spread over cheese filling.
Top with Cool Whip and sprinkle with chopped nuts.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Beat eggs, shortening, lemon extract and sugar together.
Add sifted dry ingredients and milk; mix.
Add oats, raisins and nuts. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: happy home scent(not to drink)
directions: Combine all ingredients in a tea kettle or saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; simmer as long as desired.
Additional water can be added as needed.
This can be stored in the refrigerator and reused.

title: gratin of scallops and mushrooms(lo-cal)
directions: Place scallops, wine, clam juice, mushrooms, salt, cayenne, dill, onion and lemon juice in a heavy nonreactive saucepan. Bring to boil; cover.
Reduce heat to medium-low; simmer 3 to 4 minutes.

title: apricot banana bread
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients well; add remaining ingredients. Pour into greased 9 x 5 loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes. Remove from pan.

title: blue plate meat loaf
directions: Mix together the ground beef and pork to blend the two meats. Add cracker crumbs, onion, worcestershire sauce, eggs and salt and pepper to taste.
Blend all ingredients well and add milk to moisten.
Shape into two loaves and put into two lightly greased pans.
Bake at 350° for 1-1/2 hours or until done.
Remove meat loaves and carefully cut loaves lengthwise from one end to the other.
Remove the top of each loaf, place sliced cheese on each bottom loaf and place the top back on the loaf, like a sandwich. Place meat loaves back in the pans.
Drizzle or baste each loaf with ketchup and put back in the oven for about 10 minutes just long enough to melt the cheese.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Combine crab meat, mayonnaise, cheese and onions in a double boiler.
Cook over simmering water until cheese melts, stirring constantly.
Serve hot in a chafing dish with crusty French bread cubes.
Yields 4 servings.

title: apple cobbler
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients with the apples.
Sprinkle with water.
Dot with butter.
Cover with foil.
Bake 15 minutes.
Sift the 1 cup flour, 1 tablespoon sugar, baking powder and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Cut in the shortening.
Stir in milk.
Drop by spoonfuls on hot apples.
Bake 25 to 35 minutes in a 400° oven.
When cooled, serve with whipped cream, Cool Whip or scoop of ice cream.
Makes 6 servings.

title: oreo cake(takes 3 to 4 hours)
directions: Crush cookies (food processor works great).
Reserve 1/2 cup cookies for top.
Combine cookies and melted butter; press into pan and refrigerate 1/2 hour.
Mix cream cheese and powdered sugar. Add one Cool Whip.
Spread over cookies and refrigerate for 1 hour. Prepare chocolate pudding; spread over cheese layer.
Refrigerate 1 hour.
Spread second Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with remaining cookie crumbs.
Best when refrigerated for another hour.
Yields 1 (9 x 13-inch) pan.
Serves 12 to 16.

title: barbecued tuna(lo-cal)
directions: Simmer all ingredients 15 to 20 minutes uncovered.
Use on low-cal lite bread for a lo-cal meal.

title: easy cheesecake
directions: Mix Cool Whip and cream cheese.
Pour on top of crust.
Pour fruit topping on top.
Cool until firm, 6 to 8 hours.
Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: blueberry cream cheese salad
directions: Drain blueberries and measure juice.
Should be 1 cup; if not add water to equal that amount.
Dissolve gelatin in the boiling water.
Add lemon juice.
Place bowl over ice and stir until cool. Add blueberry juice and blueberries.
Chill until set; when slightly thickened, pour into mold.

title: buckeye balls
directions: Mix peanut butter, sugar, butter and vanilla together in a bowl. (It helps to knead mix together with hands also.) Line a cookie sheet with waxed paper. Roll the cookie mixture into bite size round balls. Place on cookie sheet and refrigerate for 1 hour. Then melt the chocolate chips and shortening in a double boiler.

Using a toothpick, dip the balls into the melted chocolate, leaving the top quarter of each ball undipped. Return to cookie sheet to cool and allow chocolate to harden. Keep refrigerated until ready to serve.

title: tomato sauce
directions: Combine all
ingredients.
Bring
to
boil, then reduce heat to	simmer.
Stir
frequently until sauce thickens.
Pour into sterilized jars
and seal.	(Adjust jalapenos to taste if you like sauce very hot.)

title: cinnamon swirl cake
directions: Grease and flour Bundt pan and sprinkle 1/4 cup nuts in bottom.
Combine mix, pudding, water, eggs, oil, butter and vanilla.
Beat on high 6 to 8 minutes.
In small bowl combine remaining nuts, sugar and cinnamon.
Fill pan in this order:
1/3 cake batter, 1/2 cinnamon filling and 1/3 cake batter.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Cool in pan for 8 minutes and invert on plate.
Drizzle with glaze.

title: tuna ball
directions: Mix well, shape into a ball, and roll in parsley flakes. Chill.

title: pretzel salad(or dessert)
directions: Mix together crushed pretzels, 3 tablespoons sugar and melted butter.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 8 minutes. Cool.

title: rhea's egg flower soup
directions: Bring water to a boil.
Wash spinach, then remove stems and break into bite size pieces.
Break eggs into a bowl and stir. When water is at full boil, add bouillon and stir.
Bring broth to a hard, rolling boil.
While stirring in a constant circular motion, slowly drizzle in eggs.
Remove soup from heat; add prepared spinach and stir.
Serve immediately.

title: barbecue bacon wrapped-chestnuts(hors d'oeuvres)
directions: In a saucepan, heat the last 7 ingredients until warm.
Cut bacon into 1/2 or 1/3-inch strips (width-wise).
Partially precook bacon.
Wrap bacon around water chestnut.
Use toothpick to hold in place.
Place in a 9 x 12-inch cake pan.
Pour sauce over bacon wrapped water chestnuts.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serve hot or cold.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Heat thoroughly; simmer
at
least
minutes.
Put in jars and water bath for 5
minutes.
Makes
6 to 7 pints. (Two tablespoons mustard seed may be added if desired.)

title: vegetable rice
directions: Chop the first five vegetables into small pieces.
Heat 2 tablespoons of canola oil in pan.
Add and cook the onion and garlic for a minute.
Add rice, skimmed chicken broth, bay leaf and salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil. Cover and let simmer for 17 minutes.
Remove bay leaf and serve.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken until tender.
Take off bone and cut into bite-size pieces (don't salt).
Mix chicken, soup and sour cream together in bowl.
Pour into a casserole dish.
Top with crushed Ritz crackers, coarsely crushed.
Melt butter and pour over crackers.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.

title: pecan shortbread(scottish style cookie)
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Combine flour, sugar and cornstarch.
Cut butter into 1/4-inch cubes.
Cut butter into flour mixture using a pastry blender or two knives until it looks like coarse crumbs. Stir in pecans and vanilla.
Mixture will clump.
Pour into an 8 or 9-inch pie pan and pat with fingers to evenly cover the bottom of the pan.
Score into pie piece shapes with knife back.
Prick entire surface with fork.
Sprinkle with granulated sugar and bake 25 to 30 minutes.
Cut on lines while still hot.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: In large skillet, lightly brown chicken in olive oil.
Remove chicken.
Saute onion, mushrooms, green pepper and garlic in oil until onion is clear.
Drain any remaining oil from skillet.
Add remaining ingredients to skillet (sherry is optional) and stir thoroughly.
Add chicken to sauce.
Simmer slowly with lid for about 1 hour.
Remove lid and simmer, uncovered, to thicken. Serve over rice or spaghetti.

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix together and pour into crusts; may be frozen.
Orange juice and rind may be substituted in place of lemon, if desired.

title: apricot-nectar cake
directions: Mix all together and bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: apple rings
directions: Melt butter in pan.
Heat sugar and water.
For dough, cut shortening in flour and add milk.
Roll real thin, about 1/4-inch thick.
Pour apples over dough and sprinkle cinnamon on top.
Roll up lengthwise and seal.
Slice into 1/4-inch slices and place in melted butter.
Pour sugar water over all.
Bake t 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: fulton salad
directions: Cook sugar, eggs and vinegar until thick.
Dissolve jello in pineapple juice and water.
Combine with egg mixture.
Then cut up marshmallows and add crushed pineapple.
Cool.
Add nuts, whipped cream and cherries.
Serves about 8.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Saute ground meat until crumbles.
Add garlic powder, salt and peppers.
Mix well.
Layer tortillas, then ground meat, chopped olives, then grated cheese.
Make another layer, topping with cheese.
Bake in a 400° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: mock empanadas emilia
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine first 3 ingredients in 10-inch skillet and cook over medium-high heat until browned.
Drain off any excess fat.
Add cheese and stir until melted, about 2 minutes. Remove from heat.

title: cajun shrimp soup
directions: In a large saucepan, saute green pepper, onion and garlic in margarine until tender.
Stir in vegetable juice, clam juice, water, salt, thyme, basil, pepper flakes and bay leaf.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat; add rice.
Cover.
Simmer 15 to 20 minutes or until rice is tender.
Stir in shrimp; simmer uncovered 3 to 5 minutes or until shrimp heat.
Remove bay leaf.
Add hot pepper sauce to individual servings as desired.
Yields 4 servings.

title: dill weed dip
directions: Mix ingredients in large bowl; cover.
Refrigerate for 72 hours.
Slice top of loaf off; cut out center of bread.
Dice center of bread into small pieces.
Place loaf on plate.
Fill center of loaf with dip.
Place diced pieces of bread on plate around loaf.

title: sour cream chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 13 x 9 x 2-inch oblong pan or 2 (9-inch) or 3 (8-inch) round layer pans.
Measure all ingredients into large mixing bowl.
Mix 1/2 minute on low speed. Beat 3 minutes on high speed.
Scrape bowl.
Pour into pan(s). Bake until top springs back when touched lightly with finger. Cool.
Frost if desired or eat plain.

title: apple cream cheese dessert
directions: Unroll first package of rolls and lay in bottom of ungreased 9 x 13 dish.
Mix cream cheese, sugar and vanilla and spoon over layer of rolls.
Add pie filling on top of cream cheese mixture. Unroll second package of rolls and place on top of this.
Melt margarine and pour all over.
Sprinkle top with cinnamon and sugar.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: vanilla, butternut pound cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and salt.
Add eggs, one at a time then flour and milk alternately, ending with flour.
Fold in flavoring by hand.
Bake in greased tube pan for 1 hour 45 minutes at 325°. Start in cold oven.
Do not open door while baking.
Remove from pan immediately.

title: dilled tomato slices
directions: Combine salad dressing, water, dill weed, salt and pepper. Place cucumber slices in shallow dish and top with dressing. Chill overnight.
To serve, top tomato slices with cucumbers and dressing.
Serves 6.
Calories: 33.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Cover bottom of 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish with corn chips. Cut chicken into bite size pieces.
Layer over chips.
Combine soup, broth and tomatoes (undrained) in a separate bowl and pour over chicken.
Top with cubed Velveeta.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: stuffed green pepper salad
directions: Select 2 well shaped green peppers.
Cut stem end off.
Remove all seeds and stuff with pimiento cream spread.
Chill for 3 or 4 hours (better overnight).
Slice in 1/4 inch slices with sharp knife and place 3 slices on each of 6 individual beds of lettuce or chicory.
Make a cream cheese flower or rosette in center of salad. Add bit of pimiento to center of flower and bits of green pepper stuck in side for leaves.
Serve with mayonnaise.
Serves 6.

title: italian spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti; rinse with cold water, tossing lightly with salad oil.
Cook zucchini and beans in small amount of water until just tender but still bright in color.
Drain and add to spaghetti with onions, tomatoes, salt, olives and cheese.
Beat together vinegar, oil, water and Italian seasoning.
Blend well.
Store in sealed bowl.
Makes 8 servings.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients in a
9 x 11-inch long pan.
Lay bacon on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: tamale pie
directions: Spread layer of Fritos in bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Make layer of chicken over Fritos, layer of cheese over chicken. Cover layers with enchilada sauce.
Repeat layers and finish with cheese, chicken and sauce.
Cover with foil to prevent drying. Bake 35 to 45 minutes at 350°.
Uncover for last 10 minutes.

title: carrot cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients in large bowl.
Add eggs and oil.
Mix until blended.
Add carrots.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes. Cool and frost with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: pistachio mousse
directions: Combine and blend all ingredients.
Refrigerate for a minimum of 2 hours to set.
Serve with grated almonds/nuts on top in large bowl.
Serves 4.

title: squash dressing
directions: Mix all together.
Cook at 400° to 425° for 20 to 25 minutes or until set.
Mix crumbs and broth to amount you want or size pan cooked in.

title: baked chicken breast
directions: Salt chicken and place in casserole dish that has been sprayed with Pam. Place a slice of Swiss cheese over each piece of chicken. Pour undiluted soup over each one. Bake at 350° for 1 hour, covered. Melt butter and add to stuffing mix. Spread over chicken and return to oven, uncovered, for 15 more minutes.

title: green bean casserole 3
directions: Saute onion in margarine until lightly browned.
Add flour, blending in well. Add sour cream and heat slowly, stirring until mixture thickens slightly. Drain beans and add to sauce. Stir in salt and pepper.
Turn mixture into baking dish. Sprinkle top with cheese and paprika.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown ground meat.
Drain.
Add tomatoes and tomato paste and simmer for 30 minutes.
While waiting, beat 2 eggs.
Add to cottage cheese.
Add oregano and salt; set aside.
Cook noodles until tender.
Place half of noodles in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Add meat mixture over noodles, then cottage cheese mixture, then Mozzarella cheese; repeat.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let set about 15 minutes before serving.

title: pecan pie
directions: Combine dry ingredients in large mixing bowl.
Add eggs, syrup, vanilla and margarine; beat with electric mixer until blended.
Either put pecans in mixture or place on bottom of pie shell.
Pour in mixture.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Yield: One 9-inch pie.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Put cubed bread in dish. Brown sausage; drain.
Put sausage over bread.
Sprinkle cheese over sausage.
Mix together eggs, milk, mustard and salt.
Pour over top of other.
Cover and put in refrigerator overnight.
Bake next morning at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: king ranch casserole
directions: Cook chicken in small amount of water, lightly salted, until tender. Bone and cut into small pieces.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown the ground beef, sausage, onion, bell pepper, salt and pepper in a large pan such as a Dutch oven.
Add rest of ingredients, except cheese; mix well.
Add cheese and simmer until cheese is melted.
This makes a large amount and it freezes well. Just thaw and reheat.

title: cranberry grape yogurt shake
directions: In a blender container, process grape cranberry drink and yogurt or ice cream on high until blended.

title: chicken roll-ups
directions: Saute bell pepper, onion and mushrooms in butter.
Add chicken.
Roll 1 tablespoon mixture in crescent rolls.
Bake according to directions for crescent rolls.
Heat cream of mushroom soup.
(Do not add water or milk.)
Pour over rolls when done.
Top with grated cheese.

title: chicken and fruit salad
directions: Place chicken meat in a chilled bowl and add rest of ingredients.
Stir as little as possible and serve at once.

title: baked calico beans
directions: Saute hamburger and onion.
Add bacon and mix with rest of ingredients.
Put in 2-quart casserole and bake in a 350° oven for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Take juice of pineapple, mix with sugar, egg, butter and flour.
Boil together until thick.
Let cool.
Pour over pineapple, marshmallows and nuts and toss.
This can be made the day before.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into baking dish.
Cover casserole top with cheese cracker crumbs.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: gelatin fruit salad
directions: In bowl, combine 1 cup water and lemon jello.
Add 1 cup ice cubes, stirring until melted.
Add pineapple.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch pan; refrigerate until set.
Repeat with orange jello, water and ice.
Stir in marshmallows into orange jello.
Pour over lemon layer; refrigerate until set.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix together and put in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with 1 (16 ounce) box of Pepperidge Farm stuffing mix.
Cook at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Mix when half done.

title: fruit cake cookies
directions: Cream together butter, sugar and eggs.
Sift flour, baking soda and cinnamon.
Add to the first mixture and mix well.
Add the rest of ingredients.
Drop on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: cajun chicken and pasta
directions: Cook rotelle 12 to 15 minutes.
In deep 12-inch skillet over medium-high heat, heat 2 tablespoons oil.
Add chicken pieces, stirring frequently until browned on all sides and cooked through. Remove chicken and keep warm.
Heat remaining 2 tablespoons oil in skillet; stir in flour.
Cook 5 minutes until flour is brown, but do not burn.
Stir in can of tomatoes and liquid, red and green peppers, onion, salt, red pepper and black pepper.
Cook until vegetables are tender and mixture thickens.
Drain rotelle and add to mixture along with chicken.
Warm and serve.
Serves at least 4.

title: best glaze for ham
directions: Baste ham and brown.

title: tasty potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes and eggs; let cool.
Cut in small pieces.
Mix well in large bowl.
Add cut pickles, onions, salt and seasoning salt.

title: chocolate icing
directions: Mix Crisco (melted), cocoa and salt. Add in milk, vanilla and sugar. Beat until creamy.

title: cheese-pineapple casserole
directions: Drain pineapple.
Reserve 3 tablespoons juice.
Mix flour, sugar and cheese.
Gradually add juice and pineapple.
Pour into greased 1-quart dish.
Mix crackers and butter.
Cover mixture with cracker mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: bubbling party punch
directions: Combine chilled juice and nectar in a large punch bowl.
Add soda and sherbet just before serving.
Makes 25 to 30 servings.

title: sour cream potatoes
directions: Boil the potatoes and let cool, then grate.
Grate the cheese into the potatoes.
Add margarine, sour cream, onion, salt and pepper.
Combine these ingredients and bake at 425°
for about 20 minutes.

title: play dough
directions: Mix flour, salt and cream of tartar in medium pot.
Add water, food coloring and oil.
Stir over medium heat 3 to 5 minutes (mixture will look globby).
It will turn into dough.
When mixture forms a ball in the center of the pot, turn off stove and let cool.
Then remove from pot and place on a floured surface. Squish it and punch it around a bit.
When you're done, put it in a bag or container and store in the fridge.

title: red hot jelly
directions: Wash and sterilize canning jars and lids.
In a large, heavy saucepan, combine juice and sugar.
Stir well.
Add margarine and candies.
Stirring constantly, bring to a rolling boil over high heat.
Stir in liquid pectin, stirring constantly.
Return to a rolling boil and boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Skim foam from top of mixture with a large metal spoon.
Fill sterilized jars to within 1/4-inch of tops.
Wipe jar rims and seal jars.
Store in refrigerator.
Yield:
2 pints jelly.

title: "chicken and rice casserole"
directions: Put rice in bottom of baking dish.
In saucepan, mix soups, lemon juice and butter.
Heat until margarine melts.
Pour 1/2 soup over rice.
Place raw chicken on top of soup.
Pour remaining soup over the chicken.
Spread grated cheese (optional) over. Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours or until chicken is done.

title: grilled london broil
directions: Place London Broil in large casserole or container with lid. Pierce meat with fork all over and pour bottle of dressing on and cover overnight.
Put more fork marks in to make sure it is completely marinated.
Place on hot grill approximately 20 minutes. Should be medium rare.
Slice thin to serve.

title: pasta soup
directions: Cut the chicken tenders into quarter size pieces. Cook for a few minutes in a bit of olive oil. Do not completely cook them. Put the chicken tenders aside. Pour the three cans of chicken broth into a large pot.

title: dirt dessert
directions: Make pudding according to directions.
Mix cream chocolate with pudding mix, using a mixer, a little at a time, until smooth. Next, mix in Cool Whip.
In a blender, process cookies (5 to 6 at a time) until crushed in a very fine mixture.
In a large bowl, put a layer of crushed cookies and smooth over until even.
Next, put a layer of creamy mixture in and make it even.
Keep alternating layers (about 30 of each).
Refrigerate.

title: lazy lasagna
directions: Mix together the eggs, cottage cheese and Parmesan cheese. Add the spaghetti sauce, water and Italian seasoning to ground beef.
In a 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish, layer 1 1/2
cups of sauce, 5 noodles, half of cottage cheese mixture, half of Mozzarella cheese, remaining half of sauce, noodles and cottage cheese.
Top with Mozzarella cheese and sprinkle Parmesan cheese. You may add olives.
Cook in oven for 1 hour at 350°.

title: ham balls
directions: Roll in 1-inch balls and place on a jelly roll pan.
Place 2 inches apart.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 7 dozen. Serve warm.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Sift together the flour, baking powder, salt and sugar. Combine sifted ingredients with milk.
Spoon over butter in pan. Pour fruit over batter.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Mix together eggs, sugar, pecans, corn syrup, butter and vanilla.
Pour filling into prepared pie shell.
Arrange pecan halves around inside edge.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 325°; bake for 45 minutes or until center is firm.
Cool to room temperature.

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together; bake at 350° until done or baked away from the sides of cake pan.

title: fried chicken
directions: Wash chicken.
Roll chicken in flour, salt and pepper mixture. Dip in water.
Roll in flour mixture a second time.
This makes chicken crispier.
Drop in deep fryer in hot oil.
Fry until chicken comes to top or until golden brown and done.

title: my grandma's corn casserole
directions: Saute onion and pepper in 2 tablespoons bacon fat.
Pour over crumbs; toss.
Spoon corn and bacon into 1-quart casserole.
Pour crumb mixture over with spoon to partially mix with corn and bacon. Bake in a 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: sweet pickles
directions: Select firm cucumbers.
Wash.
Place in gallon container.
Mix salt with water to cover pickles.
Let stand 4 days.
Remove, wash and slice to desired thickness.
Place in large container and cover with turmeric, alum and water solution.
Let stand 10 hours or overnight.
Mix sugar, vinegar and pickling spice.
Cook to boiling stage.
Pack sliced cucumbers in hot jars and cover with syrup.
Seal.
Let stand 1 week before eating.
Refrigeration one day makes pickles more crispy.

title: cranberry-grape salad
directions: Grind the cranberries and add the sugar.
Refrigerate overnight.
Mix the jello, boiling water, grapes and pecans. Combine with cranberry mixture and chill. Fold in the whipped cream (sweetened).
Chill.

title: clam dip
directions: Drain clams; reserve juice.
Combine all ingredients at room temperature; mix thoroughly.
If you want a dip, add clam juice until mix has a loose consistency, refrigerate (this thickens it) and serve.
If you want a cracker spread, use less clam juice to make a thicker consistency, refrigerate and serve.
You won't have any left.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix together and pour into pie crusts.
Keep chilled.

title: "banana split" pie
directions: Beat eggs, butter and sugar for 10 minutes.
Pour into crust. Spread over mixture the pineapple, bananas, pecans (optional) and Cool Whip.
Makes 2 pies or 1 oblong pan.
Keep cool.

title: complete meal in 15 minutes
directions: Pick up the phone and call Sugar-n-Spice to place your order. Get in your car and drive to S. Pine Street.
Go inside to pick up your meal and pay Mrs. Copses.
Bring home and enjoy.

title: strawberry angel squares
directions: Combine
flour, sugar, nuts and butter; spread into a 9 x 13-inch
baking
pan.
Bake
minutes
at 350°, stirring occasionally.
Crumble
when
cool.
Reserve
of this for topping.
Spread remainder back into the pan.
Combine unbeaten egg
whites,
sugar and lemon juice in a large bowl.
Beat for 10 minutes.
Fold in whipped cream and strawberries.
Pour over the crumbled mixture.
Add topping; freeze 6 hours before serving.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix all
ingredients together and bake in large pan for 1 hour at 300°.
Do not grease the pan.

title: caramel chocolate cake
directions: Mix cake mix as directed.
Pour 1/2 in bottom of 11 x 14-inch pan.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.
Melt caramels, butter and milk.
Pour over bottom layer.
Pour the rest of the cake over this with chocolate chips and chopped nuts.
Bake for 20 minutes. Top with whipped cream and serve.

title: zucchini frittata
directions: Heat oil over low heat.
Add zucchini, onion and parsley. Saute until soft about 5 minutes.
Remove from heat; set aside. Beat eggs in a large bowl with grated cheese and seasonings.
Add zucchini mixture and chopped Cheddar cheese; blend well.
Pour into lightly greased 9-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° until just firm in the center.
Will take about 20 to 25 minutes.
Serves 6. Best if eaten hot out of the oven.

title: bagels
directions: Sift together flour and salt.
Soften yeast in 2/3 cup of potato water.
Add to flour and salt.
Add honey, oil and 1 1/3 cups potato water.
Add lightly beaten eggs.
Beat into a dough. Knead for 10 minutes.
Let rise at room temperature unti double in bulk (1 1/2 to 2 hours).
Knead dough until smooth and elastic. Roll pieces of dough and make into bagels (doughnut shape).
Add sugar to boiling water.
Drop bagels into boiling water (a few at a time).
Bagel should sink.
When it rises, turn over and boil one minute longer.
Place on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake in 450° oven for 10 to 15minutes, or until golden brown.

title: orange-buttermilk shake
directions: Measure all ingredients into blender; mix on high speed until smooth (or beat all ingredients with rotary beater).
Makes 2 servings.

title: wild rice casserole
directions: Tear chicken into pieces.
Add cooked rice, soup, onion, mayonnaise, pimento, water chestnuts and green beans.
Top with paprika, cheese and croutons.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: easy 1-dish hamburger
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch ungreased pan.
Mix Bisquick with 1 1/2 cups milk.
Pour over mixture and spread.
Sprinkle with parsley, if desired.
Bake at 450° for 27 to 30 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: ginger carrots
directions: Bake at 350° for 20 minutes, covered.

title: english trifle(punch bowl cake)
directions: Break cake into bite-size pieces in bottom of large punch bowl.
Prepare pudding mix as directed on box.
Fold in ice cream. Pour half of mixture over cake.
Make Jell-O as directed on box, folding in strawberries.
Pour half over pudding mix.
Slice 2 bananas over this.
Repeat layering process with pudding, Jell-O and bananas.
Spread Cool Whip on top.
Garnish with whole strawberries.

title: wacky cacky cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar, cocoa and baking soda.
Make three holes in dry ingredients and pour in vinegar, vanilla and oil.
Pour water over entire mixture and mix until smooth.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: blackberry cake
directions: Cream sugar and Crisco.
Add eggs and spices.
Stir soda and buttermilk together and add.
Then add flour, berries, etc.
Mix all.
Bake about 40 to 50 minutes in 3 layer cake pans greased and floured at 350°.

title: quick and easy cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In ovensafe dish, melt butter.
Stir in sugar, milk and flour.
Mix well.
Stir in fruit.
Cook until top is golden brown.
Serve hot!!!!!

title: peanut butter cake
directions: Sift together the dry ingredients.
Add peanut butter, shortening and 2/3 cup milk.
Beat until smooth. Add remaining 1/3 cup milk and eggs.
Beat well.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: coleslaw
directions: Place all ingredients in a bowl and stir until the sugar dissolves.
Stir in cabbage.
You can add raisins if you want. Good served with fried catfish.

title: chicken squares
directions: Combine soup, egg, water and seasoning in bowl.
Saute vegetables in butter.
Stir in dressing mix and soup mix.
Put in oblong Pyrex dish and bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: simple meat loaf
directions: Hold bread under cold water faucet until wet.
Press out as much water as possible.
Crumble over meat and add egg, salt, pepper and onion.
Mix together lightly with a fork.
Place in a greased baking dish and shape.
Place 1 1/2 slices of bacon on top.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.
Mix soup and water together; pour over meat loaf after it has baked 40 minutes.
Cook 20 minutes longer.
Serve with tomato gravy on each portion.

title: breakfast before
directions: Saute sausage and drain.
Beat eggs with milk; add salt and mustard.
Layer bread on the bottom of oiled 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Spread the sausage and cheese over the bread, then pour the egg mixture over all.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
(This can be completely assembled the night before.)

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Combine baking soda, water and vanilla in a small dish and set aside.
Place sugar, water and corn syrup in a deep 3-quart heat resistance, non-metallic casserole.
Stir to blend.

title: georgene's brownies
directions: Mix all ingredients (in order listed) well.
Spread in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° about 35 to 30 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine meat, pepper, onion, garlic, eggs, bread crumbs and some sauce (1/2 can) for consistency into bowl and mix together. Transfer to baking dish (mold it into shape).
Pour rest of sauce over meat.
Cover with tinfoil.
Place in 375° oven for 1 hour. Should be brown inside.
Uncover; remove foil first few minutes but don't burn.

title: warm sweet potato chips
directions: Preheat oven to 475°.
Slice the potatoes thin in rounds and toss them well with the olive oil.
Line a cookie sheet with parchment paper and spread the rounds out in a single layer.
Bake until the chips are cooked through and beginning to crinkle at the edges, about 15 minutes.
Toss with the oregano, basil and pepper and serve at once.
Great with turkey sandwich.

title: mandarin orange chiffon cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift all dry ingredients together (cake flour, baking powder, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt).
In a large mixing bowl, combine the vegetable cooking oil and sugar.
Beat the mixture until it becomes smooth.
Add egg yolks and beat well. Add the hot water.
Stir well.
Add all the dry ingredients. Stir in the vanilla, then the sweet potatoes and nuts.
Beat well.

title: sour cream chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients; will be very stiff.
Bake until bubbly. Cover with 2 rolls of Ritz crackers (crumbled with butter).
Cook at 350° until slightly brown.

title: fried squash blooms
directions: Wash squash blooms.
Make batter with flour, pepper, salt and water.
Dip blooms in batter and fry in oil in hot frying pan. Brown on both sides.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all together, adding some of the chicken broth to keep from being too dry.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: colby's chicken and dumplins'(this is so easy.)
directions: Boil chicken breasts until done (about 20 to 25 minutes).
Keep chicken broth.
Cut chicken into small pieces.
Add cream of chicken soup to chicken broth.
Stir until smooth.
Pinch biscuits into small pieces and add to mixture.
Salt and pepper to taste. Let cook for 20 to 25 minutes on medium or until biscuits are hard and fluffy.

title: sausage-egg casserole
directions: Brown and crumble sausage; drain on paper towels.
Mix eggs, milk, mustard and salt.
Stir in bread, sausage and cheese.
Pour into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Cover with foil; refrigerate overnight.
Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour.

title: rum plum duck
directions: Wash ducks inside and out; dry.
Salt insides of ducks.
Peel oranges and divide into sections.
Cut apples into wedges. Combine apples, oranges and bread crumbs and stuff ducks.
Place ducks in roasting pan.
Mix jelly with a little cinnamon, cranberry sauce, rum and lemon juice together and pour over ducks. Place roaster in oven, uncovered, at 350° for approximately 1 hour.
Baste every 10 minutes while cooking.
Serve with cooked rice (cooked birds on top of it) and pour leftover sauce over the top; add garnish for final touch.

title: banana pudding
directions: Heat milk with margarine.
Mix sugar, eggs, vanilla, salt and flour.
Pour in milk mixture.
Stir until creamy.
Put a layer of bananas, a layer of wafers and then milk mixture alternately.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Sift flour with baking soda and salt into a large bowl.
Add sugars, egg, vanilla and butter with a wooden spoon or hand electric mixer at medium speed.
Beat until well combined, about 1 minute.
Stir in nuts and chocolate chips.

title: feather rolls
directions: Stir yeast into 1/4 cup warm water and let stand 5 minutes to dissolve.
Mix margarine, sugar, salt, egg, milk and dissolved yeast in large bowl and beat until smooth.
Add the flour and beat vigorously until well blended.
Cover and let rise in warm spot for 1 hour.
Stir down and fill buttered muffin tins 1/2 full.
Cover and let rise for about 30 minutes.
Preheat oven to 400°.
Bake rolls for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: rhubarb dessert
directions: Mix. Press in 9 X 13 pan (or can be bigger).
Greased pan. Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: green rice
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook rice. While rice is still hot, add the cheese. Mix well. Add the bell pepper, chilies, parsley, garlic and onion.
Fold in the milk, oil, salt and pepper. Put in lightly oiled casserole and bake for 1 hour.

title: cherry chocolate torte
directions: Mix and bake cake mix according to box directions in a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan at 350°.
Cool and split into 3 layers.

title: melvina's low-fat spaghetti sauce
directions: Saute turkey; drain.
Return to kettle and add all other ingredients.
Cover and simmer for about 45 minutes.

title: crab casserole
directions: Combine soup, crabmeat, milk, noodles and mayonnaise. Sprinkle with cheese.
Cover and bake 25 minutes at 350°.
Uncover and top with onion rings.
Cook 10 minutes longer.

title: cracker snackers
directions: Combine oil and garlic and let stand 30 minutes.
Remove and discard garlic.
Place crackers in a bowl.
Sprinkle with oil.

title: barbecue beef for 100
directions: Combine vegetable oil, liquids, sugar, vegetables and seasonings.
Heat thoroughly, but do not cook enough enough to soften vegetables.
Brown ground chuck and drain well.
Add browned meat to the sauce and stir.
Serve on hamburger buns. Serves 100 people.

title: danish puff
directions: Mix 1 stick oleo, 1 cup flour and 2 tablespoons water with fork.
Spread on bottom of cookie sheet.
Boil 1 stick oleo in 1 cup water.
Add almond flavoring.
Remove from heat and add 1 cup flour.
Beat in eggs, one at a time, until thick.
Spread over first layer.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes.
Spread with a butter frosting and nuts.

title: orangeade
directions: Stir all ingredients and serve with ice.
Makes 8 servings.

title: mary southerland's broccoli cheese soup
directions: Cook the broccoli according to package directions (but do not add salt); drain well.
Saute onion in butter in a medium saucepan, then add the cooked broccoli and the remaining ingredients.
Cook over medium heat until cheese melts, stirring often to keep from burning on the bottom of the pan.
You may double or quadruple the recipe easily.

title: dijon potato salad
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Stir in remaining ingredients. Cover; chill.
Makes 4 1/2 cups.

title: elegant seafood quiche
directions: Preheat
oven
to
Sprinkle cheese, crab flakes, onion, flour and seasonings in pie crust.
Beat together eggs and half and
half.
Pour over cheese mixture.
Bake 50 to 55 minutes or until set.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: moist cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Cream oil and sugar.
Add beaten eggs.
Beat.
Then add dry ingredients alternately with baby food.
Last, add nuts if desired.
Bake in a lightly greased tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: luscious lemon shrimp
directions: Peel shrimp, leaving tails on; devein and set aside.
Melt butter in a large skillet.
Add shrimp, crabmeat and the rest of the ingredients.
Bring to boil; reduce heat and simmer 4 to 5 minutes.
Spoon into 4 individual serving dishes.
Arrange shrimp around crabmeat.

title: 5 bean soup
directions: Combine pinto beans, black-eyed peas, white beans, lentils, split peas, salt, pepper, onion, celery seed and garlic in a 5-quart pan.
Fill the remainder of the pan with water.
Bring to a boil and boil on high for 15 minutes.
Turn heat to medium temperature and cook for 1 hour, adding water when needed.
Turn temperature to low and add rice, ground beef, bouillon and parsley.
Cook until all beans are very tender and the soup is thickened.

title: red cabbage
directions: Soak cabbage in water (to cover) with 1 tablespoon of salt mixed in for 15 to 20 minutes.
Rinse and drain well.
Put in a large pot with no more water added.
Put cloves in onion halves. Add to cabbage.
Add all other ingredients.
Let boil, then simmer, covered, for one hour.

title: fresh fruit dip
directions: Blend cream cheese and marshmallow cream thoroughly.
Serve with strawberries, pear slices or other fruits.
Makes 16 servings.
Two teaspoons contains 92 calories and 5 grams fat.

title: strawberry daiquiris
directions: Mix together and put in freezer in covered plastic bowl.

title: diabetic sugarless oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine ingredients, beating well.
Let stand 5 minutes (oats to absorb).
Drop by spoonfuls onto greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: deluxe applesauce cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Add eggs and beat well. Add flour sifted with soda, baking powder and spices alternately with applesauce. Mix well. Fold in nuts and raisins. Pour in well greased and floured tube pan. (Loaf pan may be used if desired.) Bake 50 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.

title: waffles and maple syrup
directions: Combine flour, cornmeal or oatmeal, salt, baking powder and brown sugar in bowl.
Combine in another bowl the milk, eggs and oil.
Mix and beat with a whip.
Add liquid to dry ingredients and stir until just mixed.
Add apples and chopped nuts.
Bake on a moderately hot, lightly greased waffle iron.

title: pimiento and cheese
directions: Melt Velveeta in milk.
When Velveeta cheese is melted, add pimiento, sugar, vinegar and beaten egg.
Cook 10 minutes, stirring constantly.
Cool.
Add mayonnaise.

title: coal miner's pie
directions: Preheat oven to moderate 350°.
Brown beef and onions in a Dutch oven or large kettle, breaking up meat with a wooden spoon, until meat is no longer pink.
Stir in tomato sauce, green peppers, corn, chili powder, 1 teaspoon of the salt and the pepper.
Bring to boiling; lower heat.
Cover; simmer for 15 minutes.

title: double cheese double baked potatoes
directions: Brush potatoes with vegetable oil. Bake in 425 degree oven until done. Cool slightly. Cut lengthwise from top. Scoop pulp into bowl. Mash. Add all other ingredients. Return to potato skins. Bake at 425 degrees for 20-25 minutes.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Boil chicken, then tear in small pieces.
Keep chicken broth. Mix Ro-Tel and sour cream.
In baking dish, dip tortilla in chicken broth and lay in pan; add some chicken, then sour cream mixture, then some cheese.
Repeat 2 more times.
When ready to eat, may want to put some salsa on yours.

title: coal garden
directions: Sprinkle ingredients over lump of coal placed in saucer or small dish.

title: ambrosia
directions: Add 1 cup of boiling water to Jell-O.
Chill until almost set, about 1 hour.
While waiting, drain pineapples then cream together with cream cheese.
Add Jell-O to pineapple and cream cheese.
Fold in cool whip and the drained mandarin oranges.
Put in large bowl and to with nuts.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease baking pan and set aside.
Mix dry ingredients, raisins and caraway seed in large mixing bowl.
Add egg, margarine and buttermilk and mix well. Place dough on a floured board and mold into a round loaf.
Place in greased pan and bake for 1 hour.
Serve at once or let cool and serve toasted.

title: ham and cheese quiche
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes or until knife inserted in middle comes out clean.
Can be made ahead of time and refrigerated until ready to bake and serve!

title: layer dinner
directions: Place alternate layers of carrots, potatoes and onions in a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Press ground beef on top. Dilute soup with 1/2 cup of water.
Pour slowly over meat and vegetables.
Bake, covered, in a 350° oven for 1 hour and 30 minutes.

title: funnel cakes(4 cakes)
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine eggs and milk.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to egg mixture; beat smooth with rotary beater.
Heat oil to 360°.
Hold funnel close to surface of the oil.
Cover bottom opening of funnel with finger, then pour about 1/2 cup of batter into funnel.
Remove finger and release batter into hot oil in a spiral shape.
Fry until golden, about 3 minutes. Using wide spatula and tongs, turn cake carefully.
Cook 1 minute more.
Drain on paper towels.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: cream cheese ball
directions: Allow cream cheese to soften (room temperature).
Chop green onions and ham to 1/4-inch size pieces.
Mix with cream cheese. Form mixture into a ball; roll in sunflower seeds or chopped nuts. Serve with crackers.

title: cucumber relish
directions: Let the first 3 ingredients stand for 2 hours.
Drain and squeeze.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Bring to boil.
Let sugar dissolve.
Add cucumbers and onions.
Bring to boil and seal.

title: chicken corden bleu
directions: Pound chicken breasts until thin.
Place a slice of ham and a slice of Swiss cheese on each chicken breast.
Roll up and secure with toothpicks.
Put a pat of margarine on each roll.
Bake for 1/2 hour at 350°.
Put soup over chicken during last 10 minutes of baking time.

title: date nut bread
directions: Cover dates and shortening with boiling water; cool.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake in greased loaf pan at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Sift flour, soda and salt together.
Cream shortening and two sugars together; add egg and vanilla.
Beat thoroughly.
Add sifted ingredients.
Stir in chips.
Drop by spoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° about 10 minutes. Makes 50 cookies.

title: janice's taco dip
directions: Mix first three ingredients and spread in 9 x 12-inch pan. Spread shredded lettuce, chopped tomatoes and shredded cheese over top.
Chill for several hours and serve with crackers or chips.

title: lemon sherbet
directions: Slice 2 lemons very thin; juice other 3 lemons.
Soak slices, juice and sugar overnight, adding milk just before freezing in 1 gallon ice cream freezer.

title: morning glory muffins
directions: Mix dry ingredients and then add all other ingredients in order.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Makes 12 good size muffins.

title: rancho beans
directions: In large frypan, brown ground beef and onion; drain excess fat.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Simmer, covered, for 20 to 30 minutes, or bake for 25 to 30 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: In skillet, brown chicken in shortening. Pour off fat. Add remaining ingredients, except pepper.
Cover and cook over low heat 30 to 40 minutes. Add pepper. Cook 15 minutes more. Stir now and then. Serve over rice or pasta, if you like.
Serves 4.

title: easy turkey pot pie
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together in a bowl. Pie shells must be slightly thawed.
Pour ingredients into pie shell carefully. Remove the other shell from the tin pan and layer over the top. Seal around the edges.
Bake in preheated oven at 450°. Serves 4.

title: almond chicken
directions: Slice chicken breasts thinly. Stir-fry in hot oil in heavy skillet for 5 minutes. Add onion and celery. Stir-fry for 5 minutes.
Add water chestnuts, bamboo shoots, chicken broth and soy sauce, mixing well. Cook, covered, for 5 minutes.
Blend cornstarch and sugar with water. Stir into chicken.
Cook until thickened, stirring constantly. Sprinkle with almonds and serve over rice. Serves 4.

title: spanish lima beans in a snap
directions: Microwave Directions:
Place onion, red pepper, garlic, oil and thyme in microwave dish.
Cover and cook on High 1 minute or until red pepper is tender-crisp.
Stir in lima beans.
Cover and cook on High 3 to 4 minutes or until hot.
Makes 4 servings.

title: quick peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Combine flour, 1 cup sugar and milk; mix well.
Pour over melted butter; do not stir. Combine peaches and remaining 1 cup sugar in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Pour over butter; do not stir.
Bake in a 375° oven for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: pizza breadsticks
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Knead dough over baking stone.
Cover dough and let rest 15 minutes.
Stretch dough over stone again. Brush dough with olive oil.
Press garlic and spread over dough. Grate cheese over dough.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes or until light brown.
Cut with pizza cutter and dip in sauce.

title: hot cheese dip
directions: Melt cheese in microwave on High for 2 minutes. Add hot chunky salsa.
Serve over or with tortilla chips.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients; place in casserole dish.
Top with cracker crumbs.
Pour melted butter over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars.
Beat together eggs, peanut butter and hot water.
Gradually blend in flour.
Form cookies on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Yields 7 to 8 dozen.

title: zucchini appetizer(yields about 4 dozen pieces)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients together and spread in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Bake for about 25 minutes, or until brown.
Cut into squares.
Serve hot or cold.

title: salsa
directions: Crush coriander seed and soak in 1 tablespoon of water; set aside.

title: mexican rice
directions: In a large skillet, heat oil over medium heat.
Saute onion, garlic and rice in oil, stirring constantly, until rice is golden brown.
Break up tomatoes into small pieces.
`Add tomatoes and juice and chicken stock to the rice.
Stir only enough to mix. Cover and simmer 20 to 30 minutes, until rice is tender and liquid is absorbed.
Do not uncover or stir during cooking time.

title: 7 layer cookies
directions: Melt butter in cookie sheet.
Add Eagle Brand condensed milk. Add butterscotch chips, chocolate chips, coconut flakes and chopped nuts.
Bake in slow oven at 250° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: apple squares
directions: Add eggs and shortening to flour, 1 cup sugar, baking powder, vanilla and salt; mix well.
Take 3/4 of mixture and press into ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with 1 can fruit.
Mix remainder of mixture with brown sugar.
Sprinkle evenly over fruit.
Bake in 350° oven for 40 to 50 minutes.
Sprinkle cinnamon and/or powdered sugar when cooled.
Cut into squares and put in cupcake papers to serve.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: Cook the pasta, drain and rinse with cold water.
Preheat the oven to 350°.
Lightly oil a two quart casserole dish.
Place 1/2 the pasta in the bottom, top with 1/2 the sauce and 1/2 of the cheese and 1/2 breadcrumbs.
Repeat.
Bake for
20 to 30 minutes of until the top is lightly browned.
Serve warm.
For a more meaty taste you can add ground beef or Italian sausage.

title: cheese and broccoli soup
directions: In large saucepan, place chopped cheese, broccoli, chicken broth, onion and pepper.
Bring to a boil and simmer 10 minutes or until broccoli is tender.
Process in blender until smooth.
Return to saucepan.
Add all but 1/4 cup milk.
Return to boil, stirring occasionally.
Stir cornstarch into reserved 1/4 cup milk.
Add slowly to boiling soup.
Simmer until thickened.
Reduce heat and stir in cheese until melted.

title: jello mold with sour cream
directions: Prepare jello with 5 cups water in a large bowl.
Add fruit with liquid and nuts (bananas, pineapple, strawberries and nuts). Scoop 1/2 into jello mold pan.
Refrigerate. Set aside remaining mixture. When first half is jelled, spread sour cream over mold, then scoop remaining mixture over sour cream and refrigerate to set.
Best made 1 day in advance (overnight).

title: broccoli and cauliflower casserole with ham
directions: Cook vegetables until crisp; drain well.
Saute margarine and finely chopped onion.
Blend cream cheese and mushroom soup.
Stir in ham dices.
Place cooked vegetables in a 10 x 13-inch dish. Pour sauteed onion, cream cheese, ham and soup over vegetables. Cover with grated cheese.
Crush crackers and sprinkle over the top.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes, uncovered.
Serves 10.

title: easy lasagna
directions: Brown hamburger and onion; add salt, pepper and garlic salt. Meanwhile cook noodles according to package directions.
Mix together noodles and soup; top with meat mixture; then tomato sauce.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: lite pistachio salad
directions: Mix Cool Whip and dry instant pudding; add pineapple and marshmallows.
Refrigerate.

title: strawberry angel delight
directions: Boil water.
Mix with jello and add frozen strawberries.
Let stand while berries thaw in jello.

title: nut or jelly squares
directions: Warm to lukewarm 1/4 cup milk and crumble the yeast into warm milk.
Set aside.
Sift baking powder, salt, sugar and 1 cup of flour into 6 cups of flour.
Cut shortening into the flour mixture. Add yeast mixture.
Beat eggs until lemon colored, then add to mixture.
Knead until smooth.
Add flour if necessary.
Cover with a bowl and set aside.

title: quark
directions: Using a blender or electric mixer, combine all ingredients. Serve over granola or fresh fruit.

title: "hardy soup" - a heart healthy recipe
directions: Mix beef bouillon in 8 cups of water and bring to a boil. Brown turkey and onions and add to soup pot.
Add sliced carrots, corn, basil and bay leaf; cover and simmer for 45 minutes.
Add 3/4 cup of crushed tomatoes and pasta "bows; " simmer for 10 more minutes.

title: paste e fagioli(bean soup)
directions: Melt a little butter in saucepan.
Add celery, onions and parsley.
Cook over medium heat only until wilted.
Add the beans (with liquid), water, tomato sauce and seasonings.
While this simmers gently, break up spaghetti and boil in a separate pan of salted, boiling water.
Cook until al dente (a chewy stage), about 5 minutes.
Strain pasta and add to soup.
Cook about 5 minutes longer, then serve hot in bowls with fresh minced parsley and plenty of grated cheese.

title: thank you pie filling
directions: Peel and slice apples.
Fill quart jars.
Cook first four ingredients and water until thick and bubbly.
Add lemon juice. Pour syrup over apples while hot.
Can in hot water canner 30 minutes.
Makes 7 to 8 quarts.

title: baked acorn squash
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Split squash into halves and scoop out the fibers and seeds.
Sprinkle the cavity of each half with remaining nutmeg, salt, pepper, brown sugar and a teaspoon of butter.
Bake 30 to 45 minutes or until flesh is tender.
Five minutes before serving, add a teaspoon of sherry to each cavity. Serves 6.

title: turkey dressing
directions: Fry onions, celery and apple until tender.
Break bread and add rest of ingredients.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: mexican cheese dip
directions: Melt cheese.
Brown hamburger and drain grease.
Mix together with taco sauce, seasoning package and refried beans.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Place chicken in lightly oiled baking pan.
Sprinkle with salt and ginger.
Top with diced celery.
Bake at 325° until lightly browned (about 20 minutes).
Drain pineapple juice into cup.
Blend in brown sugar, water, soy sauce, vinegar and cornstarch (or use ready made sweet and sour sauce from store).
Pour mixture over chicken.
Continue baking for about 45 minutes, or until chicken is done.
Ten to 15 minutes before chicken is cooked, top with pineapple chunks and red pepper.

title: chocolate marshmallow surprise
directions: Place marshmallows standing up in round/oval serving dish.
In a double boiler, melt 1 cube of butter/margarine over medium-low heat so it doesn't burn.
Combine peanut butter and chocolate chips to margarine mixture, stirring until melted and smooth.
Remove from heat; immediately pour over marshmallows evenly.
Place in refrigerator until hard.
Put around each marshmallow and serve.

title: tuna casserole
directions: In large skillet, bring soup and water to a boil.
Add rice, vegetables and tuna.
Stir.
Remove from heat.
Place cheese on top.
Cover and let stand for five minutes.

title: homemade bread
directions: Let rise 45 minutes. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: taco salad
directions: Drain cooked hamburger; stir in taco seasoning.
Chill.
At time of serving, toss all ingredients in large bowl or individual bowls.
Add dressing and throw in corn chips.

title: jalapeno pepper jelly
directions: Grind or finely chop peppers.
Combine peppers, lemon juice and sugar.
Boil 10 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add pectin. Return to high heat and boil for 1 minute.
Remove and place in sterilized jars.
Place in boiling water for 5 minutes.

title: chopped chicken liver pate
directions: Melt butter and when hot, saute chicken livers until done. In last two minutes, add chopped onion and celery.
Add salt and pepper.
Put chicken livers, onion, celery, hard-boiled egg and butter drippings through a food chopper.
Place in refrigerator and chill for several hours.
Shape on oval platter and serve with crackers.

title: creamy carrot bake
directions: Cook carrots in boiling water 10 minutes or until tender; drain.
Combine next 6 ingredients; mix well.
Add carrots; toss gently.
Spoon into lightly greased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish. Combine breadcrumbs and butter; mix well.
Sprinkle over carrot mixture; bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: pie crust
directions: Measure shortening into large mixing bowl.
Add boiling water and stir until shortening is dissolved.
Add flour and salt and mix until blended with shortening and water.
Divide mixture into three parts and wrap in wax paper.
Refrigerate crusts until thoroughly chilled.

title: scallop puffs
directions: In a large skillet, melt butter.
Saute lemon rind, garlic and scallops for 3 minutes.
Stirring constantly, add the dill and cook 30 seconds longer.
Cool to room temperature.
Stir in cheese, mayo and pepper.
Refrigerate covered until ready to use (up to 3 days). Remove crusts from bread.
Cut into quarters.
Toast at 400° for 5 minutes.
Turn over and top with scallop mix.
Sprinkle with paprika.

title: hot spiced cider
directions: Mix together in crock-pot or stove top.
Cover and cook on low for 2 hours or until hot.
Enjoy!

title: chili
directions: Brown beef, pepper, onion and garlic.
Add tomatoes, cumin and chili powder.
Cook about 1 1/2 hours.
Add beans and cook 1/2 hour more.
If thick, add a little water.
You may add Tabasco if you like.

title: cream cheese, beef and bread appetizer
directions: Mix all ingredients except bread together.
Cut off the top of the sourdough ball and hollow out the inside.
Slice the hollowed out bread and any extra sourdough pieces you need into 2 x 2-inch pieces.
Put these on a cookie sheet and set aside.
