Put mixture into hollowed bread ball.
Place on another cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Place sliced pieces in oven a few minutes before bread ball is done to get bread slices warm and crusty.
Place cooked ball and dip onto a platter, arranging the sliced bread around it and dig in.

title: blue cheese dip
directions: Beat cream cheese in small mixer bowl until it gets fluffy. Add milk, one tablespoon at a time, as you beat.
Amount will vary. Beat just until fluffy, not too thin.
Add garlic salt.
Fold in Blue cheese and minced parsley.
Place in serving dish.
Cover and chill.

title: low-fat golden glaze chicken
directions: In a small bowl, thoroughly combine onion soup mix, preserves and water.
Set aside.
In aluminum foil lined broiler pan, arrange chicken breasts and peppers.
Top with soup mixture. Broil 10 minutes or until chicken is done, turning once. Serve over hot rice.
Makes about 4 servings.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate.

title: almond tea
directions: Combine sugar, 2 cups of water and lemon rind in saucepan. Bring to a boil, stirring until sugar is dissolved.
Add tea, almond extract, vanilla, lemon juice and enough water to equal 1 gallon liquid.
Serve hot or cold.
Yields 16 servings.

title: cheese patties
directions: Mix all ingredients (except cornflakes) to form patties.
Roll in cornflake crumbs.
Fry in small amount of oil until well cooked.
(Patties can be formed, frozen and fried just before serving.)

title: pumpkin or squash pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add squash or pumpkin, molasses, eggs, butter and milk.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake for 10 minutes at 450°, then for 40 minutes at 350°, or until done.

title: pan pizza
directions: In large bowl, dissolve yeast from roll mix in 1 cup warm water.
Stir in flour mixture from mix and 1/2 cup of the Parmesan cheese.
Cover and let rest 10 minutes.
With greased fingers, pat dough out onto bottom and halfway up sides of a greased 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch baking pan.
Bake at 375° until deep golden brown (about 20 minutes).

title: steak and rice
directions: Cook meat for 1 hour (no seasoning) with oil and water until tender.
Add vegetables.
Cook 5 minutes.
Stir in bouillon water; bring to boil, adding ginger and soy sauce.
Add 1 1/2 cups instant rice; cover.
Remove from heat.
Let stand 5 to 10 minutes.

title: easy barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients on low heat until it begins to thicken.
Pour over any meat and cook according to the meat.

title: sweet potato crunch
directions: Mix all the ingredients well and put into buttered dish.

title: lime congealed salad
directions: Drain pineapple; heat juice and add jello.
Stir until dissolved.
Cool; add marshmallows and cottage cheese.
Mix well. Fold in Cool Whip.

title: pink champagne salad
directions: Mix cream cheese and sugar.
Add rest of ingredients.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Freeze.
Serves 12 to 15.

title: dilled garden dip
directions: Combine cottage cheese and vinegar in container of an electric blender; process until smooth.
Combine cottage cheese mixture, milk, green onions, 1 tablespoon chopped parsley, dill weed and pepper in a medium mixing bowl.
Cover and chill at least 2 hours.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients and cook over low heat until mixture thickens.
Put in vanilla and margarine.
Pour into baked pie crust.
Top with meringue made from 3 egg whites and brown.

title: stuffed clams
directions: Mix ingredients together, mix well. Fill foil cups to 1\3 to 1\2 full.
Bake at 400° for 10 min.

title: protestor's dessert
directions: Hollow out baked angel food cake, leaving a 3/4-inch shell. Break apart the cake pieces into smaller pieces for the filling. Stir the top 3 ingredients until dissolved.
When cool, add pineapple.
Refrigerate until soft set.
Then add cake pieces and whipped cream or use Cool Whip.
Fold in gently and fill cake with mixture.
Refrigerate until set.
Frost cake with whipped cream. (Can make this a day before you have committed to protesting somewhere.)

title: chicken in a garden
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine chicken, vegetables, water chestnuts, soup and milk.
Mix well.
Add 1 cup onions.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake, covered, for 45 minutes.
Uncover and top with remaining onions.
Bake, uncovered, for 10 minutes.

title: hamburger chowder
directions: Brown hamburger and onion evenly.
Add tomatoes, carrots, celery, barley or rice and seasonings.
Add water.
Cover; simmer for about 1 hour.
Add potatoes (optional); cook until tender.

title: peanut butter 'n' milk chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, with electric mixer on medium speed, beat margarine, sugars and peanut butter until light and fluffy.
Blend in eggs and vanilla.
Mix in flour, baking soda and salt.
Stir in chips.
Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool two minutes; remove from cookie sheet to wire racks to cool.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: cheddar onion bites
directions: Heat broiler. Mix mayo and onions. Spread on toasted bread slices. Top with cheese. Broil 2-3 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: hanky panky
directions: Brown beef and sausage; pour off grease. Combine seasonings and 1 pound Velveeta cheese; stir into beef mixture. Spread on party size rye bread.
Bake 8 minutes at 450°.

title: sour cream corn
directions: Cook onion and green pepper in oleo.
Add flour and salt then sour cream and bring to a boil.
Heat corn and mix all ingredients together.
May be garnished with cooked bacon crumbled on top.

title: muffins
directions: Mix ingredients well.
If adding blueberries, add 1/4 to 1/3 cup additional sugar.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: fudge pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour, cocoa and water. Stir until mixture is thick. Add butter and vanilla. Pour into baked pie crust.

title: bakery icing
directions: Cream half of the sugar with shortening.
Add stiffly beaten egg whites and remaining sugar.
Add vanilla and lemon to taste. Beat well.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown and salt and pepper the pork chops in 2 tablespoons cooking oil.
Peel and slice potatoes and put in rectangular pan or baking dish.
Peel and slice onion and put on top of potatoes.
Salt and pepper over potatoes and onion. Put pork chops on top of the potatoes and onion.
Take cream of mushroom soup and the 1 can of milk and mix together in a bowl. Pour over pork chops and potatoes.
Bake, uncovered, in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: pickled beets
directions: Boil sugar and vinegar until sugar is dissolved.
Pour over beets.
Cover; let cool.
Refrigerate.
Let set a few days.

title: peanut butter waldorf salad
directions: In medium bowl, combine apples, raisins and celery.
In a small bowl, combine yogurt, vanilla and peanut butter.
Pour over apple mixture and toss gently.
Cover and chill.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix flour, meal and buttermilk in a large bowl.
Add onions, sugar, baking powder, salt and pepper.
Mix well and then deep fry.

title: potato casserole au gratin
directions: Boil potatoes with jackets on until almost tender, about 15 minutes.
Drain and let cool.
Melt butter in saucepan.
Stir in flour.
Slowly add chicken broth and cook, stirring constantly, until thickened and bubbly.
Stir in cream, salt and pepper. Remove from heat.
Cover and let cool.
Peel and grate potatoes. Combine with celery, onion, cheese, melted butter and salt.
Stir sour cream into cooled cream sauce, then fold sauce into grated potato mixture.
Turn into 9 x 13-inch shallow baking dish. Sprinkle with breadcrumbs.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: chicken cordon blue
directions: Place chicken between 2 pieces of waxed paper and pound until cutlets are 1/4-inch thick.
Place ham and cheese slices on top of each and roll up each (like jelly roll).
Dip into eggs and bread crumbs, then brown slowly in butter and garlic (slowly about 25 minutes).
Remove cutlets and add lemon juice and wine to the pan juice.
Boil and scoop up all browned bits and pour over cutlets, then bake 10 minutes at 350°.

title: baked salmon steaks
directions: Mix lemon juice, salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Dip salmon steak in mixture and place in baking dish.
Sprinkle diced onion and sliced tomatoes on top.
Bake in microwave for 15 minutes. Serves 4.

title: clam chowder
directions: Fry bacon and cut into tiny pieces.
Add onion to skillet and saute until golden.
Return bacon bits to skillet with potatoes and juice from clams. Add enough water to cover potatoes and simmer, covered, until potatoes are tender.
Add clams, cream (or milk) and parsley.
Warm gently; do not boil. Add salt and pepper to taste. Yield: 3 servings.

title: cherry cream pie
directions: Mix the cream cheese and whipping cream together and add the sugar.
Slice bananas and place in the bottom of the pie crusts. Pour cream cheese mixture over the bananas.
Put the cherries on top.

title: southwest tart
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease (or Pam) a 9-inch spring-form or 10-inch pie pan. Combine Bisquick, cornmeal, 1 cup Cheddar cheese and chilies. Stir in broth.
Pat mixture into bottom of pan. Spoon beans over tart to within 1/2-inch of edge. Sprinkle with remaining cheese. Bake 35 minutes. Cool.
Remove spring-form pan and arrange tomatoes. Serve with toppings.

title: mincemeat pie
directions: Brown beef in small skillet; drain.
Break mincemeat in small pieces.
Mix beef, mincemeat, apple and sugar.
Add water; heat to boiling.
Boil and stir 3 minutes.
Cool.
Prepare pastry.
Pour mincemeat mixture into pastry-lined 9-inch pan.
Bake until pie is bubbly at 425° and crust is brown, 35 to 45 minutes.
Makes a 9-inch two crust pie.
Very good!

title: easy butterscotch rolls
directions: The night before, place a layer of frozen rolls in well-greased Bundt pan. Sprinkle pudding mix (dry) over rolls. Melt butter and add brown sugar and nuts, mixing well. Pour over rolls. Cover with towel and let rise for 8 to 10 hours. Bake in preheated 350° oven for 30 minutes. Turn onto plate while hot.

title: ground beef and rice casserole
directions: Cook onion, bell pepper and celery.
Stir well and add the 2 cans soup, rinsing each can with 1/4 cup water.
Place in casserole dish and spread 1 cup uncooked rice on top.
Add 1 cup water, cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix cream cheese, pimentos, onions, garlic and shredded cheese until well mixed. Roll into ball, then roll in crushed pecans. Put in the refrigerator until firm. Serve with crackers.

title: chicken crescent roll casserole
directions: Cook and bone chicken. Roll small chunks of chicken in each crescent roll. Mix soup, milk and cheese and pour into 9 x 13 pan. You can either put the rolled crescents directly on the soup mixture and bake that way or put the crescents on a cookie sheet and bake about half the baking time given on the can, then put over the hot soup mixture and finish baking. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes until browned.

title: rice stuffed fish fillets
directions: In medium saucepan, combine 2 cups water, rice and sauce mix and green onions.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat to medium-low and simmer 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Heat oven broiler. Layer on fish fillet, smooth side up, on work surface.
Spread 1/2 cup rice mixture over fillet and roll up starting at narrow end. Place roll in shallow baking dish, seam side down.
Repeat with remaining fillets.
Sprinkle bread crumbs evenly over fish rolls; drizzle with melted butter.
Broil 5 to 6 inches from heat for 4 to 5 minutes.
Serve with lemon wedges.

title: nut horns
directions: Blend eggs, margarine and sugar.
Add flour and salt.
Add dissolved yeast.
Roll out on sugar.
Cut in triangles.
Put nut mixture (walnuts, 1/2 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon vanilla) in center and roll.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: enchiladas
directions: Heat chili in pan over low heat.
Dip tortillas in hot chili. Place in center of each tortilla grated cheese and chopped onion. Roll each tortilla and place, seam side down, in shallow baking dish.
Cover with remaining chili.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake in oven at 350° for 15 minutes.
Makes 12.

title: rover's favorite crumb cake
directions: Pick over and wash the berries.
Drain in a sieve and turn them onto a towel.
Pat dry and set aside to dry.
Preheat oven to 375°. In a small bowl combine 1/3 cup of flour, the cinnamon and 1/2 cup sugar.
Cut in 1/4 cup of the butter until the mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Set aside.
Sift together the remaining flour, baking powder and salt.
Place blueberries in a bowl and sprinkle with 1 1/2 tablespoons of the dry ingredients.
Toss gently.
Set aside.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix jello with sugar and salt.
Add hot water and stir until dissolved.
Add mayonnaise and lemon juice. Mix with rotary beater until dissolved.
Pour in refrigerator tray and let chill.
Remove and pour in cranberry sauce, fruit and nuts.
Pour into mold and chill until firm.

title: caramel rolls
directions: Thaw frozen bread dough.
Pull into small pieces and place in greased Bundt pan.
Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.
Bring brown sugar, ice cream and butter to rolling boil; cool.
Pour over dough.
Let rise until double.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes.

title: amanda's play doh
directions: Cook, stirring constantly, until it balls together like biscuit dough.
Cool.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: This favorite was discovered on our excursions to Miami art festivals.
Falafel is sold as a street snack, a pita sandwich and is called a "dig dag.".
The sabras claim it as part of their Oriental heritage, and in Israel, falafel is an ingredient of many dishes.

title: breakfast bread custard
directions: Cut the bread into thick slices, then arrange on a 7 x 10 ovenproof glass baking pan.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Whisk together the eggs and milk and season with the pepper.
Arrange tomato slices over the bread.
Pour egg and milk mixture over all. Sprinkle with the cilantro and top with cheese.
Bake for 15 minutes or until custard sets.
Serve in squares.

title: skillet sour cream corn bread
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients
in bowl, mixing well.
Add cornmeal and baking powder,
mixing
well.	Pour
into greased 10-inch iron skillet.
Bake at
for
30 minutes or until cornbread tests done.

title: pork sausage cake
directions: Cover raisins with water and simmer for 20 minutes.
Mix all other ingredients except water.
Add water from raisins.
Bake in 2 lightly greased and floured round 9-inch cake pans at 350° about 45 minutes.
When cake is cool, ice with Penucle Icing.

title: company ham and noodles
directions: In a skillet over medium heat, saute onion in butter until tender. Add ham.
Cook and stir until heated through.
Sprinkle with flour and stir for 1 minute. Reduce heat to low. Gradually stir in sour cream. Add the mushrooms.
Cook and stir until thickened, about 2 to 3 minutes. Serve over noodles.
Garnish with parsley, if desired.
Yields 6 servings.

title: just for kids play dough
directions: Mix all ingredients with a fork.
Boil over medium heat until thick.
Store in an airtight container.
This has a wonderful velvety texture.

title: peanut butter and chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar and peanut butter with mixer.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Stir in flour, baking soda, salt and chips.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Allow to cool for 3 minutes; remove from cookie sheet. Makes 3 1/2 to 4 dozen.

title: easy lasagna
directions: Brown turkey.
Wash off excess fat in a large strainer.
Mix with spaghetti sauce and water.
Cook 1/2 package (nine lasagna noodles).
Mix together 8 ounce package low-fat skim Mozzarella cheese with 1/2 cup low-fat cottage cheese.
Use a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put a layer of sauce in bottom of pan.
Line pan with a layer of noodles.
Put another layer of sauce on noodles.
Spread cheese mixture on sauce.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: pork chops and stuffing
directions: Combine soup and stuffing.
Spoon stuffing mixture in greased pie plate.
Arrange chops over stuffing, pressing down lightly into stuffing.
Combine sugar and mustard and spread over chops. Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Mix together pretzels, butter and 3 teaspoons sugar.
Place in 13 x 9-inch pan and bake at 400° for 8 minutes.
Do not overbake!
Combine softened cream cheese, 1 cup sugar and Cool Whip; mix well.
Spread mixture on cooled pretzels.
Mix together jello, frozen strawberries and boiling water.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Pour over the top of cream cheese mixture.
Refrigerate.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Mash sweet potatoes.
Be sure to get all lumps out.
Add 1/2 stick oleo, nutmeg, sugar, milk, cinnamon and eggs.
Mix.
Pour into a greased baking pan.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or until firm.
Melt 1/2 stick oleo.
Add brown sugar, nuts and corn flakes.
Mix.
Spread on sweet potatoes and bake for about 15 minutes.

title: pecan pralines
directions: Combine all ingredients and cook to soft ball stage.
Remove from heat; add nuts and drop on wax paper.

title: peanut butter blossoms
directions: Sift together flour, soda and salt; set aside.
Cream together butter, peanut butter, sugar and vanilla.
Add egg and brown sugar.
Slowly add flour mixture.
Batter with be stiff.
Round teaspoonful of dough shape into balls.
Roll balls in sugar and bake 8 minutes.
Remove from oven add a chocolate kiss press down until cookie cracks.
Bake 2 to 5 minutes longer.

title: coconut dream cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions (2 layers or oblong pan). Let cool.

title: oyster cracker snacks
directions: Place crackers in large bowl.
Combine all other ingredients. Mix well.
Pour over crackers.
Stir well to spread evenly over crackers.
Spread on large baking sheet.
Bake at 250° for 15 minutes.
Stir halfway through.
Cool before storing in airtight container.

title: macaroni 'n cheese
directions: Toss cooked macaroni in 2 tablespoons of oil.
Add all remaining ingredients.
Pour into lightly greased crock-pot.
Stir well.
Cover and cook on low 3 to 4 hours.
Stir occasionally.

title: confetti slaw
directions: Combine cabbage, pimentos, tomatoes and green pepper in large bowl.
Mix sugar, vinegar and salt in small bowl.
Add to cabbage mixture; toss well.
Chill for 24 hours before serving.
Yield: 24 servings.

title: banana-nut cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar, adding eggs, 1 at a time, milk and flour.
Beat after additions, then add bananas and beat.
Then fold in pecans.
Bake in a greased and floured tube pan at 300° for 1 hour.

title: festive chicken bake
directions: Combine flour, salt and pepper.
Dredge chicken in flour. Brown in hot oil.
Drain pineapple, reserving juice.
Combine juice, molasses, mustard and vinegar; mix well.
Place chicken in 3-quart casserole; arrange potatoes around chicken.
Brush with half of sauce.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Uncover and top with pineapple.
Brush with remaining sauce.
Cook 30 minutes more.
Makes 4 servings.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream margarine or butter.
Cream cheese and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add vanilla and lemon flavoring.
Add flour slowly.
I put this cake in a cold oven and then set the temperature at 325° for 1 1/2 hours or until brown and leaves sides of pan.

title: pasta salad
directions: Wash and prepare vegetables in bite size pieces.
Let drain. In a large bowl, combine all ingredients except salad dressing. Mix well and chill.
About 30 minutes before serving, add salad dressing and toss thoroughly.
(Recommended:
Italian or Ranch.)

title: gemasetti
directions: Cook noodles in salted water.
Fry sausages in bite size pieces with diced green pepper and diced onion.
Add tomato soup. Mix well and add to drained noodles.
Place in 1 1/2-quart casserole; top with strips of cheese.
Bake 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: frito pie
directions: Heat chili.
In single serving bowl, put a layer of Fritos on bottom, then some chili, then some cheese, lettuce, tomatoes and onion.
Top with a few Fritos.

title: skillet macaroni and beef
directions: Cook beef until browned; drain fat.
Stir in macaroni, onion, green pepper, salt and pepper.
Cook, stirring occasionally, until macaroni is translucent.
Add tomato sauce, water and Worcestershire sauce.
Cover and simmer for 20 minutes.
Stir and let stand for 5 minutes with heat off.

title: eat-your-heart-out fudge
directions: Cut a piece of foil big enough to fit inside and up over the edges of an 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish or pan.
Place foil in the pan and press against bottom, sides and corners to fit the pan. Set aside.
Stir in a large microwavable bowl powdered sugar, milk and salt.
Add butter.
Microwave, uncovered, at 100% power (700 watts) for 1 minute.
Stir.
Microwave at 100% power for 1 1/2 minutes.
Stir.
Microwave at 100% power for 1 1/2 minutes longer or until bubbling.
Total cooking time is 4 minutes.
Bowl will be hot!
Use hot pads and place directly on a wooden board or heatproof surface.
Quickly add chocolate chips, peanut butter and vanilla.
Stir until melted and blended.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Melt oleo; mix all together.
Add oatmeal last.
Put in pie shell.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix sugar and eggs together.
Add vanilla and butter.
Fold in flour, a little at a time.
If it starts getting too thick, add bananas.
Alternate flour and bananas, then add nuts.
Do not overbeat!
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cheesy bread
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix cheese, margarine and seasoning. Spread on bread.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake for 5 to 10 minutes, until lightly browned.

title: tuna crunch
directions: Combine and mix thoroughly.

title: sausage and egg casserole
directions: Place bread cubes in grated 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Layer sausage over bread; sprinkle cheese (and mushrooms, if desired) over sausage layer.
Combine egg, dry mustard and 2 1/2 cups milk. Pour over all.
Cover and refrigerate 3 hours or overnight.

title: chocolate-vanilla pudding cake
directions: Mix chopped pecans, flour, sugar and softened oleo.
Press in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 350° or until slightly browned.
Mix cream cheese and powdered sugar until fluffy; add half of Cool Whip.
Spread over crust.

title: pennsylvania dutch pork chops
directions: In skillet, heat bacon drippings or oil and brown pork chops on both sides.
Combine applesauce, sauerkraut, onion, brown sugar and caraway seed.
Spoon over chops.
Season with salt and pepper. Cover and simmer until chops are tender, 35 to 45 minutes.

title: pepper steak
directions: Heat salad oil; add salt and pepper.
Add steak to oil.
Cook over high heat until brown.
Add onion and garlic salt.
Add green peppers and celery.
Dissolve bouillon in boiling water; add to mixture.
Cover.
Cook over moderate heat until meat and vegetables are tender.
Blend cornstarch in 1/4 cup water.
Add soy sauce. Add to mixture.
Cook, stirring constantly, until sauce thickens. Serve over fluffy rice.

title: half-a-pound cake
directions: Cream sugar, butter and shortening until light and fluffy; add eggs, one at a time.
Beat well.
Combine cake flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to creamed mixture alternating with milk.
Add extracts.
Beat 5 minutes.
Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until done.

title: gretchen's french silk pie
directions: Beat sugar and butter until fluffy.
Blend in melted chocolate and vanilla.
Add eggs, one at a time and beat for 5 minutes each. Pour into pie shell and chill until set.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Take sugar cookie dough out of package and slice 1/4-inch. Place round slices on pizza pan.
Bake at 350° until brown.
Dough will spread to make crust.
Let cool.
Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and vanilla until smooth.
Spread on cooled crust.
Top with can of drained fruit cocktail or any fresh fruit desired.
Slice like pizza.
Delicious!

title: clam dip
directions: Mix together all ingredients and chill.

title: hobo stew
directions: Use ingredients in the quantity you have on hand or need to fill the casserole or baking dish you have selected.
You may cut potatoes to your liking.
Layer ingredients in the order listed, repeating layers as needed.
Pour tomato soup over mixture.
Add no water.
Bake for 2 to 2 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: mama's fudge
directions: Pour boiling ingredients in bowl and stir until chocolate is melted.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Let stand a few hours before cutting.
Store in tin box.

title: black walnut cake
directions: Cream butter, shortening and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Mix together dry ingredients.
Add to creamed mixture alternating with the milk.
Add flavoring and nuts. Batter will be very stiff.
Bake in a greased and floured tube pan at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Don't peek while cooking.

title: salad dressing
directions: Put all ingredients in quart jar, cover and shake well to mix. Add 1/2 teaspoon garlic salt; shake.
Chill; keep in refrigerator.
Good over lettuce wedges.

title: russian sauce
directions: Mix in a double boiler and cook until mixture thickens.
Add 2 tablespoons coconut while still hot.
Let cool and add 1/2 pint whipped cream.
Serve over slices of angel food cake.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Add eggs and oil.
Stir until moistened.
Do not beat.
Stir in vanilla, pineapple, nuts and bananas.
Spoon batter into well-greased and floured tube pan. Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes or until cake tests done. Let cool 30 minutes.
(May also be baked in three 9-inch pans at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.)
Frost with Cream Cheese Frosting:

title: chicken crescent
directions: Roll out rolls and coat with a thin layer of mayonnaise. Place cubed chicken in rolls and roll up. Mix soups and pour over rolls. Dot with butter. Bake at 350° until rolls are golden brown, approximately 30 to 45 minutes.

title: scalloped salmon
directions: Mix all together in a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Dot with butter.
Bake in oven at 375° for 1 hour.

title: pecan pie
directions: Dump dry pudding mix into bowl, mix with Karo syrup and stir. Gradually add slightly beaten egg, stir.
Gradually add milk, stir. Add pecans.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.
Makes one pie.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Blend artichoke hearts in a food processor.
Mix all ingredients and put in a small baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour or until golden brown.
Serve with crackers or Melba toast.

title: herb-triangles-snack
directions: Mix all ingredients in small bowl.
Brush very thin layer on flour tortillas.
Cut in wedges and place single layer on baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes or until crisp or golden brown.
Serve warm or cold.

title: all day beef stew
directions: Put all ingredients into a large ovenproof pan.
Mix and cover.
Cook in preheated oven at 250° for 7 hours, at 300° for 5 hours or at 350° for 3 hours.
It makes its own gravy.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Halve all ingredients and place in layers as they are listed. End with bread crumb topping.
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°, using 8 x 8-inch casserole dish.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream together sour cream, butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, with a portion of flour and continue
beating
until
all is combined and well mixed. Add flavorings.
Pour
into
a
large greased and floured (or spray with
Baker's Joy) Bundt pan and bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours. Keeps well.

title: pudding salad
directions: Make pudding and chill well.
Drain and chill fruit.
Fold together with whipped topping before serving.

title: onion sloppy joes
directions: Brown and drain ground beef. In a skillet, stir in flour and soup. Heat on medium-high heat until thick. Add mushrooms. Serve on buns.

title: scalloped pineapple
directions: Mix all ingredients, except cinnamon, in large bowl; place in 8 x 11-inch glass casserole dish.
Sprinkle cinnamon on top for crust (optional).
Preheat oven to 375°.
Bake 50 minutes.

title: fried spaghetti
directions: Cook and drain spaghetti according to instructions.
Set aside.
Cut onion tops into 1-inch pieces. Saute briefly in hot oil.
Remove and set aside.
Cut chicken into bite-size pieces. Stir-fry in
hot oil.
Season with garlic, salt and pepper. Remove.
Toss cooked spaghetti in frying pan with oil and soy sauce to taste.
Add chicken and onions.
Stir-fry.
Sprinkle a pinch of sugar.
Stir and serve.

title: meat loaf-microwave
directions: Saute
onion
in
oleo.
Mix all other ingredients with sauteed onion.
Place in a greased 5 x 2 x 8-inch baking dish. Bake
on High in 700 watt microwave for 14 minutes, uncovered. Cover
with
foil
and
set
for
10 minutes.
Remove foil and serve.
Very good.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook and cool macaroni.
Add vegetables and mix well.
Combine Eagle Brand milk, vinegar, sugar, mayonnaise, salt and pepper.
Add to macaroni and vegetables.
Mix well.
Chill 4 hours before serving.

title: quick stove top baked beans
directions: Render a slice of bacon.
Add the pork and beans.
Add a dash of mustard powder and brown sugar; stir as mixture simmers slightly to thicken.
Add ketchup (about 3 good smacks on the bottom of the bottle) and onion slices.
You may also use onion flakes or onion salt.
Simmer and stir until hot.
For larger amounts, add more of everything.

title: old fashioned apple pie
directions: Slice apples into bowl and mix with sugar and cinnamon.
Line pie pan with bottom crust.
Sprinkle 1 tablespoon sugar and 1 tablespoon flour in bottom of pan and stir with fingers.
Mix remaining flour into apples.
Pile in pan and dot with butter. Put on top crust and seal.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 400° for 40 minutes.

title: giant oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream together butter or margarine, sugar, brown sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Sift together flour, salt, soda, cinnamon, cloves, ginger and allspice.
Add to creamed mixture and stir in oatmeal, nuts and raisins.
Drop dough by 1/4 cup measure 5-inches apart onto lightly greased cookie sheet.	Bake 12 to 14 minutes at 375° or until lightly browned.
Cool on wire rack.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cut squash in 1/2-inch pieces and cook until just tender. Drain.
Mix all ingredients except cornbread crumbs for top.
Put in greased casserole dish and bake at 350° for 35 minutes approximately (ovens vary).

title: helen leatherwood's pear relish
directions: Put pears, onions, peppers and pimento through a grinder on medium setting.
Sprinkle salt over the ground mixture.
Soak overnight (no water).
Next morning, pour all in a colander. Rinse all salt out. In a large container, put vinegar, sugar, turmeric and mustard seed.
Bring to a boil and let boil 5 minutes.
Add all ground ingredients, stirring constantly.
Return to boil.
Add celery seed and garlic powder, if desired.
Let boil another 1/2 hour.
Jar while hot and seal.

title: avocado corn salsa
directions: Toss together adding avocado last.
Cover and refrigerate. Make up to 8 hours in advance.
Serve with chips.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs lightly into large bowl.
Stir in oil, sugar, zucchini and vanilla.
Sift flour, baking soda, baking powder, cinnamon and salt onto wax paper.
Stir into egg mixture until well blended.
Stir in raisins and nuts.
Spoon batter into 2 well-greased and floured 8 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour or until center springs back when pressed with finger tip.
Cool 10 minutes.

title: pecan log rolls
directions: Work sugar, Marshmallow Creme and vanilla together.
Roll out into rolls and refrigerate.
When cooled, dip rolls into melted caramel and roll in nuts.

title: queijadinhas (coconut sweets)
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix all ingredients well.
Drop 1/2 teaspoon in aluminum candy cups.
Bake until slightly browned.

title: fettuccine a la creme
directions: Cook the fettuccine in boiling, salted water until al dente. Drain well.
Melt the butter in a large skillet and saute the garlic for 3 to 4 minutes over low heat.
Remove the garlic from the skillet and discard.
Add the wine, salt, pepper, parsley and basil and simmer for 5 minutes.
Add the cream and heat through. Place the fettuccine in heated bowl.
Pour cream sauce and Parmesan cheese over the pasta and mix well.
Garnish with chives and serve.

title: corn bread stuffing
directions: Saute celery, onion and bell pepper in butter or margarine. Mix corn bread in stock and soup.
Beat eggs slightly.
Add milk and pepper.
Add to bread mixture, then add chopped celery, poultry seasoning, bell pepper and chopped onion.
Bake in a well-greased pan at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes, or use for stuffing bird.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix sugar, pumpkin and oil, then beat well.
Add flour, salt, spices and vanilla.
Dissolve soda in 1/4 cup water.
Add to mixture and blend well.
Add nuts, if desired.
Bake in loaf pans or juice cans to make round slices.
Fill cans only 1/2 full. Bake at 350° for 40 to 60 minutes or until done.

title: toffee squares
directions: Line a cookie sheet with foil.
Butter foil generously. Lay saltine crackers over entire sheet with salted side up.
Mix butter and brown sugar in saucepan.
Bring to a boil for 1 minute.
Drizzle this mixture over crackers.
Bake for 8 minutes at 325°.
Remove from oven and sprinkle chocolate chips over the top of crackers.
Place in refrigerator to chill.
When chocolate is set, break apart in squares.

title: pam's macaroni casserole
directions: First fry up ham cubes.
Make macaroni and cheese mixes as directed on boxes.
Combine all ingredients and simmer 20 minutes. Serves 4.

title: chocolate marshmallow torte
directions: Crush Oreo cookies (may remove cream filling if desired) and cover bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix puddings according to directions on package.
Pour on Oreo crust.
Melt marshmallows with 1 cup of milk in microwave.
(Mixture will separate and be runny.) Cool.
Add carton of whipped cream.
Pour over pudding layer. Garnish with additional crushed Oreos.
Keep refrigerated.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Mix together coconut and pecans.
Put in bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Prepare cake mix using directions on box.
Pour over coconut and pecan mixture.
Place margarine and cream cheese in saucepan and heat until warm enough to stir in confectioners sugar.
Spoon on top of cake batter.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Do not cut until cold.

title: pure and simple vanilla ice cream
directions: In a medium bowl, combine the sweetened condensed milk, water and vanilla. Mix well.

title: heath bar cake
directions: Crumble together the brown sugar, flour and margarine.
Save 1 cup.
Combine the vanilla, milk, baking soda, egg and water.
Add to the first mixture and blend.
Pour into an 8 x 12-inch pan.
Mix the reserved 1 cup crumb mixture, crushed Heath bars and chopped nuts for the topping.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pumpkin pie cake
directions: Blend all above ingredients, except yellow cake mix, walnuts and butter; beat well.
Pour into lightly greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle with 1 package yellow cake mix and 1 cup walnuts. Drizzle 1 1/2 cubes of butter (melted) on top of mixture.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream or ice cream. Serves 10 to 12.

title: fried rice and pork chops
directions: Fry pork chops until lightly browned, but not dry.
Cool and cut meat into narrow strips, discarding bone.
Leave two tablespoons of fat in skillet.
Saute onions, mushrooms and meat in fat.
Add rice; stir and drizzle soy sauce on mixture until brown in color, but not soupy (about 2 ounces soy sauce).

title: clam casserole
directions: Mix Ritz crackers and eggs with rest of ingredients.
Sprinkle top with crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: reception salad
directions: Drain the pineapple and reserve the juice.
Heat the juice to boiling and dissolve jello in it.
(Be sure jello is completely dissolved.)
Add the cream cheese while mixture is still hot and stir until the mixture is smooth.
Stir in the rest of the ingredients and pour into a dish or mold.
Chill until firm.

title: exotic chicken salad
directions: Combine chicken, celery, fruit and nuts; blend oil, orange juice, vinegar and seasonings.
Add to chicken mixture.
Allow to stand 1 hour in glass bowl.
Drain well.
Add mayonnaise and toss lightly.

title: lemon sauce
directions: Cook over low heat until thick and clear the sugar, cornstarch, salt, nutmeg and water.
Remove from heat.
Add butter and lemon juice.
Makes 1 1/3 cups sauce.
Great as a topping on cheese cake.

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients. Pour in pie crusts and chill. Very rich but good.

title: cucumber salad
directions: In large bowl, combine sour cream, onion, lemon juice, vinegar, salt and pepper.
Add cucumbers and mix them into the sauce.
Chill for at least 2 hours.
Then can stay about a week in the refrigerator.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: ham roll-ups
directions: Put cheese on ham and broccoli and roll up.
Place in shallow casserole seam side down.
Dilute the mushroom soup with sour cream.
Pour over roll-ups and sprinkle 1/2 cup grated cheese over that.
Bake at 350° for 3/4 to 1 hour until bubbly.
Remove from oven and cover with Durkee onion rings in can.
Return to oven 3 to 4 minutes.
Serve over noodles and rice.

title: mom's easy pickles
directions: Ingredients for 1 quart jar of pickles.

title: south-of-the-border corn
directions: Cook corn.
Combine rest of ingredients. Stir well.
Add to corn.
Also good brushed on corn-on-the-cob.

title: hamburger and potato casserole
directions: In a large baking pan, put on layer of hamburger, one layer of diced or sliced potatoes, one layer of onions, one layer of mangos and one layer of Cheddar cheese.
Repeat all with second layer, then pour cream of mushroom soup on top.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: cajun crawfish
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Mix with lemon juice, mayonnaise, ketchup, hot sauce and onions.
Add
crawfish.
Mix well.
Makes about 2 cups.
Serve with crackers.

title: jackstraw eggplant
directions: Cut eggplant in half lengthwise; pare, slice 1/2-inch thick. Cut slices in 1/2-inch strips.
Make batter.
Mix flour with salt. Combine egg, milk and salad oil; add gradually to flour, beating until smooth.
Dip eggplant strips in batter; drain well on wire rack.
Fry 2 to 5 minutes in deep hot fat (375°) or in shallow hot fat.
Drain on paper towels.
Sprinkle with salt and Parmesan cheese, if desired.
Makes 6 servings.

title: corn pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes until brown.

title: chocolate chip kiss cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix butter, sugar and vanilla.
Add flour and blend until smooth. Stir in mini chips. Mold dough around Kiss and place on ungreased pan.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.
Drizzle Hershey topping over cookies.

title: pineapple-glazed pork loin(microwave)
directions: Glaze:
Mix pineapple juice, mustard, ginger, paprika, brown sugar and cornstarch in a dish.
Microwave at High power for 1 minutes.
Stir well.
Microwave 30 seconds until mixture boils and thickens.

title: corn bread casserole
directions: Mix together and place in a greased baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour, or until set.

title: shoe peg corn casserole
directions: In casserole dish place green beans and corn.
Mix soup, sour cream, Cheddar cheese, onion and spread over green bean mixture. Crush crackers and sprinkle on top.
Sprinkle butter on crackers. Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Serve cold or hot.
Can be made ahead and refrigerated.

title: broccoli cheese salad
directions: Chop broccoli buds, discarding thick stems.
Peel and chop onion.
Mix broccoli, onion, shredded cheese and bacon in a large bowl.

title: relleno de pollo
directions: Peel and chop tomato.
Rinse chili peppers; discard seeds. Chop chili peppers.
Stir together chicken, chopped tomato and chopped chili peppers, vinegar and 1 teaspoon salt.
Chill mixture until ready to use.
Makes about 1 3/4 cups.
